title: seven layer bar
directions: Smash up grahams, layer them in bottom of pan.
Melt butter, pour over grahams.
Sprinkle a layer of chocolate chips, then a layer of butterscotch chips.
Next layer will be pecans.
Pour can of milk over the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken with celery and onions.
Remove from bone and cut into pieces.
Mix soup and milk.
Fold in sour cream.
Add chicken and prepared broccoli.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Prepare 1 package of stuffing mix or use Plainville stuffing as directed.
Cover entire top of casserole with stuffing.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Uncover for last 15 minutes.

title: pistachio fruit salad
directions: Sprinkle box of pudding into a bowl over pineapple.
Mix well.
Add nuts, cherries and Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: ham 'n cheese roll-ups
directions: In a small bowl, combine Cheddar cheese and cream cheese and butter until well blended.
Spread 1/4 cup of mixture on ham slice, repeat with remaining cheese mixture and ham slices.
Roll up; chill for several hours or wrap and freeze, if desired.
To serve, slice rolls into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Arrange slices on top of crackers.

title: original banana pudding
directions: Reserve 1 banana and 10 to 12 wafers for garnish.
Cook 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler.
Stir in 4 egg yolks and milk.
Cook, uncovered, in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover with wafers and sliced bananas.
Make 3 layers of each. Pour milk and egg mixture over bananas.
Beat egg whites; add 1/4 cup sugar.
Spread on top.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes, until brown.
Serve with wafers and sliced bananas.

title: chicken florentine(6 servings)
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions and then drain well.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter.
Cook in it and stir constantly garlic, basil and marjoram.
Add 1 tablespoon flour and mix well. Add 1/3 cup cream and spinach.
Place mixture on bottom of casserole.
Cover with chicken, which has been separated into smaller pieces. Melt 3 tablespoons butter.
Add 3 tablespoons flour and blend well.
Stir in and cook until thickened 3/4 cup cream, chicken stock and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Cover with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until cheese is bubbling.
May be refrigerated or frozen prior to cooking.
When ready to serve, return to room temperature before cooking.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, soup, celery, green pepper and onions.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Layer on olives, potato chips, almonds and stuffed olives.
Bake at 325° about 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Blend together sugar, shortening, vanilla and egg.
Add flour and mix until moist.
Place by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.

title: busy day pizza
directions: Brown sausage in a skillet.
Drain off grease.
Add oregano, garlic and tomato sauce to the sausage.
Mix well.
Turn off eyes of stove.
Sprinkle a place with small amount of flour.
Flatten biscuits to about 5-inches around with rolling pin or glass. Place biscuits on a greased cookie sheet and place sauce mixture in center of biscuit.
Add cheese.
Bake until 12 minutes is up at 400°.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender or mixer and chill.

title: crispy fried carrots
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients. Set aside.
Beat egg white until foamy. Stir in buttermilk and hot sauce.
Dip carrots in buttermilk mixture. Drain off excess moisture, then dredge in corn meal mixture. Fry in deep fat until lightly brown. Serve with meats and vegetable.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Bring all but vanilla to a boil for 3 minutes.
Add vanilla. Spoon over cake.

title: dream cream cherry cheesecake
directions: Prepare Dream Whip with 1/2 cup milk and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla. Set aside.
Cream the cream cheese, powdered sugar and 3 tablespoons milk.
Fold Dream Whip into cream cheese mixture. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Pour pie filling in center of pie, covering entire pie.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese and potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and top with crushed crackers.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: honey baked lima beans(something different)
directions: Wash beans; drain.
In a large saucepan, cover beans with water and refrigerate covered, overnight.

title: creole potato bread
directions: Bake yams;
remove
the meat and mash it with a liberal amount of butter. Then add next 7 ingredients.
If the mixture is too thin,
thicken
it	with
flour.
It
should be of the consistency of thick mashed potatoes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini into thin pieces.
Boil in water for 6 to 8 minutes.
(Shake pan to keep from burning.)
Drain well.
Combine sour cream, butter, grated cheese, salt and garlic powder over low heat until melted.
Add zucchini and mixture in casserole dish. Top with bread crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Make pudding according to instructions on box.
Let cool.
Add devil's food cake mix to pudding and mix.
Put into greased and floured cake pan. Sprinkle semi-sweet little bits on top. Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: quick and easy ham dish
directions: Saute peppers, onion and mushrooms in butter and garlic.
Add ham and stewed tomatoes, including juices; simmer until hot. Serve over rice.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Brown sausage in large Dutch oven.
Pour off excess fat.
Add celery and cook for 10 minutes, stirring often.
Add all remaining ingredients, except green pepper.

title: lemon lush
directions: Cream softened butter and flour; add sugar and nuts.
Press in Pyrex dish (9-inch square).
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.
Mix well cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip. Layer on cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk; add as next layer. Top with Cool Whip.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients together and set aside.
Cream oleo, sugar, eggs, sour cream and vanilla together; add to flour mixture.
Pour 1/2 of batter (it will be thick) into floured and greased Bundt pan.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans. Sprinkle over batter in pan, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Let stand a few minutes before turning out.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature so it will blend better.
Mix cream cheese and milk with electric mixer until smooth.
Add lemon juice and mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
If nuts are used, mix with fruit filling.
Pour on top of pie. Chill and serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook pepper and onion in 2 tablespoons of butter 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add flour mixed with seasonings and stir until blended.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Brown bread in 1 tablespoon of butter and add with corn and egg.
Turn into greased baking dish.
Cover with crumbs.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: mirro fruit cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add 3 eggs.
Mix and sift soda, salt and flour and add to first mixture with the cream.
Mix well and add nuts and raisins.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: trash
directions: In a large microwave-safe bowl, melt chocolate chips on High for 1 minute.
Stir; microwave 30 seconds longer or until chips are melted.
Stir in peanut butter.
Gently stir in cereal until well coated; set aside.
Place confectioners sugar in a 2-gallon plastic storage bag.
Add cereal mixture and shake until well coated.
Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator. Yield:
6 cups.

title: no knead yeast rolls
directions: Place 3 1/2 cups water, butter, salt and sugar in pan until butter is melted and sugar and salt is dissolved.
Mix good and transfer to a large bread bowl.
Cool.
Crumble yeast in a small bowl and sprinkle some sugar over top (about 1/2 teaspoon).
Cover with real warm water (not hot) until yeast is completely activated.
Add eggs to water mixture, beating with wire whisk. Add 5 cups flour.
Spread flour over top of water in bowl and add activated yeast.
Stir and add rest of flour.
Will be very sticky.
Cover with a flour sack towel and let rise about 2 hours. Spray roll tins with Pam and place some dough in each tin.
Dough will be very sticky.
Let raise another 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 375° until browned.

title: shrimp cocktail sauce
directions: Mix together all the ingredients.
Chill thoroughly.

title: texas style chili
directions: Heat oil in large kettle.
Add beef and brown.
Add garlic, chili powder, salt, oregano, cumin, pepper sauce and water; stir to mix well.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 1 1/4 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add cornmeal and mix well.
Simmer uncovered 30 minutes or until meat is tender.
Garnish with chopped onion, if desired.
Serve with rice and beans on the side.

title: freddy's egg souffle
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cube bread; place in bottom of baking dish.
Brown sausage and drain.
Spread pork sausage over bread cubes.
Combine eggs, milk, salt, pepper and ground mustard; beat well.
Pour over sausage and bread.
Spread cheese over top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Combine flour, pie spice, soda and salt in a large bowl.
Make well in center.

title: caribbean pineapple chicken
directions: Serves 2. Cut pineapple in half lengthwise and refrigerate one half.
Cut fruit from other half.
In a skillet, saute pineapple in oil over medium high heat until slightly browned.
Remove to plates.
Rub garlic on chicken.
Sprinkle with flour.
In same skillet, saute chicken, covered, in pan juices over medium high heat until browned; turn once.
Mix water, honey, soy sauce, lime juice, coconut extract and red pepper in cup; pour into skillet. Cover.
Simmer 12 to 15 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken to serving plates.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle with coconut, lime peel and cilantro.

title: crab-stuffed potatoes
directions: Slice baked potatoes in half.
Scoop pulp from inside and retain shells.
Mix together potato pulp, butter, cheese, sour cream, salt, onion, pepper and crab meat.
Fill potato shells with mixture and garnish with paprika.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix well and press into bottom of a 3-quart baking dish.

title: drop sand tarts
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Then add eggs, mix until creamy.
Add flour and baking soda.
Chill dough for 30 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet, flatten with bottom of a floured drinking glass.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
(You wil have to keep small bowl of flour to dip glass in every few cookies flattened.)

title: macaroon pie
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add baking powder and sugar; beat until stiff.
Fold in other ingredients and pour into greased pie plate. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: polk dot cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars; blend in egg and vanilla. Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Add alternately with milk. Mix well after each addition. Stir in chips, cherries and nuts. Place by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dot's punch
directions: Combine ingredients.
Make juice ring filled with orange, lime, peach, etc., slices to float in punch.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil fryer; skin, bone and cut into pieces.
Set aside.
Cook macaroni; set aside.
Fry pepper and onion in butter.
Add milk and flour; cook until thick.
Add cheese, mushrooms and pimentos, then add soups.
Add macaroni and the chicken with other ingredients.
Pour into baking dish; bake at 350° until brown. Serves 20.

title: payday bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1/3 cup margarine and egg. Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan for 12 to 18 minutes at 350°.

title: winter squash soup
directions: Dice squash and simmer in water with salt until tender.
Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Liquify all ingredients in food processor.
Add sherry; season to taste.
Heat to serve.
Garnish with almonds.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Melt butter and add spices.
Put in a few drops of hot sauce. Put pecans on cookie sheet; coat well with the butter and spice sauce.
Put in 300° oven for 20 minutes, stirring frequently. Store in glass jar.

title: white chocolate chip macadamia cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mushroom spread
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Save 2 Tbsp. drippings.
Crumble bacon; then cook mushrooms, onions, and garlic in reserved 2 Tbsp. of drippings. Stir in flour and seasonings.
Add cream cheese, soy and worcestershire.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Stir in sour cream and bacon.
DO NOT BOIL! 2 1/2 c. spread.

title: white chocolate and macadamia nut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside. In a large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy. Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture; mix well. Stir in white chocolate morsels and macadamia nuts. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Let stand 1 minute; remove from cookie sheet. Cool completely.

title: brownies
directions: Melt shortening and chocolate together.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to chocolate mixture.
Beat eggs; mix with sugar. Add to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut large pepper in half and remove seeds.
Place in roasting pan.
Mix 3 tablespoons catsup and 3 tablespoons mushroom soup in a small bowl.
Mix all other ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix with hands until well blended.
Fill peppers until all mixture is used (heaping, if necessary).
Use mixture in small bowl to spread over top.
Fill pan 1/4 full with water.
Cook in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Freeze leftover cooked peppers in foil for later use.

title: baked noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions until just tender. Drain.
Combine noodles with Swiss cheese.
Spoon into 10-inch pie plate or a casserole.
Cook bacon.
Drain.
Crumble.
Blend together the milk, sour cream, eggs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Add bacon.
Pour over noodles.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes until set.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar gradually.
Add eggs and beat well. Stir in vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, a little at a time.
Pour in milk slowly.
Fold in coconut.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with butter icing and cover with coconut.

title: fruit cake (dark)
directions: Chip fruit and nuts
the
size you desire.
Sift flour, baking powder, cloves
and
cinnamon
together.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs
together;
add
flour mixture alternately with milk. Thoroughly work fruit and nut mixture into cake batter. Spoon batter into a tube pan.
Bake in a slow oven at 300° for 1 hour, then at 350° for remainder of period about 2 hours.

title: soybean-cheese stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare peppers and set aside.
Grind or chop soybeans coarsely and combine with onion and cooked rice. Dissolve nutritional yeast in 1/4 cup stock or water.
Add the grated Cheddar cheese to rice-soybean mixture.
Salt to taste. Fill pepper halves and place them in casserole.
Pour 1 cup of stock or water into casserole or pan around (not over) peppers. Cover and bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover peppers and top them with Parmesan cheese and wheat germ.
Bake, uncovered, another 15 minutes or until peppers are tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, oleo and sugar.
Pat on bottom of 9 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Then fold into Cool Whip and spread on pretzel mix.
Mix Jell-O and water.
Stir in strawberries; refrigerate until partially set.
Pour over cheese layer and refrigerate.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice according to package; combine and set aside.
In saucepan, saute onion in butter.
Add soup, milk and Cheez Whiz.
Stir over medium heat until cheese melts.
Combine all in medium casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until center bubbles, approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: texas special
directions: Rinse ribs and spread on cookie sheet. Combine remaining ingredients and heat to boiling point. Spread on ribs.
Transfer ribs to charcoal grill that is white hot.
Barbecue, turning ribs and basting with sauce frequently.
Cook about 40 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: crab dip
directions: Heat mushroom soup, set aside.
Dissolve gelatin in 3 tbsp. water. Add to soup and stir.
Add cream cheese and mix.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Place in mold or serving dish. Refrigerate overnight or until firm.
Serve with carrot sticks, celery sticks, or other relishes.
Also tasty with Triscuits.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in boiling water for 6 or 7 minutes; drain well. Combine milk, soup and egg in a large bowl; mix well.
Add eggplant, onion and 3/4 cup of stuffing; toss lightly.
Turn into greased baking dish.
Finely crush remaining stuffing mix with butter.
Sprinkle over eggplant.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: best ever rice pudding
directions: Rinse rice.
Add to 1 quart water in heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat until the water is absorbed.
Remove from heat.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Add mayonnaise and milk together and blend.
Add remaining ingredients to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in unbaked pie shell.
Makes 2 (8-inch) pies.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ginger-applesauce bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: delicious lemon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Mix together ingredients in large bowl, beat at high speed about 10 minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Turn batter into tube pan and bake about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
While cake is baking, combine sauce to pour over cake when done.

title: hot spinach and artichoke dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach; add to bowl. Drain artichokes, chop into tiny pieces and add to bowl. Mix in garlic, cream cheese, Parmesan, mayo and lemon juice. Grease glass pie dish. Pour contents into pie dish and sprinkle mixture with breadcrumbs. Bake for 25 minutes (or until bubbling) at 375°. Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Cover chicken breast with bread crumbs.
Partly cut chicken to the middle, then put ham and cheese inside chicken and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes one sandwich.

title: corn bread sage dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in microwave for 3 minutes. Pour over the rest of the ingredients, blending well. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. You can layer your turkey over the dressing, if you wish.

title: corn meal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Stirring constantly. Boil 3 minutes.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cukes and onions
directions: Put a layer of cukes and a layer of onions.
Sprinkle a little dill weed over.
Repeat layers.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil and pour over cukes and onions.
Chill.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut margarine into dry cake mix until crumbly.
Mix in coconut.
Pat mixture lightly into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan, building up edges slightly.
Bake for 10 minutes. Arrange peach slices on warm crust.
Blend sour cream and egg; drizzle over peaches (will not completely cover peaches).
Bake for 25 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Do not overbake.
Serve warm.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: In large bowl, thoroughly mix 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and dry yeast (undissolved).
Combine milk, water and margarine in saucepan.
Heat over low heat until very warm (130°).
Margarine does not need to be melted.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed on mixer scraping bowl occasionally.
Add 1/2 cup flour and beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make soft dough.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and place bowl in pan of warm water.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Roll 3 balls and put in greased muffin pans (or shape as you wish) and let rise a few more minutes.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes or until done.

title: clam bisque
directions: In a large pot, saute onion in margarine.
Remove from heat; stir in flour.
Add clam juice and clams.
Let thicken and boil for 1 minute.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Blend in cream, tomato paste and lemon juice.
Heat slowly.
Makes 12 (1 cup) servings.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix chopped meat, eggs and bread crumbs together thoroughly. Shape into small meatballs.

title: savory bread sticks
directions: Melt butter and add spices.
Drizzle over hot dog buns that have been place on a large jelly roll pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°, until crisp.
These are very good snacks.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind the cranberries and orange.
Add the sugar and let stand overnight.
Dissolve the jello in the hot water.
Mix with cranberries, orange and sugar.
When starting to gel, add nuts, marshmallows, celery and salt together.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add remaining ingredients in order, blending until smooth.
Pour into hot well-greased skillet or pan. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.
Will serve 8.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar; mix in dry ingredients.
Add mixture and eggs.
Add vanilla; blend.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: coconut bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add coconut, sugar, vanilla and egg. Mix well. Add milk, a little at a time, until dough is firm but not sticky. Knead for a few minutes. Shape dough into 2 loaves and place into greased 5 x 9-inch (13 x 23 cm) loaf pans. Dust dough with sugar and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown. Makes 2 loaves.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Crumble cheese.
Blend with mayonnaise.
Add Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, onion and pepper.
Do not beat.
Add sour cream and buttermilk.
Stir and blend.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes 1 quart.

title: easy white fudge
directions: Boil slowly the sour cream and sugar, stirring constantly, to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add the vanilla and butter. Beat by hand until sets up.
When it starts to set up, add nuts of your choice and pour into greased pan.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry ground meat, onions and bell pepper, adding Mrs. Dash seasoning to taste.
Drain excess fat.
Add tomato soup, water and tomato sauce as well as cheese.
Stir.
Let cook on low heat for approximately forty-five minutes or until bubbly.
Serve over spaghetti noodles.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, salt 1/2 c. margarine and milk.
Roll out 18 x 12-inch.
Grate apples.
In saucepan combine water, sugar cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bring to boil and cook for 5 minutes.
Add remaining margarine.
Spread mixture over crust (reserve liquid for later).
Roll up like a jellyroll and cut 3/4 inch thick pieces.
Place cut slice sin large cake pan and carefully pour cooked juice over top.
Bake 425 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: calico bean soup
directions: In large pot, bring to a boil and let stand for 1 hour or soak beans overnight.
Return to boil and simmer slowly 3 hours. Simmer ham hocks in small pan with 4 cups water.
Drain reserving liquid.
Separate meat from bone and fat and set aside.
Add onion, tomatoes, vegetables, oregano, chili powder, lemon juice, salt and pepper to the cooking beans along with cooked meat and simmer 1 hour longer.
Skim fat from meat broth and add broth to cooking soup.
Serve hot.
Yields 16 servings.

title: grandmother helen's heavenly shrimp boats
directions: Cook shrimp in water at a boil for 3-5 minutes.
Mix shrimp, mayo, celery, onion and eggs.
Season according to taste with salt & pepper, mustard, worcestershire sauce, and lemon juice.
Spread into opened hotdog buns & sprinkle with grated cheese.
Top with sprinkle of paprika for color.
Place on cookie sheet & bake at 400 degrees for few minutes until they are golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: oven omelet brunch
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In oven, melt butter in a 13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Tilt dish to coat bottom with butter.
In large mixer bowl, beat eggs, sour cream, milk and salt until blended.
Stir in onion.
Pour into dish.
Bake until eggs are set, but still moist, about 35 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar with mixer; fold in other ingredients.
Freeze.
Leave out approximately 15 minutes before serving.

title: chicken cashew(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Mix half of noodles with all other ingredients.
Pour other half of noodles on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mother's mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Take from oven and while warm, spread one 7 ounce jar of Marshmallow Creme on top.
Let cool and then ice.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pinch off bite-sized pieces and form into balls.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.
Freezes well before cooking.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box in 8 or 9-inch cake pans.
While cake is baking, cook remaining ingredients except frosting until thick.
After cake is cold, split cake layers with a thread; put down first layer.
Spread with filling, then when stacked, frost with milk chocolate frosting.
I heat frosting in microwave about 40 seconds; it spreads over cake much easier.

title: tex-mex tortillas
directions: Combine cream cheese, green chilies, green onions and garlic salt in small bowl.
Spread 1 heaping tablespoonful of cream cheese mixture on each tortilla.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Place, seam side down, on baking sheet.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Slice each tortilla roll into slices, about 1/2-inch thick.
Serve with picante sauce.
Appetizers may be frozen.
To freeze, place uncut in freezer until frozen.
Store in airtight container.

title: banana-pecan spiced muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Coat a 12 muffin tin pan with a nonstick cooking spray. Combine and blend together the first eight ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add chopped pecans and 1/2 cup cranberries.
Mix until well coated.

title: pink stuff
directions: Note:
First four items are standard can or package size.

title: jean's tuna chili
directions: Drain tuna well.
Pour juice in saucepan.
Heat until warm and add chili seasoning to taste.
If you are using onions and want to use a large amount, saute them lightly and add to mixture.
Cook onions in juice a little.
Add beans and tuna.
Stir all ingredients and let cook 15 minutes.
Make sure onions are cooked to your liking.
Serve it in a nice bowl; sprinkle fat free cheese on top and serve with fat free crackers.
This is not as bad as it sounds.
Good substitute for chili if you are dieting.
You do not get indigestion from this chili.

title: 5 layer salad
directions: In large bowl, layer lettuce, pepper, peas and onion.
The top layer mix mayonnaise, sugar, salt and pepper; spread evenly. Top off with grated cheese.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: pecan sticks
directions: Blend butter, sugar and egg and beat well.
Add vanilla and the dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Mix well and add the pecans.
Spread in an 8 x 8-inch pan which has been buttered and lined on the bottom with waxed paper.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) until firm and light brown and the cookies have pulled away slightly from the sides of the pan.
Let cool for 5 minutes and cut into bars.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and arrange in an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Place cooked chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, milk and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter. Sprinkle over dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Mix in pecans, syrup and liquor. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Let stand 1 hour, uncovered.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Press pecan half in top of each ball.
Store in airtight container.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Spread potatoes in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix other five ingredients and spread over potatoes.
Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes and pour 1/4 cup melted butter over that.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain all cans. Mix together; add onion, cheese and mayonnaise. Pour in casserole dish. Top with Ritz crackers (crushed). Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish spray bottom with Pam.
Brown sausage and drain.
Line the bottom of baking dish with bread; top with sausage.
Mix eggs, half and half and cheese.
Pour over sausage.
Cover and put in the refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 45 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough out on your pizza pan or may use cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned. Cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Spread on cooled cookie crust.
Arrange sliced fruits on pizza.
Very pretty if fruits are placed in circles, beginning at outside edge.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and shape into a ball. Sprinkle with nuts. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Slice onions and saute until soft.
Dredge chicken breasts in flour mixed with paprika and pepper until well coated.
Brown coated chicken in softened onions until sealed.
Pour water over chicken and bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer.
Add 2 packages of soup mixture without noodles.
Continue to simmer until chicken is tender.
Use remaining flour/paprika mixture to broth, simmering until thick.
Add sour cream; mix well and serve over egg noodles.

title: chocolate dipped fruit
directions: Melt chocolate with shortening.
Prepare fruit for dipping. Using tongs or your hand, dip fruit halfway into melted chocolate. Place dipped fruit on waxed paper or into individual candy cups. Chill fruit.
Store in a cool place.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Mix all soups, broth and tomatoes together.
Cut tortillas in quarters.
Layer in a casserole dish: tortillas, chicken, soup mixture, onions and 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together; add water.
Cook on medium heat until mixture becomes thick.
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O and food coloring.
Stir until mixture is smooth.
Set aside to cool.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar, dry ingredients, fruits and nuts together. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Beat until thoroughly mixed.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch ceramic pie plate (ungreased) and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool thoroughly and top with Cool Whip.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and celery.
Add chili beans.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve with cheese crackers. (Good fast lunch.)

title: sour cream almond nut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sour cream and mix well.
Add dry ingredients which have been mixed together.
Mix until real creamy.
Add flavoring.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes before removing.
Frost with cream cheese frosting, if desired.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening until well blended.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add chips and stir only until incorporated into the batter. Do not overmix.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen large cookies or 4 dozen smaller cookies.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain.
Cook and drain noodles and add milk and soups.
Combine with sausage and onion and mix well. Cover with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 350°
for 30 minutes. Serves 12.

title: baked crabmeat
directions: Make a very rich, highly seasoned cream sauce with mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Add other ingredients; put in shells and top with buttered crumbs.
Bake until brown.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar and flour.
Stir in butter and mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup of the mixture and press remainder into an 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix meat, onion, bell pepper,
salt
and
pepper
in
a large pot.
(If you like meatballs, you
can
roll
a few into balls and bake in the oven.) Brown
meat;
pour off fat.
Pour in Ragu sauce, Lawry's spaghetti
mix,
steak
sauce,
garlic, water, Italian seasoning and oregano.
Let
your
taste
buds rule how much seasonings to use.
If
sauce	is too thick, add more water. If too thin, add a little more tomato paste.
Let simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cool and put in the refrigerator until the next day. Serve with cooked spaghetti.

title: russian tea(spiced tea)
directions: Put all in a cheesecloth bag in 1 gallon water and bring to boil.
Turn off fire and add juice of 4 oranges, 2 lemons and 2 1/2 to 3 cups sugar (according to your taste).
Serve.
May be put in crock-pot to keep warm for a holiday party.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old-fashioned lemonade
directions: Cut lemons into very thin slices. Remove seeds.
Place slices in large non-metal bowl. Sprinkle with sugar.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Press lemons with back of spoon to extract juice.
Add water, stirring and pressing lemons to extract juice.
Remove lemon slices.
Serve over ice.
If desired, garnish with additional lemon slices.
Makes 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll in small balls.
Dip in 1 (8 ounce) package of chocolate chips and one cake of paraffin wax, melted.
Cool on wax paper.

title: squash marmalade
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and bring to boil.
Boil for 20 minutes, stirring continuously; then stir in peach jello.
Can and seal.

title: bookbinder's rice pudding(yields 6 generous servings)
directions: Add rice to milk, seasoned with salt.
Cook on top of range, very slowly, for 2 hours.
(This slow cooking releases the rice starch to thicken the pudding.)
Add cinnamon stick the last hour of cooking.
Remove cinnamon stick and season with nutmeg, vanilla and sugar.
Add eggs and butter; mix well.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Note:
You may use corn bread mix and omit the first 3 ingredients.

title: ham n potatoes au gratin
directions: In a skillet, saute onions and green peppers in 1 tablespoon butter until tender. Combine onions and peppers with potatoes, ham and mayonnaise. Pour into ungreased 11 x 7 baking dish. In a saucepan, melt remaining butter. Stir in flour and pepper until smooth. Gradually add milk. Bring to a boil. Cook and stir for 1 minute. Stir in cheese just until melted. Pour over potato mixture. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix well.
Cook in 350° oven until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
(Egg custard may be made the same way. Take out the cocoa and add a tablespoon of flour.)

title: homemade hamburger helper
directions: Saute onion in large skillet.
Add spices to taste.
Add ground chuck.
Cook until browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Add 2 cans chopped tomatoes.
Cook at medium heat for about 30 minutes, until most of the juices have reduced, but still want it somewhat liquidy.

title: cajun shrimp dip
directions: In a bowl, mix salsa and shrimp; chill at least 1 hour.
Spoon into a bowl; top with sour cream and cilantro.
Serve as dip with Triscuits or any sturdy cracker.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes. May be put into 9 x 13 pan and baked 20 to 25 minutes, cut into bars.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Blend butter, sugar and eggs well.
Add remaining ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cran-mallow sweet potatoes
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, butter, orange juice and salt; whip in 1 cup marshmallows.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spoon cranberry sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover with marshmallows and return to oven until marshmallows are lightly browned.

title: prune cake
directions: Kream oil and 1 1/2 cups uv sugah together 'n add buttahmilk, flour, soda, allspice, sinnamun and nutmeg, one at a time.
Fold chopped prunes, chopped pecans and vanillah into kreamed mixture. Bake in a 10-inch greasy tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Let it stay in the pan while addin' icin' 'n then keep it still in the pan overnite.

title: sugarless raisin cake
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups water until water evaporates. Add applesauce, sweetener and oil. Mix well. Sift dry ingredients and add to applesauce mix. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Mix 3 eggs, butter, and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients, except 1/4 c. sugar and add to butter mixture.
Stir in chips.
Set aside 1 c. for top.
Spread in 9 x 13 pan.
Beat cheese, peanut butter, and rest of sugar until smooth.
Add remaining egg and milk. Carefully spread over batter.
Drop rest of batter on top and cut through with knife.
Bake at 350°F for 35 - 40 min.

title: apricot pie
directions: In a saucepan, mix pie filling and pineapple.
Mix sugar and cornstarch together, then add to filling and bring to a boil. Cook until thick.
Let mixture cool.
Add sliced bananas and pecans to the cool mixture.
Pour into pie shells and chill.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: pat's goodies
directions: Cream the cheese.
Add sugar, egg yolk and vanilla. Spread one package of crescent rolls on cookie sheet, pressing sides together.
Spread the cream cheese filling over the rolls.
Add the other package of rolls on top of this and pinch sides together.
Brush with egg white (unbeaten).
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Remove from oven and spread Glaze over pastry.

title: homemade cheesecake
directions: Combine in mixing bowl, cream cheese, sugar and eggs.
Mix until creamy and has no lumps.
Add vanilla, then add sour cream and continue mixing.
Pour mixture into 10-inch spring-form pan which has graham cracker crust on bottom (be sure you spray pan with Pam first).
Bake at 250° for 50 to 60 minutes in a convection oven or 2 to 3 hours in a conventional oven.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; set aside (should be crumblike texture).
Mix well the remaining 4 ingredients.

title: apple stack cake
directions: Put Crisco, sugar, molasses, buttermilk and soda on stove to get warm, "not hot." Add flour until you can work it dry. Also add 2 teaspoons vanilla flavoring. Grease an iron griddle; press out with hands to match the shape of the griddle. Bake in a hot oven at 450°. Check after 6 to 7 minutes.

title: southern biscuit muffins(for 12 muffins)
directions: In a bowl, combine the flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in the butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk, mixing just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix and bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: chicken asparagus casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except asparagus and almonds, then gently fold in asparagus and top with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Will serve about 10 to 12 people.

title: cheese and hot dog dish
directions: Put in dish and cook in oven at 375° until cheese is melted. Serve with salad.
Very good dish for dieters.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to boil over medium heat. Reduce heat to low and simmer 1/2 hour.

title: margaritas
directions: Mix ingredients together and keep in the refrigerator for future use.
For two drinks: Blend 1 cup mix and two shots tequila.
Serve in salted glass with lime garnish.

title: macaroni pudding
directions: Scald milk in heavy saucepan; do not boil.
Add macaroni; simmer, uncovered, stirring frequently until tender.
Beat eggs; add sugar and beat until thick and lemon colored.
Remove mixture from heat; stir in egg mixture and remaining ingredients.
Pour in lightly greased baking dish and bake in a 300° oven for 55 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: nut apple cake
directions: Cream together sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add dry ingredients to cream mixture.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inch) for 60 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Flour and brown chicken.
Place in baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caddo relish
directions: Put all together and pour vinegar over all ingredients. Set to boil and boil 5 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: easy vichyssoise
directions: Combine water, parsley and bouillon in saucepan.
Cover and bring to boiling.
Stir until bouillon is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add cream.
Stir in potatoes.
Cool to room temperature. Put mixture in blender.
Add onion and cream cheese.
Blend at high speed until smooth.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve in chilled bowls.
Garnish with chives.
A great dish for hot weather!

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into 2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chunky pecan syrup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy saucepan; mix well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to low and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Let cool; store in an airtight container in refrigerator.
Serve warm or at room temperature over ice cream or pancakes.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Roll out thin on floured surface.
Cut out with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for about 6 to 7
minutes.

title: carefree caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn in a brown grocery bag.
Combine next 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Microwave 2 1/2 minutes; stir well. Boil in microwave for 3 minutes; stir well.
Add soda and vanilla; stir very well.
Pour over corn in bag.
Shake very well. Microwave on High for 1 minute; shake well.
Microwave on High for 1 minute; shake well.
Microwave on High 1/2 minute; shake well. Microwave on High for 1/2 minute; shake well.
Pour onto cookie sheets.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Cook onions in butter until they are transparent.
Combine with other ingredients.
Put into a casserole dish and top with butter and bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: two friends gourmet butterbeaumont, texas
directions: Combine ingredients in food processor and whip until it changes colors and tastes right.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Combine milk, pie filling and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip. Freeze.
Several hours before serving: Remove from freezer and put in refrigerator.

title: giardiniera
directions: Place celery in large pot with vinegar, water, honey, fennel seed, celery seed and mustard seed.
Bring to a boil, stirring until well blended.
Add onions and continue boiling 5 minutes. Add peppers and peppercorns.
Boil 5 minutes more.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spray loaf pans with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: four fruit bake
directions: Drain fruit well.
Heat oven to 325°.
Melt butter.
Add sugar and cinnamon.
Place drained pears and peaches in casserole dish. Arrange pineapple slices on top.
Place cherries in rings of pineapple.
Pour butter-sugar mixture over top.
Bake 1 hour uncovered.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: potato romanoff
directions: Boil potatoes; drain and mash.
Stir in sour cream, 1 cup of cheese, onions, salt and pepper.
Turn into a casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or for several hours.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheddar biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix dry ingredients, sugar and cheese. Cut in shortening until mixture is crumbly.
Add milk all at once and stir with a fork until moistened.
Knead on floured surface 10 times.
Pat dough flat to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into biscuits, place on ungreased pan, edges touching, and bake 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: frijoles charros
directions: Put beans to boil with 5 garlic cloves and salt.
Fry the chorizo sausage, onion and the chopped tomato.
In a separate pan, fry the bacon, ham and sausage.
When the beans are almost cooked, take out the garlic cloves and add the beans to all the fried items and the hot peppers and chopped cilantro.
Let it cook for 15 minutes.

title: almond pine cones
directions: You
can
never
do
a kindness too soon, for you never know how soon it may be too late.

title: silver white cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 or 3 layer pans (8 or 9 x 1/2-inch) or an oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Blend flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in sifter.
Put in mixing bowl.
Add shortening, 2/3 cup of milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping the sides and bottom of the bowl constantly.
Add egg whites one at a time, beating batter for one minute after each egg white.
Add the rest of milk and beat for another minute. Pour into prepared pans and bake layers 25 to 30 minutes, oblong cake 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool 10 minutes in the pan.
Frost with seven minute frosting.

title: mushroom and broccoli soup
directions: Trim broccoli, using only bite-size flowerets and tender parts of stem.
Boil broccoli until tender in lightly salted water.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and mix until blended.
Cover.
Shake well before using.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos in blender; set aside.
Beat together margarine, cheese and sugar; set aside.
Mix pudding and milk.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Mix cream cheese mixture with pudding mixture.
Make a layer of cookies and then a layer of pudding.
Repeat 2 times and end up with a layer of cookies.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl mix oil, eggs and sugar together, then add zucchini.
Then add all dry ingredients; mix well.
Add vanilla and raisins and nuts if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes two large loaves or 3 small ones.

title: zesty roasted chicken and potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1 inch. Place chicken and potatoes in pan. Mix remain ingredients except chives; brush over chicken and potatoes. Bake uncovered 30 to 35 minutes or until potatoes are tender and juice of chicken is no longer pink when centers of thickest pieces are cut. Sprinkle with chives.
This has 17 grams carbohydrates.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Beat egg white at high speed with electric mixer until foamy. Gradually add sugar and continue beating until stiff peaks form. Fold in nuts. Combine butter and coated nuts in an 8-inch baking dish. Stir to coat thoroughly. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes. Cool before serving.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix together.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
Form in slender rolls and roll in chili powder.
Wrap in waxed paper and store in refrigerator or may be frozen.
Very good served on Ritz crackers for party snack.

title: simple sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix ingredients together; pour over chicken.
Cover chicken and cook 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and add crushed pineapple; cook for an extra 1/2 hour.

title: drop cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together and drop on greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° until done.

title: quick party rice
directions: Combine ingredients and bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes. Stir halfway through cooking.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Cover cabbage, pepper and carrots with cold water with 2 teaspoons salt added.
Prepare broth with sugar, celery seed, mustard seed and vinegar by bringing to a boil.
Cool.
Drain cabbage mixture from water.
Pour over cabbage.
Put into containers and freeze.

title: italian pork chops and manicotti
directions: Brown pork chops in oil.
Mix together in a medium bowl 2 cans tomato paste and 4 cans of water.
Add 1 teaspoon parsley, 1 teaspoon basil, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon pepper and the separated and peeled garlic cloves.
Place the browned pork chops in a Dutch oven and pour the tomato sauce over the pork chops. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer for 1 hour.
In a medium bowl, mix together cottage cheese, egg, softened cream cheese, 1 teaspoon parsley, 1 teaspoon basil, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Refrigerate until pork chops are finished simmering.
Cook manicotti shells according to directions on the box.
Rinse in cold water and drain.
Pour onto waxed paper.
In a 9 x 13 casserole dish, spoon a small amount of tomato sauce (enough to cover the bottom).
Fill the manicotti shells with the cottage cheese mixture and place in the casserole dish. Pour almost all of the remaining sauce over the manicotti (save some for the pork chops).
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve along with pork chops.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All. Pour into 1-quart casserole dish.
Melt oleo. Add half of the oleo and Cheez Whiz to Veg-All. Top with crushed crackers and remaining oleo. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut florets into bite size pieces.
Crumble bacon and broccoli with other ingredients.
Stir well.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours. Can be used as dip or spread on crackers.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In a medium skillet, saute onion in margarine until golden.
Set aside. In a medium bowl, mix egg and milk until blended.
Add corn and muffin mix. Mix well. Spread corn bread batter into baking dish. Spoon sauteed onions over top.
Spread sour cream over onions. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 35 minutes or until puffed and golden.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting into squares.
May be frozen and reheated. Serves 16.
Perfect with chili!

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
In baking dish, mix noodles and remaining ingredients (except peas and 1/4 bag of chips).
Mix, then gently fold in peas.
Top with 1/4 bag of chips and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin butter
directions: Cook the fruit butter over low heat, stirring constantly, until the sugar is dissolved.
Continue to cook, stirring frequently, until the mixture sheets from spoon. You can also place a small quantity on a plate.
When no rim of liquid separates around the edge of the butter, it is done.
Pour into hot sterilized jars.
Makes about 5 pints.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into balls 1-inch in diameter. Roll in powdered sugar.

title: kung pao pork
directions: Combine pork and 2 tablespoons soy sauce.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Combine remaining 2 tablespoons soy sauce, lemon juice, sugar, cornstarch, crushed pepper and 1/4 cup water.
In wok or large skillet, stir-fry pork and garlic in hot oil 3 minutes.
Add bell pepper.
Stir-fry 3 minutes.
Add cornstarch mixture.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Add peanuts enjoy.
Great served over rice.

title: mushroom meat balls
directions: Mix soup and water. Use 1/4 cup of soup mixture with other ingredients. Shape into meat balls about 1 1/2-inches. Brown in 1 tablespoon shortening in skillet; pour off drippings and add remaining soup mixture. Cover and cook over low heat for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serves 4.

title: salmon pasta
directions: Saute garlic in oil.
Add both tomato products.
Add salmon. Salt to taste.
Serve over pasta.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In large bowl, combine broccoli and cauliflower florets (cut to bite size if large).
Fry bacon; drain and crumble.
Add bacon, onion, tomato and eggs to florets.
In another bowl, combine mayonnaise (or salad dressing), sugar and vinegar.
Mix until smooth.
Chill everything.
Just before serving, pour dressing over salad.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender.
Add finely chopped onion, bell pepper and celery to the drained carrots; set aside. Mix and bring to boil soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour this hot mixture over vegetables.
Put in ice box.

title: harvest casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Saute, in water, onion, pepper, zucchini and tomatoes.
When partially cooked, add sausage and cook, covered, until tender.
Drain if necessary.
Add to macaroni.
Add tomato soup, salt and pepper (to taste).
Mix well; put in casserole and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together well.
Add cinnamon to taste.
Use 2 deep dish 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then turn oven down to 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork chops or steaks after dipping in flour.
Drain grease and cover with water.
Simmer until tender and water reduced greatly.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Set ice cream out to thaw enough to stir.
Add peanut butter and Cool Whip.
Put into crusts.
Put in freezer to freeze.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Stack in order in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften enough to mix with party dip.
Roll into ball and sprinkle nuts over ball and optional olives.
Wrap in foil and store in the refrigerator until ready to serve with crackers.

title: macaroni stew
directions: Dice bacon; saute until done.
Add green pepper, onion and garlic; saute.
Add ground beef; saute until brown.
Add tomatoes, breaking tomatoes up.
Add tomato juice; add salt and pepper to season.
Cook macaroni in boiling water until tender; drain.
Add to sauce.
Let stand for 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve in bowls.

title: glazed strawberry daiquiri cheesecake
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and butter in a small bowl.
Press into greased 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: bread pudding
directions: Toast bread.
Butter while hot.
Cut or break in pieces. Cover bottom of 9 x 11-inch baking dish with toast.
Sprinkle with raisins.
Stir salt and all but 2 tablespoons sugar into the beaten eggs.
Add milk and stir to mix well.
Pour over toast and let stand 10 minutes.
Press toast into milk to soak up the liquid.
Mix cinnamon and remaining sugar (use a little more sugar if you like it real sweet).
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shepherd pie
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Drain off fat.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, mix meat with soup and spread evenly.
Spread the vegetable(s) evenly over meat mixture.
Spread warmed leftover mashed potatoes over vegetable layer.
Heat in 400° oven about 30 minutes or until it is bubbly and potatoes are desired brownness.

title: vegetable quiche
directions: Cook frozen spinach and drain well.
Saute onions and garlic in butter till golden.
Add drained spinach.
Cook and stir till excess moisture evaporates.
Combine spinach mixture, Swiss cheese, eggs, milk, salt, basil and celery salt.
Turn into pie shell.
Arrange tomatoes around outer edge of quiche.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Lower oven to 350° and bake 10 minutes longer.
Combine crumbs and parmesan and sprinkle over tomatoes. Bake 10 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Butter bottom and sides of baking dish.
Rinse rice and place in dish.
Pour onion soup, undiluted, over rice.
Lay pieces of broiling size chicken over soup and rice, spreading out so each piece can brown.
Sprinkle with salt; add mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.

title: bug butter(baby bird food)
directions: *These are available from pet store.

title: no sugar cheesecake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a greased loaf pan.
Open oven door and let cheesecake sit in oven (oven turned off) for 1 hour.
Chill.
Top with cinnamon and serve.

title: chicken with onion gravy
directions: You will need 1 large oven cooking bag.

title: beet salad
directions: Heat 1 cup liquid drained from beets and pineapple to dissolve jello.
Add 3/4 cup cold water or juice and vinegar; cool.
Add pineapple and beets.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch square pan and refrigerate until set.
Top with sour cream or sour cream, mixed with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with nut meats.
Makes 9 large servings.

title: pork cutlets diane
directions: Press each cutlet into 1-inch thickness.
Sprinkle surfaces of cutlets with lemon pepper.
Heat butter in heavy skillet and cook cutlets 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Remove meat to warm serving platter.
Add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and mustard to skillet.
Cook, stirring with pan juices, until heated through. Pour sauce over the meat.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: date fingers
directions: Mix dates, sugar and butter in saucepan.
Cook over low heat 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, nuts and Rice Krispies. Scoop mixture with tablespoon.
Roll in coconut and shape like fingers.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: honey-glazed carrots
directions: In a large frying pan, combine the carrots, stock, honey and mustard.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes or until the carrots are tender.

title: jello salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and turn into dish or mold to set.

title: very special carrots
directions: In a shallow, covered pan, steam carrot slices in water 7 to 9 minutes, until barely tender.
Add a little more water if needed to prevent sticking.
Sprinkle with soy sauce and lemon juice. Toss to mix.
Add freshly ground pepper for garnish and flavor. Serves 2.
Or microwave, using 1 tablespoon of water.

title: hot dog chili sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in skillet. Drain. Mix all ingredients together in ground beef/onion mixture. Cook in slow cooker on low 6 to 8 hours.

title: chicken or beef curry
directions: Fry the chopped peppers and onion in a tablespoon of butter. Add frozen stir-fry vegetables and stir-fry for an additional 2 minutes.
Add broth.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all together; put in greased dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: parmesan bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 8 x 1 1/2-inch round pan.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds. Spread in pan; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into wedges; serve immediately.
Makes 8 wedges.

title: new mexico tallerine
directions: Cook onion and garlic in small amount of butter until wilted. Add ground round and brown.

title: chocolate glazed bailey's irish cream cheesecake
directions: For crust, preheat oven to 350°.
Finely grind graham crackers in processor.
Add butter and blend until combined.
Press crust mixture onto bottom (not sides) of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake crust until golden brown, about 8 minutes.
Transfer crust to rack.
Maintain oven temperature.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth until done.
Mix everything together and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and oil.
Pour over other ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: blini(russian pancakes)
directions: Mix 1/2 cup milk with the water.
Warm to about 120° (warm to the skin). Crumble in yeast and stir until smooth. Add about 1 cup flour to make a thick sponge.
Cover and let stand in a warm, draft-free place, 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Beat the egg yolks until frothy and add to the rest of the milk, butter, sugar and salt. Mix into sponge.
Add rest of the flour. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Let stand 45 minutes undisturbed.
Ladle into lightly buttered skillet, making pancakes 2 1/2 to 3-inches in diameter. Cook until brown on both sides. Serve hot with sour cream or yogurt (no syrup, please).
Caviar, optional.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, melted oleo and 3 tablespoons sugar. Pat a layer in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put remaining pretzels in another pan; save for topping.
Bake both for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cheese, Dream Whip and sugar.
Spread on cool pretzel layer.
Dissolve Jell-O; add frozen strawberries (slightly thawed).
Let set until slightly jelled.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Sprinkle crushed pretzels on top.
Refrigerate.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Grease 2 cookie sheets.
Place sugar, corn syrup and water in a glass bowl.
Cook in microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Stir in peanuts.
Cook on Roast setting for 11 more minutes.
Stir in margarine and soda.
Pour on cookie sheets and spread to 1/4-inch thickness.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Melt butter; beat in sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs and buttermilk.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Mmmm good!

title: easy chili
directions: Brown onions and meat.
Add all other ingredients and simmer 1 hour.

title: cream of wheat corn bread
directions: Beat eggs in milk and add to other ingredients.
Bake at 375° until brown.
You can substitute Egg Scramblers if you are watching cholesterol.
You can eat this if you cannot have regular corn bread.

title: jennifer's brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Melt butter over low heat.
Stir cocoa and sugar together.
Add melted butter.
Stir.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir.
Add flour and salt. Stir.
Add walnuts (optional).
Put everything in greased pan and spread out in an even layer.
Put in oven.
Let bake for about 40 to 50 minutes or until the brownies just begin to pull away from the sides.
Take out of oven and let cool.
Cut and enjoy!

title: crock pot candy
directions: Layer in slow cooker. Cook on low for 3 hours. Do not take lid off. After 3 hours stir about 5 minutes, dip out into clusters on wax paper.

title: a piggy apple(for the kids)
directions: You will need 5 wooden picks.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix first four ingredients well and chill.
Serve with Granny Smith apples for dipping.
Tastes like a caramel apple!
Yum!

title: calico fudge
directions: Boil white sugar, butter, heavy cream and white syrup until soft ball stage.
Stir in vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat.
Pour over large marshmallows (cut in half and placed in pan).
Cool, cut and enjoy.

title: baked beans texas style
directions: Mix all items together and put in a casserole dish.
Lay bacon on top.
Cover and cook at 300° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: baked fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease or foil line a 9 x 13-inch pan or rimmed cookie sheet.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Add water to egg white.
Dissolve sugar in egg white mixture. Add salt and spices; mix well.
Dip nuts in mixture.
Place nuts, flat side down, on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in very slow 250° oven until golden brown, about an hour.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Bring cocoa, oil and butter with Coke to a boil.
Set aside. Add 2 cups flour.
Add other ingredients well to mixture.
Grease and flour baking pan.
Bake at 350° until done approximately 30 minutes.

title: sweet endings chocolate bourbon pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine butter, sugar and corn syrup; mix well.
Beat in eggs until fluffy; stir in bourbon and vanilla; set aside.
Sprinkle chips over the bottom of pan.
Sprinkle pecans over the chips; pour filling on top.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place thawed hash browns in 13 x 9 x 2 greased casserole dish. Mix soup, sour cream, salt, pepper and onions.
Pour over potatoes. Top with the dressing mix that has been mixed with the melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 8 to 12.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine beef, egg, onion, Worcestershire and salt to taste. Shape into small balls.
Bake in a single layer at 350° for 25 minutes.
Drain excess fat.
Combine chili sauce, jelly and lemon juice.
Heat and add to meatballs.
Makes approximately 100 meatballs.

title: sweet potato hash
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover and cook 3 minutes.
Drain immediately and cover with cold water.
Drain.
Pat dry or let stand 15 minutes.

title: brisket
directions: Put in pan. Mix all ingredients together and smooth over meat. Pour barbecue sauce (your choice of barbecue sauce) over all. Cover with foil tightly. Bake at 250° for 7 hours.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Beat sugar and Crisco until creamy. Add eggs 1 at a time (beating well). Sift flours together. Add alternating with milk, stirring until just moistened, add vanilla. Pour in 3 greased and floured 9 inch pans. Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: happy home
directions: Blend together with a pinch of tenderness and one big dash of loyalty.
Blend in faith, hope and charity.
Add a spoon of compassion and gaiety that sings.
Also 1 of ability to laugh at little things.
Moisten with tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy. Bake in a pan of good nature and serve repeatedly.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and onion, stirring to crumble the meat as it browns.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add your favorite taco sauce to taste.
In a bowl, shred all vegetables and cheese together. Just before serving, add chips.
Serves 6 people.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix all together; then mix in cooked spaghetti.
Grate 8 ounces Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes (with a foil tent over); do not touch cheese.
Uncover last 5 minutes.
Can freeze before adding cheese and before baking (or freeze half). Chicken can be cooked the day before.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, cream cheese and 10x sugar together until well blended.
Add Cool Whip and pour in graham cracker crust. Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: carla's pumpkin dessert
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix and nuts over the top of pumpkin mixture.
Drizzle melted butter over the top of cake-nut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.
Good with Cool Whip.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: joyce's chocolate cake
directions: Mix the ingredients until thick and smooth.

title: heath bar cake
directions: In large bowl mix 2 cups brown sugar, 2 cups flour and margarine as for pie crust, take out 1 cup.
To the remainder add: egg, milk, soda, salt, and vanilla.
Put into a 13x9-inch pan. Sprinkle 1 cup of reserved crumb mixture on top of batter. Sprinkle 9 chopped heath bars over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop onions and peppers
fine
and
cover
with boiling water and let stand for 10 minutes.
Drain well.
Mix vinegar, salt, 1 pint water and sugar.
Mix
and bring to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes, then add the
chopped
vegetables and boil 5 to 10 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal while hot.

title: chicken spinach casserole
directions: Melt butter in large skillet. Add onion and chicken breasts and saut until chicken is slightly brown. Remove chicken from pan and place in baking dish. To the skillet drippings, add thawed spinach and cream cheese. Stir until cream cheese is melted. Salt and pepper to taste. Pour spinach mixture over chicken. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove foil. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Place back in the oven for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: spaghetti and ravioli sauce
directions: Fry
Italian sausage; drain and slice.
Brown ground beef; add all ingredients and simmer for at least 4 hours.
Serve over pasta.

title: zucchini bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Mix together eggs, oil and sugar.
Add chopped nuts and zucchini mixture.
Beat well.
Add flour, soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 5-inch greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Let cool 10 minutes and remove from the pan to cool completely.
For eggless, omit eggs and add 6 tablespoons of water.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine shortening, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat until well blended.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture just until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in an ungreased 9-inch square pan and set aside. Combine flour and the next 3 ingredients, stir well.
Spoon batter over peaches.
Combine sugar and water, stirring well. Pour slowly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Skin and boil chicken.
Cook broccoli; drain and butter.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Add curry powder.
Put broccoli in bottom of large casserole.
Chicken on top.
Pour soup over chicken.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top. Cook at 350° until bubbles.

title: chocolate "wet" cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour in
mixing bowl.
Bring butter, cocoa, shortening and water to boil in saucepan and pour over sugar and flour.
Add buttermilk, soda, cinnamon, vanilla and eggs in bowl. Mix together (batter will be thin and may splatter).
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° about 25 minutes.

title: 6 layer guacamole dip
directions: Mix together avocados, garlic powder, garlic salt, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Spread in dish.
Then layer on top the cream cheese, picante sauce, olives, tomatoes and grated cheese.
Chill.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together well.
This gets better the longer it stays.

title: venison hash
directions: Boil venison until tender in sage and water.
Cool, then tear meat into pieces to make into hash.
Add onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Brown in frying pan in a small amount of oil, until onions are done.
Serve hot.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown garlic and meat in hot olive oil in skillet.
Stir in onion soup mix, water, tomato paste and sauce, salt, pepper, sugar and oregano.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes (or more).
Cook lasagne noodles according to package directions.
Drain and place in cold water.
Remove from cold water as needed.
Place a small amount of meat mixture in bottom of 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Arrange single layer of lasagne noodles, placed lengthwise, then layer Mozzarella, cottage cheese, meat sauce and Parmesan in pan. Repeat, ending in meat sauce.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or longer.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: nutmeg lemon custard angel food cake
directions: Make batter for Lemon Custard Angel Food Cake as directed, except add 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg.
Bake as directed.
Cool.

title: glazed country cornish hens
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small saucepan, mix margarine, honey, mustard and orange marmalade.
Cook over low heat until margarine melts.
Stir until all ingredients are blended.
Rub Cornish hens well with poultry seasoning and black pepper.

title: heavenly bits
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, vanilla and water.
Add and mix thoroughly nuts and flour.
Form small bits of dough into little rolls 1-inch long.
Place close on baking sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Do not brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: Saute chicken.
In a saucepan, combine tomatillos, half the garlic, chiles and onion.
Cover with water and cook for 20 minutes.
Combine with remaining garlic and cilantro.
Process in the blender.
Heat tortillas in skillet.
Top with cheese and chicken.
Fold in half and pour hot green salsa over.

title: make ahead breakfast
directions: Butter large casserole or 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread diced bread on bottom of dish.

title: five layer dessert
directions: Put melted oleo in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs, then in layers add next 3 ingredients.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over all.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven.
For best results, spray pan with Pam.

title: potatoes delicious
directions: In salted water, boil potatoes with skins on.
When cool, peel and slice.
Saute chopped green onions (include tops) in butter. Mix with onions, chicken soup and sour cream.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In a skillet, fry bacon, remove from skillet and set aside. Saute green pepper, celery and onion in bacon drippings.
Add remaining ingredients except shrimp and rice.
Cook slowly until thick, stirring occasionally.
Before serving, add shrimp, stirring until shrimp are heated through.
Serve over rice and sprinkle with bacon.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: caponata from sicily(delicious & healthy)
directions: Cook cubed eggplant in slight amount of olive oil for about 5 minutes and add the rest of the ingredients. Cover and cook for 20 minutes stirring frequently. Uncover and cook 30 minutes more, or until thick. Serve hot or cold.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook rice and broccoli, separate as directed.
Saute together margarine, onion and celery on medium heat in saucepan.
Add cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Add Velveeta cheese to milk and soup mixture, then add sauteed mixture. Cook on low heat until chunks of cheese melt.
In 13 x 9-inch greased baking dish.
Add rice and chopped broccoli, folding lightly.
Pour sauteed mixture over rice and bake 1/2 hour on 350° or until done.

title: dried beef log
directions: Blend all ingredients except beef.
Shape into 2 (6-inch) rolls.
Then roll in chopped dried beef.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
Use crackers or cocktail rye bread.

title: apple pie
directions: Put apples in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Combine sugars, flour, salt and cinnamon; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix until crumbly.
Spread on top of apples.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°, then bake at 350° until pie cooks up in the middle, about 30 minutes.

title: batter dipped fried tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes.
Do not peel.
Cut into 3/4-inch slices.
Place on paper towels to drain.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Thaw lemonade.
Stir in lemon juice.
Add milk.
Fold in Cool Whip until smooth.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts and chill.

title: cabbage salad with creamy dressing
directions: Combine mustard, salt, pepper, basil, cayenne, lemon juice and heavy cream.
Chill thoroughly.
Just before serving, mix the cabbage, carrots and green onions together.
Beat the dressing until thick and pour over the salad.
Serve on lettuce cups.

title: cornflake cookie
directions: Combine in saucepan, sugar, salt and syrup on low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter until blended.
Pour over corn flakes. Spoon onto wax paper.

title: summer squash
directions: Cube squash; cook for 8 minutes in saucepan in small amount of salted water.
Drain.
Combine egg and tomatoes in bowl; add 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add remaining ingredients except bread.
Place in buttered casserole; place crumbled bread over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with powdered sugar, Rice Krispies and peanut butter.
Form into balls.
In separate container, melt 1/2 bar of paraffin wax and chocolate chips.
Dip balls in mixture; let sit on wax paper until dry.

title: hot beet soup
directions: Make soup stock of either beef, lamb or ham bone; strain. Grate beets coarsely; add to stock.
Cut onion in small pieces; fry lightly in butter (until soft).
Add to soup stock; bring to a boil.
Ladle off about a cupful of soup.
Allow to cool slightly. Then gradually stir partially cooled soup into sour cream.
Then pour cream mixture into the rest of soup which has been removed from heat.
(Cream will curdle if soup is too hot or if all of it is added to soup at once.)
Lemon juice may be added to soup for tartness.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix together and form into walnut size balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until just barely brown.
They will flatten out as they cook.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: ann's sawdust pie
directions: Partially bake the pie shell for 5 minutes in a 350° oven. Remove shell from oven, but leave the oven on while you mix filling.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Mix Dream Whip, milk and vanilla according to directions on package.
Beat until stiff.
Soften cream cheese in mixing bowl and gradually add sugar and Dream Whip, beating until smooth. Spread thin layer of cream cheese mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut angel food cake in thin slices, placing in bottom of pan.
Spoon remaining cheese mixture over slices of cake, covering completely.
Spoon cherry pie filling over cheese mixture.
Chill at least 6 hours and serve.

title: jello squares
directions: Heat all ingredients to boiling.
Boil 1 minute. Cool loaf pan with ice water.
Add Jell-O to cold pan, refrigerate 3 hours.
Cut into squares.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Let stand on waxed paper 8 hours.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat. Stir, let cool and add powdered sugar.
Mix and spread on 2 layers.

title: tomato jam
directions: Mix apples, tomatoes and orange; add sugar.
Boil until thick. Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Brown meat. Cook onion and celery in 1 cup water until tender. Drain. Add browned meat.
Mix all ingredients together and put in greased casserole.
Leave in juice from bean sprouts and mushrooms for liquid in casserole.
Bake 1 hour, covered, at 350°, then 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: black-eyed peas en casserole
directions: Cook peas as directed.
Mix with rice, ham, tomatoes, chopped onion and chopped green pepper.
Mix well; season with salt and pepper.
Pour into buttered casserole and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pickled okra
directions: Bring to boil water and vinegar.
Pack okra in jars and add to each jar 1 head dill or 1 teaspoon dill seed, 1 bud garlic and 1 small hot pepper.
Pour boiling water and vinegar mixture over okra and seal.

title: cheese potatoes
