directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° in a 2-quart buttered casserole for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with bottom pastry; trim even with edge of plate.
In a bowl, combine sugar, flour, tapioca and salt.
Mix well.
Set aside 2 tablespoons cream.
Combine remaining cream and vanilla.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add peaches; toss to coat.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Pour peach mixture into crust.
Roll remaining pastry.
Cut lovely vent pattern or make lattice strips.
Seal and flute edges.
Brush with reserved cream and sprinkle of sugar.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip squares
directions: Mix together sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in milk.
Mix in flour, salt, baking soda, oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Spread in a greased 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° until firm, about 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: Combine the 3 boxes dry ingredients with 3 cups water.
Cook until thickened.
Drain pineapple and oranges.
After pudding has cooled, add Cool Whip and fruit.
Chill.
Can serve with marshmallows on top.

title: super-stuffed sandwich loaf
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and yeast in mixing bowl.
Stir in oil and hot water.
Turn out on floured surface and knead for 4 minutes.
Roll dough to 14 x 10-inch rectangle.
Leave two inches uncovered on each end and arrange any combination of fillings on dough.
Roll as for jelly roll and place on well-greased cookie sheet or in well-greased loaf pan.
Let rise in warm place until light (35 to 40 minutes).
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes until lightly browned.
If using Italian sausage for filling, cook sausage in microwave or oven and slice thinly.
Then cook pepper and onion until tender.
Proceed as directed.

title: beef stew
directions: Saute onion in oil, put in diced beef pieces and garlic. Brown until onion and beef are tender.
Add tomato sauce and about 1 1/2 cups of water, also the parsley, salt and pepper.
Cook about 1/2 hour over a low heat.
Add chopped celery and carrots and diced potatoes.
Simmer for about another hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: impossible breakfast pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease glass pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inches. Cook sausage and onion in 10-inch skillet, stirring frequently, until sausage is fully cooked; drain.
Mix sausage mixture, potatoes and 1 cup cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients, except 1/4 cup cheese, with wire whisk or hand beater until smooth; pour into pie plate.
Bake about 40 minutes or until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake about 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: shrimp and pasta dish
directions: Cook pasta; set aside. In heavy skillet, melt butter. Add olive oil, onion, salt, pepper, garlic and Italian spices. Add shrimp and cook until shrimp are cooked through. Add pasta and cheese; toss. Add small amount of water if needed.

title: stuffed peanut yams
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
On baking sheet, arrange yams.
Bake for about 1 hour, or until fork-tender.
When cool enough to handle, halve lengthwise and scoop out yams, leaving shell intact.
In large bowl, mash yams.
Add milk, peanut butter, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Beat until fluffy.
Spoon into shells; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake until light brown, about 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: end-of-the-trail beans
directions: Mix all the beans and
other
ingredients
in
a
large baking dish;
mix well.
Cover with foil.
Place
in a 325° to 350° oven for 1 hour or until onions are tender.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Add baking powder.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken & rice
directions: Boil together the wings, neck, liver and gizzard to make broth. Sprinkle the rest of chicken with pepper, salt & paprika. Melt butter in frying pan. Add onion and rice. Cook until brown. Place rice mixture in casserole dish. Lay chicken on top of rice. Add broth and celery salt. Cover with foil and lid. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes in 350 degrees preheated oven.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put 1/2 of bread crumbs in large casserole dish.
Heat margarine in water; pour over bread crumbs.
Mix chicken, onions, celery, salad dressing, salt and pepper; pour over crumb mixture. Beat eggs with milk; pour over mixture (do not stir).
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
When ready to bake, spread soup and remainder of Pepperidge Farm crumbs on top.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken fingers
directions: Cut chicken breasts in slices or strips, about 3/8-inch thick. Toss in salt, pepper and flour.
Coat with egg mixture and toss with crumbs.
Spread on tray and refrigerate to set the crumbs. Heat oil in large frypan.
When hot, saute chicken strips 2 to 3 minutes, until crisp and brown.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Stir in flour, salt and nuts.
Chill dough.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes until set, but not brown.
While still warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Cool and roll in sugar again.

title: icebox pudding
directions: In a large bowl, mix up lime Jell-O and add crushed pineapple. Chill until set.
Put a layer of bananas, then wafers.
Top with 1/2 bowl of Cool Whip and chill.
Mix up strawberry Jell-O and chill until almost set.
Pour on top of Cool Whip mixture.
Add a layer of bananas and wafers.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and chill.

title: mom's apple crisp
directions: Put apples in square pan (8 x 8-inch).
Mix in sugar and sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Pat apples down flat.
Mix flour, sugar and margarine well in a bowl with a pastry blender and spread mixture evenly on top of apples.
Bake in a moderate oven about 350° until apples are tender and topping is a golden brown. Will serve 8.

title: quick chocolate mousse
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat Eagle Brand, pudding mix and water.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into serving dishes.
Chill.
Garnish as desired.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1 stick margarine and pour over potatoes.
Mix sour cream, onion, cheese, soup, salt and pepper.
Put over potatoes.
Combine crushed corn flakes and 1/2 cup melted margarine.
Put over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Arrange pecans in bottom of pie crust.
Beat eggs; add butter, syrup and vanilla.
Stir well. Combine sugar and flour and blend this with egg mixture.
Pour over nuts.
Let stand until nuts rise to surface.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add water and vanilla.
Mix well. Blend in flour and nuts.
Chill 4 hours.
Shape into fingers.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for about 20 minutes.
Cool slightly; roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cantaloupe ice cream
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until the mixture thickens and coats the spoon.
Remove from heat and cool. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 6-quart ice cream freezer and freeze according to freezer instructions.

title: easy  breakfast squares
directions: Put potatoes in buttered 9x13 pan.
Sprinkle with meat and cheeses.
Beat eggs with milk and pour over top.
Refrigerate overnight (or at least 3 hours).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or heat in microwave until hot.

title: reduced fat squash casserole
directions: In a saucepan, stew squash for 15 minutes.
Spray 2-quart casserole dish with Pam and set aside.

title: suspiciously scrumptious chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Cream together sugar and shortening. Add eggs and buttermilk. Beat well. Sift together flour, cocoa, salt and baking soda. Gradually add the dry ingredients to egg mixture. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and boiling water.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or more. Test with a toothpick.

title: gift of the gods
directions: Mix
well.
Use a sprig of parsley or celery to garnish roast or sausage.

title: microwave banana bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla. Stir in bananas and then remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 2-inch loaf glass pan. Cook in microwave on full power for 6 to 7 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let it stand 5 minutes. Turn out onto cooling rack.

title: easy family baked beans
directions: Saute the bacon until almost crisp.
Add the chopped onions; continue to saute until bacon is crisp.
Drain fat.
Combine bacon, onions, pork and beans, ketchup, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 50 to 55 minutes, or until beans are hot.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 6.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box.
Let cool.
Boil slowly sugar, milk and marshmallows until marshmallows melt.
Add coconut and stir well.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Put between layers and on top of cake.
Frosting will be juicy.

title: almond brickle cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Combine flour, sugar, butter, egg, baking soda and vanilla.
Beat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in brickle bits.
Shape rounded teaspoonfuls of dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheets. Flatten cookie with bottom of buttered glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 8 to 11 minutes or until edges are very lightly browned.

title: fabulous peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2 to 2-quart heavy saucepan add white sugar, white syrup and water.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally, until it reaches 235° on a candy thermometer.
Add oleo or butter and peanuts.
Continue boiling and stir constantly until it reaches 300° on thermometer.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and soda. Stir well, but do not overbeat, it will foam up some and you want this texture.
Pour onto two well-greased cookie sheets.
Cool, crack and enjoy!!!

title: norwegian salmon souffle
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in bread crumbs, butter and salt.
Add slighlty beaten egg yolks and cool mixture.
In a separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Add salmon to milk-yolk mixture. Then fold in beaten egg whites.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes and chopped onion in a bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix salad oil or olive oil with vinegar, salt, paprika and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Let stand several hours to marinate. Add cucumber, watercress and mayonnaise.
Mix well.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients together with an electric mixer.
Serve with veggies.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Add sifted dry ingredients. Add hot water, vanilla, apple and nuts.
Grease pie pan and add mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream or enjoy plain.

title: chicken la strata
directions: Put chicken breasts in flat casserole.
Mix together soups and sherry.
Pour this over chicken breasts.
Cover with almonds and bake in oven at 350° for 2 hours.

title: mock chicken dumplings
directions: Put bouillon cubes in hot water until melted.
Add the broth and chicken soup.
Bring to a rolling boil, then add dumplings. Don't add any salt.

title: italian chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, Ricotta cheese and vanilla.
Mix.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mom's apple swirl cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in pan (Corning Ware 12 x 12-inch square pan). Heat water and sugar in a saucepan until dissolved.
Make pie crust.
Roll out in rectangular shape.
Peel, core and chop apples finely.
Sprinkle cinnamon over apples.
Spread apples over pie crust.
Start at one end, roll pie crust and apples into a roll and cut in 1/2-inch thick slices.
Place in pan of melted margarine. Pour sugar water over slices.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: pillsbury basic roll dough
directions: Heat milk and margarine until very warm (130°).
In large bowl blend warm liquid, 1 cup flour, sugar, salt, yeast and egg on low speed.
Then beat on medium speed for 2 minutes Stir in enough flour to form soft dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl; let rise until double, 45 to 60 minutes.
Punch down.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix crushed cookies with butter; press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix pudding with milk.
Fold in softened ice cream. Stir together.
Pour over crust.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Spread with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with Heath bars.
Refrigerate.
Serve cool.

title: maude's tamale pie
directions: Mix all together in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes to 1 1/2 hours or until browned on top.
Can add a cup of diced, cooked chicken or beef (optional).

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Beat eggs; stir in milk.
Dip chicken in egg mixture.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Add water to cover bottom of pan and bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Do not turn chicken.

title: italian stew
directions: Brown beef, sausage and onions. Place in pan. Add sliced potatoes, carrots, beans, corn and stewed tomatoes. Add ketchup and Italian seasoning. Mix. Bake 2 hours at 325°. Mix cornstarch and water and add after 1 hour.

title: lasagna primavera
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

Cook and stir mushrooms in 1 tablespoon of margarine on medium-high heat until tender; remove from skillet. Cook carrots, onion and garlic in remaining 3 tablespoons of margarine 5 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Reduce heat to medium; add tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in mushrooms.
Mix together 2 cups of Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese, spinach and Parmesan cheese.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
In a well-greased cake pan, sprinkle nuts in the bottom.
Pour cake mix in pan.
Melt butter and mix it with cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread cream cheese mixture over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool in pan.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, eggs and oil.
Mix until well blended. Add combined flour, oats, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and soda. Mix well.
Pour into greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan, spreading evenly.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick in center comes out clean.
Cool completely before icing.

title: cool fruit salad
directions: Mix lemon juice and condensed milk.
Drain juice off fruit. Add the rest of the ingredients to Cool Whip.
Allow to set for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: snow peas
directions: Wash peas, trim ends and remove strings.
Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add snow peas and cook, stirring constantly until crisp-tender.
Spoon onto plate; garnish with pimiento strips.

title: corn pie with meat crust
directions: Combine egg, milk, 3/4 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper, Worcestershire sauce, onion and crumbs.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add ground meat and mix well.
Pack firmly on a 9-inch pie plate. Hold in place with another plate.
Bake in a 350° oven for 7 minutes.
Remove top plate and bake 3 minutes longer.

title: diet brownies
directions: Mix all.
Put in small pan.
Microwave on High 1 minute.

title: mama's pimento-cheese
directions: Grate mild Cheddar cheese.
Add well-drained pimento, salt and pepper.
Add mayonnaise as desired.
Good on sandwiches, crackers or celery.

title: debbie's sopaipillas
directions: Stir
together
flour,
baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening
until
mixture resembles corn meal.
Gradually add water; stir
with
a
fork (dough will be crumbly).
Turn onto floured surface; knead into small ball.
Divide dough in half, cover and
let
stand
for 10 minutes.
Roll each half into 12 1/2 x
10-inch rectangle.
Using a knife or cookie cutter, cut eighteen 2 1/2-inch squares or circles (do not reroll or patch dough).
Fry a
few
at a time in deep hot oil (425°) about 30 seconds per side.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with honey or powdered sugar and ground cinnamon.
Makes 18.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In a large bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in blueberries.
Add milk, egg, and butter.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
The batter will be lumpy.
Do not over-beat!
Spoon batter into twelve 2-1/2-inch greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400 for 25 minutes or until top springs back.
Serve warm.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt oleo and cook onions until soft, but not brown.
Grate Cheddar or Parmesan cheese.
Crush the Ritz crackers.
Layer onions and cheese; top with crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Combine milk, sugar and cornstarch and bring to a boil while stirring. After mixture boils, reduce heat and remove 2 to 3 tablespoons of mixture and let cool. After cooling, add the 2 to 3 tablespoons to the egg yolks and beat into a paste. Add vanilla flavoring and stir this into the milk, sugar and cornstarch mixture. Cook until thickened to taste. For banana pudding, pour this mixture over layers of bananas and vanilla wafers.

title: marinade pape'
directions: * Recipe under Miscellaneous or purchase a commercial brand from Chinese section in grocery store.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and flavoring.
Beat until smooth.
Add cream, in which soda has been dissolved.
Mix and then add flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir until a stiff batter is formed.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet or into a pan of flour.
Turn bits of dough over and shape into rounds.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook Uncle Ben's rice according to directions on box.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain both well.
Mix broccoli and rice with 1 can cream of mushroom soup (undiluted); mix well.
Add Velveeta cheese, sliced in chunks (reserve about 5 slices to top casserole with).
Mix well again.
Top with reserved slices of cheese.
Cook, covered, for 1 hour in a 375° oven or until thick and bubbly.

title: chicken bread
directions: Soften dry yeast in warm water.
Combine scalded milk, sugar and salt in large mixing bowl.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in unbeaten egg and yeast.
Add flour to form a soft dough.
Let rise in a warm place for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add chicken to risen dough; mix well.
Turn into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cover; let rise about 45 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot with sauce by heating 1 can of cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 cup milk.

title: mom's liver mush
directions: Cook liver until tender.
Cool and crumble into small pieces. Bring to a boil and add sage.
Reduce heat.
Mix well 1 cup meal and 1/3 cup flour and add to liver.
Cook slowly stirring constantly until mush thickens.
Pour into a bowl and cool.
Slice and flour each piece.
Fry in hot oil.

title: curry vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve with any chilled fresh vegetables.
Also good with party crackers.

title: chicken squares
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients.
Take crescent dinner rolls and press dough to form squares and cut in half.
In the center of each square, place 2 tablespoons of the mixture.
Bring all 4 corners together and press, closing all openings by pressing dough together.
Roll in melted butter and bread crumbs.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.
This is sooo good!

title: barbecued country style ribs
directions: Place ribs in large pan.
Add enough water to cover.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cook 30 minutes.
Remove ribs, drain.
Place on grill, cook about 50 minutes turning frequently.
Prepare orange sauce below.
Spoon sauce on ribs, cook 5 minutes.
Turn.
Spoon sauce on ribs.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Mix together.
(I usually combine this in a jar and shake well.)

title: breaded cauliflower
directions: Note:
The amount of the ingredients will vary depending upon the quantity of cauliflower you use.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and poppy seed.
Mix soda and sour cream together.
Add to mixture.
Mix well.
Add flour and then vanilla.
Mix well.
Fold in egg whites. Bake 1 hour at 350° in tube pan.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients for crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until light brown.
Top with cream cheese mixture made by combining the next 4 ingredients.
Add following fruits as desired:
strawberries, pineapple rings, cherries, bananas, etc. Make glaze of juices, sugar and cornstarch.
Boil mixture for 1 minute.
Cool, then pour over fruit.

title: holiday sausage swirls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate crescent rolls into rectangles.
Spread with a thin layer of uncooked sausage.
Top each rectangle with either 2 teaspoons mustard, 1 tablespoon jelly or 2 tablespoons cheese.
Roll from short end; chill until firm. Slice each roll into 4 slices.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot. Makes 32 swirls.

title: southern sweet potato bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cream butter; add brown sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, sweet potatoes, milk and orange rind.
Beat with mixer until thoroughly combined.
Add flour, nutmeg and allspice to sweet potato mixture with nuts.
Mix thoroughly until smooth.

title: heavenly cake topping
directions: Combine pudding, milk and cream cheese.
Spread over cake. Cover with pineapple, then cover with Cool Whip.
A real crowd pleaser!
Tastes great with any cake.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cornmeal and salt.
Add butter, lemon juice and rind and milk; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour into shell and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: spicy meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine everything and place in a 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake for 1 hour. Drain off excess fat before serving.

title: thin pancakes
directions: Mix all together.
Cook on hot skillet.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool and add finely cut corned beef, onion and celery.
Add salt and mayonnaise.
When it starts to thicken, add cut-up eggs.
Mix well.

title: captivating hawaiian pineapple
directions: Cut top off each pineapple.
Scoop out the center.
Place each pineapple in an open container.
Freeze 3 hours or until cavity is slightly icy.
In a small mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add 2 tablespoons of reserved syrup and the lemon peel and beat until fluffy.
Stir in fruit (cherries or strawberries) and almonds.
Fill each pineapple.
Return to freezer until filling is hardened (about 3 hours).
Just before serving, cut each pineapple into 8 slices.
Makes 16 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine corn, sour cream and slightly beaten eggs.
Add sugar and melted margarine.
Stir in muffin mix.
Pour batter in ungreased 8 x 11-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Remove from oven and top with cheese.
Return to oven for 6 to 8 minutes to melt cheese.

title: mexican salad
directions: Wash and drain kidney beans. Mix vegetables together. Add grated cheese and then toss with dressing. Add Fritos at serving time and toss thoroughly again.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix well and pat smooth into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: antipasto
directions: Mix all together and let sit.

title: calico cake
directions: Make white cake mix according to directions on box.
Divide batter into 6 smaller bowls.
Squirt drops of food coloring, making each bowl a different color.
Add cocoa to 1 bowl.
Leave 1 bowl white.
Grease 2 round layer cake pans.
Drop teaspoonfuls of different color batter into both pans, being careful not to overlap same colors.
Continue layers of colored batter on top being careful not to layer same colors on top of each layer.
Bake according to directions on cake mix box.
Cool and frost with your favorite frosting.

title: ramaki
directions: In bowl, combine soy sauce, oil, lemon juice, catsup, garlic and pepper; set aside.

title: pink peppermint punch
directions: Combine milk, extract and food coloring.
Chill well.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale and 2 scoops of vanilla ice cream until ice cream is melted.
Place a scoop of ice cream in each punch cup and add peppermint punch to fill.
Makes 18 one-half cup servings.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Pour macaroni into boiling water with cooking oil until tender, stirring to prevent sticking. Mix next: Break eggs into a 12-ounce glass; beat well. Add milk to fill remainder of glass. Add salt and pepper; mix well. Cut cheese into small cubes, saving enough to cut into slices to cover top of casserole.

title: sharon's cashew chicken casserole
directions: In a greased 9x13 baking dish layer macaroni, chicken, cheese, onion, celery, pepper and water chestnuts.
In a bowl combine soups, milk and broth.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Toss butter and cracker crumbs and sprinkle over casserole.
Top with cashews.
Bake uncovered at 350° 35-40 minutes, till tender.
Makes six servings.

title: crusty garlic bread
directions: In 6-quart mixing bowl, dissolve half the yeast in 1 cup water.
Add 1 cup of the flour and mix well.
Let this ferment overnight in a warm (75°) place.
Add the rest of the yeast and water.

Mix well. Add the sugar, oil, egg white, garlic, garlic powder, salt and as much of the flour as is needed to make a soft but not too sticky dough. Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic (6 to 7 minutes).

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, flour, Cheddar cheese and sugar.
Reserve juice.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Crumble crackers and mix with melted stick of butter.
Top casserole with mixture. Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: italian potatoes
directions: Wash and slice potatoes but do not peel.
Put in shallow 2 quart casserole dish.
Melt margarine and brush on top of potatoes, then sprinkle with salad dressing mix over the top. Pour water over potatoes.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Make into round balls and place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken, cut up and mix with soup and veggies.
(Veggies should be cooked al dente before mixing with chicken and soup.) Place one crust in pie plate. Fill with chicken mixture.
Top with second crust.
Brush top with beaten egg.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° or until crust is brown.
Easy, quick and delicious!

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Mix the dry ingredients in the order given, cutting the oil in.
Add the buttermilk and yeast mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Make dough into biscuits.
Place into a warm, greased pan.
Let rise 20 to 30 minutes. cook in hot oven (400°) until brown.
This dough can be stored in the refrigerator for several days if desired.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Add cooked chicken and mix well. Mix in deep Corningware dish the Ro-Tel tomatoes, cream of chicken soup and grated cheese; add chicken mixture to this.
Stir well and put enough Doritos chips to cover.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cinnamon syrup
directions: Bring to a boil the first 5 ingredients and cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter.
Stir to melt.
Serve over pancakes, waffles, etc.

title: homemade pot pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in greased casserole dish or cookie sheet.

title: great pork chops
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Reserve 4 tablespoons and pour remainder
over
chops.
Marinate
overnight.
Grill over low coals, turning and basting frequently until done, but still juicy and tender.
Combine
mushrooms with 5 tablespoons marinade and 1 tablespoon
butter.
Microwave
on
High
for 2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute.
Serve over chops.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Pour boiling water over broccoli to thaw; drain.
Layer ingredients in casserole, ending with bread cubes on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in buttered ring mold.
Set in pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Unmold on platter. Fill center with green vegetables.
(May be baked in loaf.)

title: squash dressing
directions: Chop onion and cook in oleo until onion looks clear.
Mash squash with fork.
Combine onion and oleo with slightly beaten eggs.
Add to soup, squash and bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Mix well; pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: uncooked fudge
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in pan on low heat.
Sift the powdered sugar into the melted mixture, then add milk and blend until well mixed.
Add salt, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Press into a buttered pan.
Chill and cut in squares.

title: 4 day cucumber pickles
directions: This
is
one
of the best pickles I have ever tried or tested.

title: spicy chili
directions: Cook ground beef, onions, garlic and green peppers until beef is browned.
Add chili powder; cook 1 minute longer.
Stir in tomatoes with their liquid, tomato paste, brown sugar, oregano, paprika and Tabasco sauce.
Heat to boiling; stir to break up tomatoes.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Stir in kidney beans with their liquid.
Heat through.
Serves 6. Contains 300 calories per serving.

title: four day make ahead sour cream fudge torte
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8-inch round pans. In large bowl, blend all cake ingredients at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at highest speed; pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan completely.
Split each layer in half, forming four layers.
Fill and frost layers with Sour Cream Coconut Filling.
If desired, garnish with pecans and maraschino cherries.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip with pudding.
Line bottom of dish with graham crackers.
Spread half of pudding and Cool Whip mixture.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Add remaining half of pudding and Cool Whip mixture.
Add another layer of crackers.
Spread chocolate frosting on this layer of graham crackers.
Chill.

title: kuchen bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in baking dish.
Mix some cinnamon and sugar together and sprinkle over top of batter.
Then melt 1/3 cup butter and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mulled cider
directions: Fresh unpasteurized cider works best.
In a large, heavy pot, combine cider, cinnamon and cloves.
Taste the mixture.
If the cider lacks flavor, add the orange juice or ginger ale.
Warm over medium heat for about 45 minutes.
Do not boil!
With a slotted spoon, remove the cloves.
Serve hot in mugs.
Yields 16 (8 ounce) servings.
Has 94 calories.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat until thick, about 1 hour.
Will be thicker when it cools.
Will keep for a long time in the refrigerator.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, 1/2 cup melted butter and sugar; mix well.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Cream eggs, confectioners sugar and 1 cup softened butter together until light and fluffy.
Pour over crust.
Spread pineapple over top.
Arrange banana halves over pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over bananas.
Sprinkle pecans. Indent (score) lightly into sections.
Place 1 cherry in center of each section.
Chill thoroughly.
A layer of strawberries may be placed over bananas for variation, if desired.

title: creamy butter frosting
directions: Boil water and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until creamy.

title: springtime  punch
directions: In a saucepan, bring sugar and water to a boil.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in other juices.
Refrigerate. Just before serving, combine with ginger ale.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Fix peppers and remove seeds.
Put peppers into boiling water for 2 or 3 minutes.
Remove and drain.
Cook rice as directed. Brown ground beef and onion.
Add to rice and mix.
Stuff peppers with mixture.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: potato salad(this is for a large crowd!)
directions: *You may use 1 qt. of one type of pickle if you prefer.

title: carrot bars
directions: Combine all ingredients together. Pour on large sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Frost while hot!

title: sierra salad
directions: In an 8 to 10-inch frying pan over medium-high heat, add walnuts. Stir or shake frequently until golden, about 3 minutes. Pour into a large bowl; add vinegar, olive oil and sesame oil. Pit and peel avocados. Cut into 1/2-inch chunks and add to bowl.
Add lettuce, tomatoes, mushrooms, red onion, olives, cheese and basil. Mix and add salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 8 servings.

title: jambalaya(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (180° C).
Cook bacon in large pan over medium heat.
When cooked, remove bacon and set aside.
Add onion and garlic to hot pan.
Cook for 8 minutes over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Stir in tomatoes, fennel and thyme; cook 5 minutes. Add rice, chicken stock, ham and cooked bacon.
Mix well; bring to a boil.
Cover; cook for 15 minutes in oven.
Add shrimp and peppers to pan.
Mix and add hot pepper sauce.
Cover and return to oven.
Continue cooking 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Fold gently with wooden spoon until well mixed.
Fold sour cream in last.

title: carrot cake
directions: Flour and oil 3 round cake pans.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in pans.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Use cream cheese icing.

title: baked french toast
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in saucepan; simmer until syrupy.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Place thick sliced bread on top of syrup mixture.
Beat eggs, milk and vanilla.
Pour over bread.
Cover pan; let stand in refrigerator overnight. Preheat oven to 350°.
Uncover and bake for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: noodle soup
directions: Make a broth.
When it comes to a boil, add noodles.
When broth comes to a boil again, add onions, celery and carrots. Boil just until the noodles are tender.
(Don't let the broth get thick.
Add 1 bouillon cube per cup of water.)
Chicken may be added.
Remove celery stalks and serve.
Serves 4.

title: saucy meatballs
directions: Mix all together.
Shape into 60 to 65 small balls the size of a walnut.
Melt butter in frying pan.
Brown meatballs.
May be chilled or frozen until ready to use.
To cook, put meatballs into casserole and cover with Pineapple Sauce.
Bake in 350° oven for about 40 minutes until hot.

title: maryland fish fillets
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan over low heat.
Stir in flour. Continue to stir and cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour in milk, whisking constantly, until the sauce comes to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: spinach bars
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Mix with other ingredients.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and add mixture, patting down.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and cut into bars.
Can be prepared ahead and baked when needed.

title: eggplant pie
directions: Heat broiler.
Arrange eggplant in one layer on a baking sheet; sprinkle with salt and pepper and broil 6 inches from the heat for 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Heat oven to 375°. Line 10-inch pie plate with the eggplant, browned side down. Arrange slices of tomato, pepper and onion over eggplant.
Drizzle with oil and sprinkle with garlic and oregano.
Bake 25 minutes. Arrange Mozzarella slices on top of pie and sprinkle with Parmesan and bake 15 minutes longer.
Cut in wedges to serve.

title: garden "good stuff" salad
directions: Peel tomatoes and cut in pieces over large salad bowl, letting all the juice go into bowl.
(The juices will marinate the mixture later.)
Add pepper, cucumber, onion and salt to tomatoes. Toss mixture and refrigerate for several hours for juices to blend together.
Serve in salad bowls for mixture will be juicy.

title: simple chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: foolproof pie dough
directions: Mix flour, salt, sugar and Crisco.
In separate dish, mix egg, water and vinegar.
Combine mixtures and chill.
Can be chilled from 1 1/2 hours to 3 days.
Take out and roll at once.

title: baked beans
directions: Use the cheapest canned baked beans you can.
I use 3 cans with this recipe.
Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: ring-a-lings
directions: Soften 2 yeast cakes in 1/4 cup lukewarm water or 2 packages dry yeast in 1/4 cup very warm water.
Combine butter and hot scalded milk.
Stir until butter melts.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add sugar, salt, orange rind, eggs and yeast mixture.
Gradually add flour to form stiff dough.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover and let stand 30 minutes.

title: spanish rice with sausage
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and save.
Saute onion and green pepper in bacon drippings.
Add tomatoes, seasonings, uncooked rice and sausage; mix well.
Add water and stir.
Simmer on low heat until rice is tender.
Crumble bacon over the top of casserole and serve.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake as directed on box and bake in two round cake pans. Cool.
To assemble in bowl, place one cake layer in bottom of punch bowl.
Prepare pudding according to box.
Use half on first layer.
Slice enough bananas to cover top of pudding.
Pour 1/2 can pineapple, juice and all, over bananas.
Put one box of strawberries over pineapple.
Top with 1 carton of whipped topping.
Repeat layers.
Refrigerate.
Nice for large gatherings.

title: party pink punch
directions: Dissolve sugar and Kool-Aid with warm water. Combine all ingredients. Serves 45.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a 9 x 13 inch pan for 1 hour at 350.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, well, then roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool, blot on paper towel and place in sauce.

title: super smore brownies
directions: Melt unsweetened chocolate and butter in small saucepan over low heat.
Cool slightly.
Beat eggs in small bowl with mixer. Gradually beat in sugar until thick and fluffy. Gradually stir in chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Fold in flour and salt until well blended. Spread evenly in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until shiny and firm on top. Remove from oven and immediately put chocolate chips and marshmallows and then lay graham crackers on top of that.
(Weight it down with a heavy pan.
You might want to double recipe and put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.)
When cool, cut into squares and enjoy.

title: chocolate peanuts
directions: Betty uses 1 pound of almond bark and adds 1 cup of chunky peanut butter.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Mix together remaining ingredients. Use enough juice to moisten.
Roll into a log and chill in refrigerator until firm.
To serve, slice into half-inch pieces.

title: apple rice dessert
directions: Add brown
sugar and butter to hot rice and blend until melted.
Add
the
remaining
ingredients
and
blend
gently. Serve warm
or chilled, with additional Cool Whip, if desired. Serves 8.

title: chicken with mushrooms
directions: Dip the cubed steak pieces in flour and then place in skillet. Sprinkle slices of onion over the steak.
Fry the meat to brown. Do not overcook.
Make a gravy from the skillet drippings by adding flour to the skillet drippings and then add milk to make a medium thick gravy.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put steak in a pan and pour gravy over it.
Place in oven and allow to cook slowly for about 1 hour or until meat is tender.

title: easy broccoli quiche
directions: Cook broccoli in a small amount of water for about 6 to 8 minutes; drain.
Place broccoli in a lightly greased 9-inch pie pan.
You may use Pam if desired.
Sprinkle with green pepper, onion and cheese.
Set aside.
Blend remaining ingredients in a blender for 15 seconds or until smooth.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti shells as directed on package; drain. Mix onion, spinach, instant bouillon, garlic powder, thyme, cottage cheese, eggs, and Parmesan cheese. Fill shells with spinach mixture. Arrange in greased 13x9x2 baking pan. Pour tomato sauce over shells, and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Cover and bake at 350° until hot and bubbly. About 25 minutes.

title: scalloped salmon
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a greased casserole. Sprinkle parsley flakes on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix chicken, soup and sour cream together; put in baking dish. Melt butter; mix with crushed crackers.
Top chicken mixture; sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini-vermicelli toss
directions: Cook vermicelli.
Two minutes before vermicelli is cooked, add the zucchini to the pot and cook until vermicelli is tender. Drain.

title: war cake
directions: Boil brown sugar, hot water, shortening, raisins, cinnamon and cloves 5 minutes; cool.
Add soda dissolved in warm water, salt and flour.

title: peanut butter drops
directions: Mix together in top of double boiler; stir until mixture is glossy.
Put 4 cups Special K cereal in large bowl.
Pour mixture into cereal and stir until blended.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Wet your fingers and shape them any way you want.
Fun for kids.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In butter, brown onion, green pepper and garlic.
Simmer until pepper is tender.
Add tomatoes, paprika, salt and pepper. Boil 5 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Boil for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry angel cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries. Just as it begins to thicken, fold in 2/3 of container of frozen whipped topping.
Add cake pieces and fold together until well coated.
Pour into tube pan and refrigerate to set.
Unmold on cake plate and ice with remaining whipped topping, tinted a pale pink. Decorate with fresh strawberries and mint leaves, if desired.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Marinate chicken 15 minutes in soy sauce, cornstarch, sherry, salt, garlic and ginger.

title: cottage cheese molded salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Allow to cool until syrupy state; beat until frothy.
Mix mayonnaise and half and half; beat until blended.
Add onion, green pepper, carrot and cottage cheese.
Turn into large mold.
Refrigerate.
Unmold just before serving.

title: camp out beans
directions: Cook ground beef, chopped bacon and onions.
Add all other items.
Heat until hot and bubbly.
Serve.

title: taco casserole
directions: Press 1 package of rolls in greased 9 x 13 pan. Spread ground beef on rolls. Add taco sauce. Top with cheese. Flatten the remaining crescent rolls and place on top. Bake at 350° until crust is golden brown.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown beef in large frying pan.
Cut up bacon and add to beef, with onions and fry until bacon is done.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend thoroughly.
Cover, bake in 13 x 9-inch pan for 45 to 60 minutes at 350° until some of the juices bake off.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Add just enough water to cover first five ingredients.
Simmer until tender.
Add butter and cheese.
When cheese melts, add milk.
Thicken slightly.

title: three-cheese italian meat loaf
directions: Defrost spinach; drain to remove all moisture.
Mix together all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Add bread crumbs and mix until mixture becomes somewhat dry.
Press into loaf pan.
Bake at 350°.
Drain off any grease.
If desired, serve with Italian marinara sauce.

title: applesauce
directions: Cook apples in water or juice until tender, about 30 minutes. Cool slightly and mash with fork.
Add raisins, cinnamon and sugar.
Makes about 4 cups.
Can be stored in freezer.

title: instant salad or dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: aunt sherry's dip
directions: Mix well.
Let stand in refrigerator for at least 1 hour before using.

title: chow chow relish
directions: Grind all vegetables; add salt and let stand 1/2 hour.
Then press dry with hands.
Get out all the water possible.
Mix with other ingredients and cook 1 hour or until thick as desired.
A few red peppers add color and flavor.

title: oodles of noodles
directions: Break Steak-ums into bite sized pieces and put into medium frying pan.
Brown meat.
Add flavor packets from noodles.
Add 1 cup water and broccoli. Cover and let simmer until broccoli is tender. In large pot, bring water to a boil, then add noodles.
Remove from heat.
When noodles are tender, drain and combine with meat and broccoli.
Use soy sauce to taste.

title: special french bread
directions: Put all ingredients (except bread) in bowl and whip with hand mixer until light and fluffy.
Cut bread in half lengthwise. Spread mixture on bread lightly.
Broil until lightly brown. Grated Mozzarella can be placed on top before broiling.

title: "tang" tea
directions: Mix thoroughly and put in a tight jar.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Cover bottom of 11 x 7-inch baking pan (jelly roll pan) with the sheets of crescent roll dough, patting and stretching it to fit.
Bake in a 350° oven for 7 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: krispy nut chews
directions: Melt vanilla chips and chunky peanut butter in microwave. Add Rice Krispies, Spanish peanuts and mini marshmallows. Mix all together. Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper on cookie sheet. Chill in the refrigerator until hardened.

title: helen's chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: raisin creme pie
directions: Mix in saucepan the 3 tablespoons cornstarch, flour, sugar and salt.
Gradually add 3 cups milk.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir 1 cup hot milk mixture slowly into egg yolks.
Mix.
Boil 1 minute more. Blend in 1 tablespoon butter and vanilla.
Wash and boil raisins in the 1 cup of water until half the liquid remains.
Stir in brown sugar, remaining cornstarch and butter.
Add to cream mixture.
Cool.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Pour mixture over sliced cucumbers and onions.
Put in closed containers (do not seal).
Refrigerate. Will keep 1 year.
Ready to eat in 1 week.
Stir once a day for 1 week.

title: cabbage, potato, onion casserole
directions: Layer cabbage, onions, potatoes, salt and pepper in casserole; put in microwave oven on High 10 minutes.
Stir and turn and cook about 10 minutes more or until done.
Put only a little water in it to cook.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and boil to soft ball stage.
Add chunk of butter and vanilla.
Let stand until cool.
Beat until creamy; add nuts, if desired.
Pour into buttered plate and cut into squares.

title: heirloom fruit-nut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs;
beat until light and fluffy.
Sift flour, salt, baking pwd. and spices.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in nuts, raisins and fruit; stir thoroughly.
Drop by tsp. onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 min. or slightly brown.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: rolled dumplings
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Beat egg and add to dry ingredients.
Add enough milk to make a soft dough.
Knead.
Roll dough paper-thin.
Let set 15 or 20 minutes to dry a little.
Cut into 3 inch lengths by 1 1/2 inches.
Drop into boiling chicken broth.
Cover and simmer 15 or 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° between 8 and 12 minutes.

title: fudge sundae pie
directions: Chill baked crust.
Put milk, chocolate and salt in saucepan. Stir over low heat until chocolate melts completely and mixture thickens.
Take off heat and stir in marshmallows until melted and mixture is smooth.
Cool to room temperature.
Spoon 1/2 of ice cream in pie shell.
Cover with 1/2 chocolate mixture. Repeat with rest of ice cream and chocolate.
Top with pecans.
Freeze until firm (about 5 hours).
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add sugar to water and bring to boiling point to dissolve gelatin.
Add fruit juices. Chill until slightly thickened. Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: janet's banana pudding
directions: In medium saucepan, mix flour and sugar. Add beaten egg yokes and milk.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened. Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.Layer pan with vanilla wafers, sliced bananas and pudding mixture.
Make meringue by beating egg whites until stiff, adding 1/4 c. sugar at the end. Top pudding with meringue.
Bake in preheated 425 degree oven for 5 minutes or until meringue is slightly browned.

title: oh henry bars
directions: Combine syrup and sugar. Bring to a full boil. Remove from stove and add peanut butter and Special K flakes. Mix well. Press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. In a double boiler, melt chocolate bits and butterscotch bits. Spread on top of first mixture. Cool. Cut into bars.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice.
Mix cornstarch with a little milk, add egg yolks and mix well.
Add this mixture and the rest of the milk to the rice.
Add sugar.
Cook in a large pot until thickened, 2 to 3 minutes of boiling.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into rice.
Add vanilla.
Pour into bowl and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: boneless chicken breast creole
directions: Place flour in bag big enough to hold chicken.
Add ground thyme, pepper and garlic powder.
Shake to blend flour and spices. Put chicken in bag and shake until coated.
Heat oil in pan and saute chicken breast 10 minutes per side.
Remove from pan and saute onion and green pepper for 5 minutes.
Add tomato and its juice.
Cook 5 minutes.
Return chicken to pan.
Cover and let simmer 5 minutes.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Mix all together and cook 45 minutes in a 400° oven.
Dot top with butter before cooking.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole; dot with butter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and Wesson oil in mixing bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add carrots, walnuts and remainder of ingredients.
Mix until sugar is dissolved.
Pour in greased tube pan lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour tuna crackers
directions: Flake tuna and combine with all ingredients in a 1-quart mixing bowl.
Blend thoroughly.
Spread on crackers.
Arrange 12 on paper plate.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 1 to 3 minutes, until bubbling.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Wash kraut in cold water.
Cook over low heat with 1/2 cup water.
Cut bacon in small pieces and brown with onion.
Drain fat off bacon.
Add kraut; add caraway seed and sugar.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.

title: blueberry or fruit kuchen
directions: Combine first three ingredients; work in butter and mix in vinegar.
In 8-inch spring-form pan, spread crust on bottom and 1-inch up sides.
Combine sugar, flour and spice.
Add 3 cups blueberries.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes. Remove and cool.
Remove rim.
Before serving, sprinkle powdered sugar.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: fruit cocktail torte
directions: Beat egg and sugar.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix.
Add the drained fruit cocktail.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Cover with nuts and brown sugar before baking.

title: split pea and barley soup
directions: Put all ingredients in a 3 to 4-quart pot. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, one hour, until peas begin to fall apart and vegetables are cooked tender.

title: alabama cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually, beating well at medium speed with electric mixer.
Add eggs and vanilla, beating well. Combine flour and salt; add to creamed mixture, beating well. Stir in oats and remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove to wire rack and cool.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: my sister shirley's baked beans
directions: Place all of above in oven-proof casserole dish.
Cover & bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake for another hour.

title: cheesy spinach bake
directions: Drain and squeeze liquid out of spinach.
Combine all ingredients; pour into 1-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ground beef chop suey
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add celery, onion and meat; cook about 5 minutes, until meat begins to brown.
Blend starch with water, then stir in soy sauce and salt.
Add this mix to the meat and cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Stir in cabbage and sprouts; cook 5 minutes.
Serve over brown rice.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix together berries, eggs and oil; set aside.
Mix all other ingredients in large bowl.
Add strawberry mixture.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans (9 x 5-inches).
Bake one hour or until toothpick comes out clean at 350°.
Best if quite ripe berries are used.
Can be frozen.

title: mud pie
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients and whip.
Melt the chocolate chips and add to above mixture.
Add the eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Pour into the pie shells and freeze until 1 hour before serving with Cool Whip.

title: cook-out hamburgers
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Make 6 patties.
Broil 5 to 7 minutes or longer.
Baste with barbecue sauce on both sides. (Won't dry out or fall apart.)

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Excellent for beef, chicken or pork.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans and drain.
Add can of cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Stir together.
Fold in French fried onions.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge
directions: Lightly grease an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Combine dry ingredients in a heavy 4-quart saucepan.
Stir in milk.
Bring to a bubbly boil, over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil, without stirring, to 234° (soft ball stage) or drop in some cold water and it will form a soft ball.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Cool at room temperature and beat with wooden spoon until fudge thickens and loses its gloss.
Quickly spread into pan.
Cool completely.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice together.
Place in crust; place in refrigerator to chill, about 2 hours.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oats, water and margarine.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Add sugars and eggs.
Stir in flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg. Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine the diced apples, celery, mayonnaise and mustard. Arrange salad on the chopped lettuce and top with the walnuts. Serve at once as the apples will discolor if left out.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Swish oil in 9 x 13-inch pan. Add cake mix, coconut, pineapple, water and eggs in pan until all is stirred. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Punch top full of holes with toothpick. Pour cream of coconut over cake. Let cool completely. Spread Cool Whip on top at serving time and sprinkle with coconut. Store in refrigerator.

title: light crepes
directions: Beat eggs; blend all other ingredients until batter is smooth and just thick enough to coat a spoon.
If batter is too thick, add a little more milk.
Cover and let stand 1/2 hour.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a 9 hole muffin pan.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: orange pie
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, flour, salt and grated rind.
Add juices. Cook in double boiler until thick.
Stir constantly.
Add butter and slightly beaten egg yolks.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Pour into baked shell.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add buttermilk, cornmeal, vinegar, vanilla and eggs. Mix and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 20 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all together and bake in a 375° oven until done, maybe 30 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour and sugar until well blended. Gradually stir in milk and cook until just hot.
Remove from heat. Beat in eggs and baking powder.
Stir in both cans of corn.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for about 1 hour, or until set in center.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Grease and bake potatoes
at 400° until done (1 1/2 to 2 hours). Cook until you can
handle
them.
Cut
in half;
scrape out into mixer bowl, saving shells.
Beat
centers
good.
Add sour cream, milk, etc. Beat until fluffy.
(You
may add more milk if desired.) Refill and put grated cheese and parsley
on top. You can freeze them and bake later. Hold in refrigerator
for overnight
or
bake
at 350° for 25 minutes. Serves 14.

title: kevin's cream tuna on toast(easy)
directions: Cook everything in a saucepan until heated.
Pour over toast.

title: gooney bird pie
directions: Mix flour, nuts and butter, lumpy.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° about 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix together sugar, cheese and Cool Whip.
Hard to spread on top of cake.
Beat slowly the pudding and milk.
Add to pie.
Cover top with Cool Whip.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together except crackers and pour into casserole dish with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.
Put crackers on top and return to oven and bake until bubbly hot.

title: orange crush pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream the margarine, Crisco and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each.
Alternate flour and Orange Crush; add flavorings.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Place all ingredients in blender in order listed:
milk, potatoes, salt, onion, bacon fat, bacon and celery.
Cover and run on low speed, until vegetables and bacon are chopped.
Pour into saucepan.
Simmer over low heat 30 minutes.

title: shrimp or crawfish fettucini
directions: Cook fettucini noodles; drain and set aside. Cook onions, peppers and celery in melted butter until limp. Add shrimp or crawfish, parsley and
flour.
Cook on medium-low for 15 minutes. Add Velveeta cheese, milk and jalapeno relish.
Cook until cheese has melted.
Remove from heat. Add fettucini.
Put in large Corning Ware. Top with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and cook in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Serve well with garlic bread.

title: one-rise cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix whipping cream and brown sugar in ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine 1 1/2 cups flour, yeast, 1/4 cup sugar, salt, warm water, 2 tablespoons butter and egg in mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Stir in remaining flour.
Knead for 1 minute.
Roll into 7 x 15-inch rectangle on floured surface. Mix 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and 1/4 cup butter in bowl.
Spread over dough.
Roll tightly; seal.
Cut into 20 pieces.
Place cut side down on brown sugar mixture in prepared pan.
Let rise, covered, for 45 to 60 minutes, or until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 400°
for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Invert onto serving tray.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: Combine the first seven ingredients in medium saucepan.
Bring to boil over high heat, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Gradually pour beaten egg into boiling soup, stirring constantly in one direction.
Remove from heat; stir in green onions.
Garnish with additional chopped green onions or cilantro, as desired.
Serve immediately.
Yields 5 cups.

title: "real" tacos
directions: Cook roast in a crock-pot; top with 2 teaspoons lemon juice and one can of stewed tomatoes while cooking.
When done, shred beef with fork.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add carrots, oil and eggs.
Mix together until moistened.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into pan and bake in a 325° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: stroganoff
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic, etc.
Add 2 cans of vegetable soup and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add 1 cup of sour cream, milk and heat. Top with biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: ruth kerr's party pie shell
directions: Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and 1/2 teaspoon of salt until very stiff.
Add vanilla and 1 cup of sugar slowly.
Bake at 275° in a greased 9-inch pie plate for 1 hour.
Mix egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar, 1/8 teaspoon salt, lemon rind, lemon juice and pineapple together.
Boil until thick.
Cool and pour in baked shell.

title: caramel cookies
directions: Melt butter and sugar over low heat.
Beat in egg.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in 9-inch square pan (greased) at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut in squares while still warm.
Leave in pan to cool.
Cookies will be soft to touch when ready to remove from oven.

title: confetti cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill until firm.
Shape into a ball and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
For best taste, prepare the day before and chill overnight.
Serve with party rye bread or crackers.

title: zwiebel kuchen(german onion pizza)
directions: Make dough from first four ingredients and 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 cup butter and 2 eggs.
Mix all ingredients together at one time.
Let set 30 minutes.
Cut bacon into small pieces and saute in 1/8 cup butter.
Cut onions into thin slices.
Add to bacon, simmering until golden.
Let cool.
Roll out crust (dough will be sticky, use flour as needed).
Place on a large greased cookie sheet.
Flute edges.
Spoon 1/2 cup sour cream over entire crust. Mix remaining sour cream, 1/2 teaspoon salt, caraway seed and 2 eggs.
Spoon onion mixture over the sour cream and top with the sour cream and egg mixture.
Bake in a preheated oven at 450° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut and serve warm.
Very traditional in our area in the Fall.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Brown half of ground beef; drain well.
To meat, add remaining ingredients and simmer, stirring occasionally.
To remaining beef, add 2 eggs, 1 teaspoon garlic powder and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese. If mixture is too dry, add an additional egg or if too wet, add more Parmesan cheese.
Roll mixture into balls and brown lightly in skillet on medium heat until browned.
Add meatballs to sauce. Cook sauce on low heat several hours, stirring frequently.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and
chop eggplant and cook in boiling water until tender.
Saute onion in 1/2 stick of oleo.
Combine all ingredients in
a
greased casserole.
Place cheese on top (optional).
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: morning rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a medium bowl.
Jam could be used in place of honey and any fruit you like.
Serves 2.

title: queen of puddings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Heat milk almost to boiling in a heavy saucepan. Stir in butter, sugar and vanilla.

Place crumbs in a large bowl and pour mixture over crumbs. Stir in yolks and turn into dish. Bake until set, approximately 40 to 45 minutes. Remove from oven and spread preserves or jam on top. Top with Meringue.

title: taco salad
directions: Add the taco seasoning mix and the water to the cooked beef and simmer 15 minutes until thickened.
Prepare ingredients but toss together just before serving.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together until light and fluffy. Add egg and beat well.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Stir into sugar mixture.
Add pineapple and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cover cookie sheet with aluminum foil. Beat egg whites and salt until very stiff.
Gradually add sugar, little by little.
Keep beating until very stiff.
Add vanilla and chocolate bits, folding it in.
Drop on foiled cookie sheets by teaspoons, 30 on two sheets, making 60 small cookies. Put both sheets in oven (one on middle rack and other above).
Immediately turn oven off.
Don't open door for 5 hours or overnight.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Drain sauerkraut and press out all liquid.
Saute onion in margarine until transparent.
Add sauerkraut and rest of ingredients to onion.
Simmer on low heat at least 30 minutes. Serve immediately or transfer to casserole and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, heat at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes or in microwave 6 to 7 minutes.

title: marge's caramels
directions: In
a
saucepan,
over	medium heat, melt oleo.
Mix in brown sugar.
Mix in slowly
the corn syrup and milk.
Cook to 240°, stirring
all the time.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.	Pour on buttered cookie sheet.
Cool and cut in logs and wrap in wax paper.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Slice eggplant into 1/2-inch pieces.
Place by layers in a casserole.
Season and add a little of the cheese.
Continue layering.
Sprinkle with oil and paprika.
Cover and bake 45 minutes in moderate oven.
Uncover and bake until cheese starts to brown.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts. Beat eggs slightly. add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until creamy. Add zucchini and pineapple. Stir in dry ingredients until all are moistened. Bake in two 9 x 5
x 3-inch loaf pans, greased and floured. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes before removing.
(You may add raisins, if you desire.)

title: ambrosia balls
directions: Mix with a fork.
Chill for 1hour.
Roll into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix lemon pudding and crushed pineapple with juice; drain other fruits and add Cool Whip last.

title: chocolate pie *
directions: Mix dry ingredients into milk.
Pour into uncooked pie shell. Cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients and beat until thick.
Add sour cream and Eagle Brand milk and beat.
Fold in 1/2 of Cool Whip.

title: mother-in-law's turkey stuffing
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Add liver, chopped beef, parsley and thyme.
Cook until done.
Remove crust from bread. Soak in water and squeeze out.
Add to meat mixture along with eggs and season with salt and pepper.
Add chestnuts and mix thoroughly.
Stuff your turkey.

title: low sugar strawberry pie
directions: Bring cornstarch, water, corn syrup and food coloring to a boil.
Stir in Jell-O.
Set aside to cool.
When cool, put in packages of sugar.
Place strawberries in a pie shell.
Pour in Jell-O mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: cheese broccoli
directions: Precook the broccoli.
Mix soup, milk and 1/2 of the onion rings.
Mix into broccoli. Spread grated cheese on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with the rest of the onion rings across the top and bake 10 minutes more.

title: krystle's famous pickles
directions: First, you get your pickles and cut them into about half-inch slices, then you dip some peanut butter out and put a little bit on each slice of pickle.
There!
You have it.
Pickles And Peanut Butter is very good, especially if you eat it at Papaws.

title: boil cookies
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients together for 1 minute and 30 seconds. Add marshmallows.
Let stand for several minutes.
Beat until marshmallows are melted.
Add crumbs.
Drop by tablespoon on wax paper. Shape into logs.
Servings:

title: shells and cheese with chicken
directions: Cut cream cheese into squares.
Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Set aside to cool.
Save broth.
Cut chicken into cubes. Cook shells in chicken broth (add water if needed to make 6 cups) for 10 to 12 minutes.
After 6 minutes, add onion and celery. Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir over low heat, just until all cheese melts, and all is blended.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Use greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat oven to 325°.
Mix egg, milk and soup in bowl.
Layer browned meat, bread (torn in pieces) and hash browns in pan.
Pour egg mixture over.
Top with cheese. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: Mix nuts and coconut and spread in bottom of pan.
Bake in greased sheet cake pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box and pour over nuts and coconut mixture.
Melt butter and cream cheese and stir in sugar then pour mixture over above mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked soy pork chops
directions: Brown the pork chops and minced garlic in the cooking oil. Place browned chops in a 13 x 2 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour soy sauce and wine over the chops.
Cover with sliced onion and mushrooms.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes.
Serve with rice, using the extra sauce.

title: borsch(meatless)
directions: Grate carrots and beets on medium size grater.
Add diced celery, one chopped onion, salt and cold water and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Fry chopped onion in oil until light in color.
Add cabbage and mushrooms.
Simmer until all vegetables are tender, but firm. Add tomato sauce, seasonings and lemon juice.

title: prize cookies
directions: In large bowl, cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar, blending well after each addition.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Crumble and stir in mincemeat.
Drop mixture by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet, about 2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: 7-minute strawberry 'n ice cream pie
directions: Combine strawberries, sugar and lemon juice in bowl.
Spoon in ice cream and blend.
Fold in Cool Whip, blending well.
Freeze if necessary until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust and freeze until firm at least 4 hours.
Garnish with additional strawberries if desired.
Store any leftover pie in freezer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tamale pie
directions: Saute meat; add salt and chili pepper.
Add corn and tomato juice; stir in corn meal.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour or until firm.
If desired, thicken more tomato juice and use as a sauce.

title: pecan sticks
directions: Spread very, very thin on greased cookie sheet and bake in a slow oven until light brown.
Cut immediately into 1 x 3-inch strips; remove while warm and roll in powdered sugar.
Very crisp and good.

title: star spangled crispies
directions: Place white chocolate chips and butter in a microwave bowl. Heat on medium power for about 1 min., check and stir every 20 seconds so that chocolate doesn't burn. Stir until mixture is smooth; combine with cereal and M&M's. Drop by tbsp onto wax paper lined sheet pan to set. Store in an airtight container.

title: key lime pie(original "conch" recipe)
directions: Beat egg yolks lightly.
Add condensed milk and beat until well blended.
Very slowly add lime juice, beating well all the time.
Pour into cooled shell.

title: lemon crinkles cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg thoroughly; blend in lemon rind.
Measure flour in separate bowl with all other dry ingredients; slowly stir into sugar mixture.
Roll into 1 inch balls.
Dip top of ball into granulated sugar.
Bake 350 degrees on a ungreased cookie sheet for 10 -14 minutes.
Remove from sheet to cool.
Good cookie to make ahead and freeze.

title: french onion soup
directions: In a covered 3-quart saucepan, cook sliced onions in butter or margarine about 20 minutes or until tender.
Add beef broth, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg, melted chocolate, vanilla and milk.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Add nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet or form dough into a roll, chill and slice.
Bake at 375° until brown or done to your liking.

title: easy roast beef
directions: Prepare roast by rinsing and seasoning to taste.
Place roast in crock-pot or roast pan.
Add soup and/or vegetables on top of roast.
If you plan to prepare roast in crock-pot, prepare in the morning and roast will be ready at meal time in the evening.
If the conventional method is used, bake in roast pan for 3 hours at 250°.
The longer the time, the lower the heat, the more tender the meat.
The same method may be used on pork roast and for chicken, minus the vegetables.

title: silly putty
directions: Mix together. If putty is too sticky, add more starch until the texture is workable.

title: sweet onion pockets
directions: Combine all ingredients, except rolls.
On a lightly floured board, separate each can of rolls into 4 rectangles each, making a total of 8.
Press perforated edges together.
Place approximately 2 to 3 tablespoons of onion mixture over half of each roll.
Fold edges together; press with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serves 8.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place crescent rolls on cookie sheet and press together. Bake as directed and cool. Mix remaining ingredients and spread mix on cooled crust. Add raw vegetables on top. Top with shredded cheese.

title: peggy's chops
directions: Brown
salted
and
peppered
chops
in
large	skillet (Teflon is	best);	remove	chops.	Stir
in cream of mushroom soup,
dissolving brown residue in pan.
Place chops back into pan with soup/gravy;
slice onions on top of chops.
Cover and simmer until
chops
are
done and tender (about 45 minutes). Serve over mashed potatoes or rice.
So good, easy and fills a hungry family. Use 2 cans of soup if more gravy is desired.

title: jubilee punch
directions: Mix orange and lemon juice with cherries.
To serve, place large block ice in punch bowl; add fruit mixture, then pour in grape juice.
Serves 12.

title: egg stuff
directions: Fry potatoes, onion and bacon/ham in oil until potatoes are tender.
Add egg and scramble until done.
Top with cheese if desired.

title: pecan pie(serves 6)
directions: Turn on oven and set at 375°.
Beat eggs slightly in a 2-quart bowl.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup and melted oleo.
Stir in pecans. Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake near center of oven 30 to 40 minutes or until filling is slightly firm.
Center of pie may look soft when pie is gently shaken, but will become firm when cool.

title: pasta casserole
directions: Mix all together in roaster.
Top with Mozzarella and Cheddar cheeses.
Bake for 15 minutes, covered, and 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: mini pizza bites
directions: Mix first eight ingredients together and cook for 15 minutes. Brush party rye with oil, cover with heated sauce, put Mozzarella cheese on top.
Then add 2 or 3 slices of pepperoni on top of Mozzarella.
Sprinkle with parsley and oregano.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: egg soup
directions: In a large saucepan, bring to a boil broth and water over medium heat.
Meanwhile, cut steak into thin strips.
Marinate about 10 minutes in water, cornstarch and soy sauce.
Drain.
Stir boiling broth to make it swirl; pour in beaten eggs.
Reduce heat. Cook 1 minute.
Spoon in beef strips.
Simmer about 3 minutes until meat is cooked.
Spoon hot soup in bowls.
Top with green onion or Chinese parsley.
Good with buttered bread or crackers.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Cook fresh mushrooms in broth.
Drain and measure broth.
Add water to make 1/2 cup.
Heat 1 1/2 cups skim milk and 1/2 cup broth in the top of a double boiler.
Blend flour and the remaining 1/2 cup skim milk until no lumps remain.
Add to heated milk and broth, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add chicken, mushrooms, pimento and seasoning.
Reheat.
Serve on toast.
Yield:
4 servings.
Carbohydrate 22 g, protein 28 g, fat 10 g, calories 290. One serving = 3 meat low-fat exchange, 1 bread starch exchange, 1 vegetable exchange.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Mix sugar and eggs in bowl.
Add butter, flour, baking powder, vanilla and nuts.
Pour in a greased cake pan, 10 x 12-inch, and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into 1-inch bars.

title: lime jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello and marshmallows in boiling water.
Beat in cream cheese, crushed pineapple, sugar, lemon juice and nuts.
Beat well; blend in heavy cream.
Pour in mold.
Put in refrigerator until formed.

title: lemon cake pudding
directions: Sift together into a bowl flour, sugar and salt.
Stir in grated lemon rind, lemon juice, egg and milk.
Fold in egg whites. Pour into 1 qt. casserole bowl and set it in a pan of water 1 inch deep.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 9-inch buttered pie plate for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry tarts
directions: Whip first four items until light and fluffy.
Put vanilla wafer in bottom of medium size cupcake liner.
Fill liner 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Add cherry pie filling on top.
Refrigerate for a day before serving.

title: pork chop dijon
directions: Combine mustard, Italian dressing and pepper; set aside.
Spray 10-inch skillet with nonstick spray.
Preheat to medium high heat. Add the pork chops and brown on both sides.
Remove chops from skillet and add onion.
Cook onion for 3 minutes.
Push onion aside and return chops to skillet.
Spread mustard mixture over chops. Cover and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.

title: mock eclairs
directions: Mix and bake cake mix according to directions on the box.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut cake into 16 pieces (4 1/2 x 1 1/2 inches).
Cut each piece in half lengthwise, then spread 1 tablespoon pudding between split cake pieces and top with chocolate fudge topping.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: little smokies
directions: Cut bacon into strips to wrap around sausages.
Hold with toothpicks.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, turning once in awhile.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage, onion and celery.
Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° in a covered container for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sloppy joe's from bear clan
directions: Brown
hamburger and onion.
Drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until flavors mix.
Adjust seasonings and serve on hamburger buns.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Quarter potatoes, boil in covered pot for 20 to 40 minutes. Drain, then add butter and beat well.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, milk and seasonings.
Beat until fluffy.
Pour into well-buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish and top with grated cheese. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal scotch cookies
