directions: Heat oven to 375°. Stir together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt in large bowl. Beat butter and sugars in another large bowl on medium-high speed 3 minutes, until smooth. Scrape down sides of bowl after 2 minutes. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Beat in vanilla until combined.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onion, raisins and bacon.
Pour dressing (recipe follows) over all and marinate 1 to 2 hours only.

title: aunt leona's apple butter
directions: Mix applesauce, sugar and cinnamon to taste.
Cook on low 20 minutes.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: pot-luck soup
directions: Pour all together and bring to a boil.
(For a fun pot-luck dinner, everyone signs up to bring a can of soup or ingredient to be made into the pot-luck soup.)

title: bread dressing
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; set aside. Saute onion
and
celery
in
margarine until tender.
Add to bread mixture, stirring well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 2 quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; add pecans last.
Press in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: soy chicken divan
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place dough in 2 long rectangles in Pam-sprayed 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press dough into pan and up sides 1/2-inch, forming crust.
Bake at 375° for approximately 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and place broccoli and soy chicken evenly on crust.
Combine mayonnaise, onion, soup and pimento. Spoon over chicken and broccoli; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand about 5 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Fry sausage until crumbled; drain off all fat.
Add all ingredients in the order given to sausage in a large skillet.
Mix thoroughly and pour into a large baking dish.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes or until brown.

title: shredded brussels sprouts in cream(this reheats beautifully if you slightly undercook the sprouts.)
directions: Coarsely shred Brussels sprouts in a food processor fitted with a 4mm slicing blade or slice about 1/8-inch thick with a sharp knife.
Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Add garlic and cook and stir for 30 seconds.
Add shredded Brussels sprouts; salt and toss well.
Cook, stirring frequently, until the Brussels sprouts are wilted and just tender, 3 to 5 minutes. Season with nutmeg and pepper to taste.
Add the cream; stir well and cook for 2 minutes.

title: whipped potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes as for whipped potatoes.
Drain and whip.
Mix together sour cream and cream cheese. Add to whipped potatoes. Add garlic salt and chives to taste.
Beat 2 eggs; add a little milk and mix into potato mixture.
Put into a greased casserole. Sprinkle with paprika and dot with butter.
Can now refrigerate covered or bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: gooey cake
directions: Mix dry cake mix with margarine and 1 egg.
Pat into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Boil hen, gizzards and livers until tender.
Bake a large, flat pan of Egg Bread.
Saute onion and celery in butter until tender. Cut up all meat, 3 or 4 slices of bread and 4 or 5 saltine crackers.
Mix all.
Take chicken off bone or leave it on.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Put a little bacon drippings on top.

title: broccoli rice
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Add rice, onion, celery, soups, water and Cheez Whiz.
Mix together.
Place frozen broccoli in center of pan.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir and bake for 30 more minutes or until celery is tender.

title: onion burger
directions: Slice onion in half, leaving on the shell.
Remove center of onion, leaving 2 to 3 layers, depending on thickness.
Pack center of onion with hamburger.
Place onion directly into coals until done.
Onion is not only part of meal but your cook pot.
Simple, easy and no clean-up!

title: sweet potato and pecan casserole
directions: Mix together sweet potatoes, half cup margarine, eggs, sugar and spice.
Spoon mixture into greased small casserole dish. Blend the flour, 1/3 cup margarine, and pecans with a fork until ingredients are crumbled together.
Sprinkle crumb topping on the potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: dang good pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar and butter; add flour, vanilla and 1 egg at a time.
Add pineapple and coconut; mix well. Put in unbaked pie shell and bake for 50 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese, blending in sugar with electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time and continue to blend. Add flavorings and flour and beat until smooth and light.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven 1 1/2 hours or until cake is golden and tests done.

title: fruity chicken salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons of juice.
Combine tidbits and next 6 ingredients.
Mix well. Combine 2 tablespoons pineapple juice, mayonnaise, soy sauce and curry powder.
Stir well and add to chicken mixture.
Chill.
Stir in noodles just before serving.

title: my best chicken
directions: Put chicken in a large plastic bag.
Pour on marinade and let stand at least 1 hour, turning frequently.

title: fat-free foam rubber birthday cake
directions: Cut out the piece of foam rubber from an old foam mattress or buy one from an upholstery store.
Cover all sides (including bottom) with a thick layer of frosting, with a 1/2-inch thick layer on top.
Refrigerate before inserting candles, so frosting stiffens up enough to support the candles.
Serve to birthday honoree at a party and insist the honoree cuts the cake.
Be sure to have camera ready to catch honoree's expression when the cake refuses to be cut.
If honoree is a friend or employer, be sure to have a real cake as a back-up!

title: all american meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Pour glaze over meat loaf.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes to heat glaze.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: sour cream-chili bake
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef; drain off fat.
Stir in drained beans, enchilada sauce, tomato sauce, shredded American cheese and the instant onion.
Set aside 1 cup of the crushed taco shells; stir remaining into the meat mixture.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: creamy chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine marshmallow cream, sugar, evaporated milk, butter and salt.
Bring to a full rolling boil over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add milk chocolate morsels and semi-sweet chocolate morsels; stir until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla extract.
Pour into foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm (about 2 hours).
Makes about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: plantation marble cake
directions: Sift
flour
once;
measure
and
add baking powder and salt. Sift
together
times.
Cream butter thoroughly; add sugar gradually
and
cream
together until light and fluffy. Add eggs, then flour alternately with milk a small amount at a time.	Beat after
each addition until smooth.	Divide batter into 2
parts. To	one
part add spices and molasses.
Put by tablespoon into greased loaf pan, 8 x 4 x 3-inches, alternating light
and	dark molasses.
Bake in moderate oven at 325° for 1
hour and 15 minutes. Spread butter frostings on top and sides of cake.

title: gramma's noodle bake
directions: Fry hamburger with onion and peppers.
Drain.
Mix tomatoes and tomato juice.
Set aside.
Cook noodles for 5 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer sauce, then noodles, then top with olives, cheese and sauce.
Repeat layering, ending with cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crock-pot barbecue
directions: Before bedtime, place roast in crock-pot.
Baste with 1/4 cup barbecue sauce.
Cook on low overnight.
Next morning, shred pork with fork, add remaining ingredients.
Continue cooking on low at least 4 more hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: never fail brownies
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl at one time and mix.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Allow to cool and cut.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Grease casserole. Make potatoes. Add sour cream, cream cheese, butter, milk and eggs (eggs should be added last).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until well heated through.
Do not cover. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: beef macaroni
directions: Place all items in a 2-quart casserole; stir well.
Be sure ground beef is broken up.
Cover; microwave for 15 minutes at High.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Let stand 5 minutes, covered.
Serves 4.

title: green beans with stewed tomatoes
directions: Saute onion with garlic and basil, in the oil.
Add stewed tomatoes, with juice, green beans and pepper.
Cook on medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: martha's easy strawberry dessert
directions: Mix berries, lemon juice and milk.
Whip the cream.
Fold in berry mixture.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Break angel food cake into bite-size pieces into buttered dish.
Pour mixture over cake pieces.
Cover with chopped pecans, if desired.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix everything but butter and a few crumbs.
Pour into greased casserole and top with remaining crumbs and pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: feathery fudge cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla five minutes at high speed.
Blend in cooled, melted chocolate.
Add dry ingredients sifted together and water alternately.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in 2 (9-inch) layer pans, greased and floured.
Cake is done when tester comes out clean.

title: hello dollies
directions: Select a 7 x 7-inch square pan.
Melt the butter in the pan. Do not stir at any time.
The ingredients are to be applied in layers.
Cover the entire butter surface with graham cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle the coconut over the crumbs.
Drop the chocolate chips over the coconut layer.
Sprinkle the pecans over the chips. Cover with the condensed milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven.
Cool completely in pan before cutting.

title: farmer's delight
directions: Cook meat, bell pepper and onion.
Meanwhile, cook egg noodles and then mix with meat mixture.
Blend other ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
This makes a large dish.

title: bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in a little water.
Add rest of ingredients. Let rise.
Knead and put in a pan.
Let rise and cook until done and brown.

title: power balls
directions: Mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls and let the kids at 'em. Full of good things and will really make "powerful" kids.
Makes 36 balls.

title: chicken alfredo "lite"
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, blend flour, liquid Butter Buds, skim milk and chicken broth.
Add minced garlic, salt and pepper. Continue to cook over low heat, stirring constantly until the sauce thickens.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Combine sauce with chicken and mushrooms.
Fold into cooked pasta.
Serve immediately.
If sauce is too thick, add a little more evaporated skim milk and chicken broth.
Makes 6 servings, 279 calories per serving, 3.83 g fat per serving.

title: kentucky sauce for roast pig
directions: Blend all ingredients over low heat.
Do not boil.

title: frito chili pie
directions: Layer 2 1/2 cups of corn chips, onion, 1/2 cup of cheese and chili in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining corn chips. Bake in preheated oven at 375° for about 25 minutes.
Top with remaining corn chips.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for about 25 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and continue baking 5 minutes. Garnish with sour cream and ripe olives (optional).
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter in skillet.
Add onions and bell pepper. Cook until onions are clear; add ground beef and cook.
Drain excess grease.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour into baking dish. Bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: apple strudel
directions: Whisk cheese with water until smooth; set aside.
On a nonstick cookie sheet, place 2 sheets of phyllo.
Brush top sheet lightly with melted butter.
Place 2 more sheets over first two; butter top sheet.
Repeat with last 2 sheets; then sprinkle buttered top sheet with cornflake crumbs.
With a spatula, spread 3-inch wide band of cheese along one long side of phyllo, leaving 1/2 to 3/4 inch margin around edges.
Spread jam over cheese mixture.

title: ugly annie's lobster stew
directions: Scald all milks together.
Do not boil.
Pour this mixture into Lobster Mixture and heat thoroughly.
Do not boil or cover!

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hot instant tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 2 or 3 tablespoons in cup of hot water.

title: pink lady
directions: Chill all liquids.
Place sugar in pitcher.
Slowly add cranberry juice until sugar dissolves, then add pineapple juice and chill thoroughly.
Add ginger ale.
Pour into glasses and add 1 spoon of ice milk to each drink.
Stir until foamy.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 glasses.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream Crisco, sugar, milk, vanilla.
Add egg.
Combine flour, salt, and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts and chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoon, 3 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes for chewey or 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: blueberry or peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour over margarine.
Pour fruit over top. Sprinkle mace over this and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lep kuchen(dorlea's german christmas cookies)
directions: Mix all together until moistened and stiff.
Let stand overnight in the refrigerator.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Glaze while still warm with powdered sugar glaze.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Mix dressing ingredients.
Spoon over salad.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Will keep about 1 week refrigerated.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
No flour needed for this!!

title: maxey's pralines
directions: Place the above in medium saucepan, stirring often and heat to soft ball stage, 234 to 240° on candy thermometer.
Add 4 large marshmallows, cut in small pieces or 40 small marshmallows, 3 Tbsp. butter (not margarine), 1/2 tsp. vanilla, 2 cups pecans and stir until marshmallows are melted.
Drop on buttered wax paper. Leave until set and very cool.
Place in covered tin with wax paper between layers. Enjoy!
You must have a candy thermometer.

title: creamy potato soup(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Saute onion in butter or oleo until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook vegetables until tender and then add White Sauce.
Blend.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add salt, oil, and rice.
Turn heat to low.
Cover pan and cook gently until rice is tender, 25 to 30 minutes.
In another pan, cook onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Add beans and salt and pepper and cook until hot.
Stir beans and rice together.
Heat together over low heat 5 minutes to blend flavors.

title: orange crisps
directions: Cream shortening, gradually add sugar and orange juice.
Cream well.
Add egg and orange rind. Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture a little at a time.
Fill cookie press.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet, 10 to 12 minutes, at 400°.
Yields 7 dozen.

title: ranch potatoes
directions: Use enough potatoes to make 1 layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pasta salad delight
directions: Cook macaroni and drain well.
Allow to cool.
Add cauliflower and broccoli to macaroni.
Arrange in flat container.
Pour enough dressing over mixture to cover it.
Top with pepperoni (sliced). Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight or two hours before serving.
Add tomatoes and
mushrooms.
Stir well and refrigerate.
Will last 2 to 3 days if kept in airtight container.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 13-inch baking pan melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: lemon pudding dessert
directions: Mix ingredients; pat
in
a
9	x 13-inch pan.	Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until brown.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise into 4 wedges.
Place skin side down in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
Combine remaining ingredients. Brush over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Brush with oil-cheese mixture at 15-minute intervals.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pitzels (italian cookies)
directions: Mix together and bake 10 seconds in a pitzel iron.
Grease the iron with Crisco.

title: tomato dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a storage container and let the mixture stand overnight to fully develop the flavor. This has just a few calories in the whole batch.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix jello with 2 boiling cups water, then add 1 cup cold water and put in refrigerator to set.
(Not too hard, takes about 1 hour.)
Line bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan with whole graham crackers. Beat well the sugar, oleo, eggs and vanilla about 10 minutes. Add nuts and well drained pineapple.
Put creamed mixture on graham crackers.
Cover with another layer of graham crackers. Put set jello on top and cover with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Generously grease bottom only of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Sprinkle marshmallows evenly over bottom of pan.
Combine thawed strawberries, syrup and dry gelatin.
Set aside.
Measure flour in large mixing bowl.	Combine remaining ingredients.	Blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed, scraping sides of bowl.
Pour into baking pan.
Spoon strawberry mixture evenly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.

title: sure shoot rolls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, stir until Crisco melts.
Add one beaten egg and 1 package quick rise yeast dissolved in 2 tablespoons warm water.
Add 3 cups flour.
Beat until dough is smooth.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours.
Turn out on floured surface and knead until smooth and no longer sticky.
Roll out to about 3/8-inches thick.
Cut with large cutter.
Brush with melted oleo and fold over.
Place in greased pan.
Let rise until doubled again.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 18 large rolls.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, add enchilada sauce.
Simmer. Mix soup and chilies and bring to a boil.
Layer in dish as follows:
chips, meat, cheese, soup mixture.
Repeat layers. Store in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Work butter or margarine into dry ingredients.
Beat in eggs and milk.
Add caraway seed and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. (Grease 10-inch iron frypan to bake.)
This is a large recipe.

title: noodles
directions: Stir in all the flour it will take.
Roll as thin as you can. Hang over napkin on back of chair to dry.
Then, roll up like a jelly roll and slice off in thin (wafer type) slices.
Cook in your broth or soup 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook bell pepper, onion, garlic, basil and rosemary in vegetable oil until tender.
Stir in rice, tomato, salt, pepper and water.
Cook, covered, on low heat for 20 minutes.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
In a large bowl, cream shortening until light and fluffy.
Add milk; gradually stir in flour mixture. Stir in nuts.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until top springs back.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: shrimp and marinated vegetable salad(scampi crudi e legume insalata)
directions: Bring 1 quart salted
water
to
boil.
Add carrots and broccoli; boil for 2 to
3 minutes.
Remove and cool completely. In large bowl,
combine
broccoli, olives, carrots, mushrooms, tomatoes
and artichoke
hearts.
In
mixing
jar
add vinegar, Parmesan cheese,
salt, lemon juice, mustard, pepper, oil and oregano.
Shake
well
and
pour over vegetables; toss gently. Cover and refrigerate overnight, stirring occasionally.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar until light.
Add flour and chopped nuts.
Cream until mixture crumbles.
Set aside 1 cup of mixture for topping.
Press remaining mixture into ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: ice cream cocktail
directions: Soften coffee ice cream and add white creme de cacao.
Place in a blender.
Pour into champagne glasses.
May be frozen.
Thaw 20 minutes before serving.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix well and make into sandwiches, or serve with crackers.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Drain 3/4 cup syrup from pineapple.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and mayonnaise.
Beat in cranberry sauce. Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream and add food coloring.
Pour into mold and freeze.
Take out of freezer 2 hours before serving. Place in refrigerator. Unmold.

title: sunday morning mimosas
directions: Pour 1/2 of the champagne and 1/2 of the orange juice into a chilled 8 ounce wine glass.
Serves 2.

title: sweet potato casserole(dessert)
directions: Combine and cover with topping.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix crumbs and margarine and sprinkle in bottom of pan.
Save some for top of cheese cake.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine flour, sugar, milk and eggs.
Mix until smooth. Heat oil
until	it
gets
to
Pour
mix into saucepan through a funnel.
Put powdered sugar and cinnamon on finished cakes.

title: easy garlic bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and spread on sliced French bread. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, then place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until slightly brown.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together being careful not to stir too briskly as powder rises and will stain clothing.
Makes 4 cups of tea mixture.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup of boiling water.

title: custard pie
directions: For a richly flavorful pie, choose pears at the peak of ripeness and spice them with freshly grated nutmeg.
Serve with unsweetened, lightly whipped cream.

title: 24 hour dessert
directions: Freeze evaporated milk overnight.
Beat frozen milk until fluffy.
Add cream cheese.
Bring crushed pineapple (including juice), sugar and Jell-O to boil.
Place milk and cream cheese mixture in a glass dish or salad bowl.
Fold in pineapple-Jello-O mixture; mix well until mixture becomes pink.
Place in refrigerator until set, like Jell-O would be.

title: slow cooker chili casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage until no longer pink; drain. Transfer to slow cooker.
Add the next 9 ingredients; stir well. Cover and cook on low for 7 hours or until rice is tender.
Stir in cheese during the last 10 minutes of cooking time.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: easy scandinavian supper
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a large bowl, break up potatoes with a fork.
Add carrot, green onion, dill, seasoned salt and pepper; toss until combined.
Spread half of the vegetable mixture in baking dish.
Top with half of the cheese.
Repeat.

title: saladmaster greaseless pancakes
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until thick and add melted butter and milk.
Add flour to egg mixture.
Preheat skillet.
Do not baste skillet with oil for the first pancake made.
Turn pancakes when bubbles appear.
This recipe makes thin pancakes, much like Swedish pancakes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix and pour into pie crusts.
Freeze and serve.

title: mandarin orange and curried chicken pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta al dente; rinse with cold water until cool and place in bowl.
Add chopped chicken breast, mandarin oranges with half of the juice they are packed in, yogurt and mayonnaise.
Mix together.
Then add curry powder, sugar, toasted almonds, raisins and salt and pepper to taste.
Combine all ingredients well.

title: heavenly dirt(flowerpot pudding)
directions: Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar until creamy and set aside.
Mix pudding and milk until thick.
Combine with cheese mixture.
Add Cool Whip topping and vanilla to pudding/cheese mixture.
Crush cookies, including filling.
Using a glass bowl, put a layer of cookie crumbs, then a layer of cream mixture. Continue layering, ending with a layer of crumbs (to look like dirt).
Decorate with silk flowers and gummy worms.

title: best dressing for hot lettuce salad
directions: Beat all and cook over low heat until thickened.
Be careful not to overcook.
Pour over lettuce with bacon and onion.
Also can combine part of this recipe with 1 part mayonnaise for macaroni salad.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: cinnamon popcorn
directions: Combine ingredients in pan.
Heat until butter is melted. Pour over 3 batches popped popcorn.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: double taffee delight
directions: Set first 3 ingredients aside.
Put remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat all of this for 2 minutes; pour 1/2 of batter in pan and then 1/2 of brown sugar mixture on top, then rest of batter mixture on top of this.
Top with the rest of the brown sugar mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan and cook 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin chip cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well, stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 - 12 minutes.

title: gooey cake
directions: Mix cake mix, melted butter and 1 egg together.
Place in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together powdered sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Add chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hot cheesy potato salad
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Saute onion, pepper and frankfurters about 5 minutes.
Add potatoes.
Cover and heat over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° in iron skillet.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Put in double boiler and cook.
Serve hot sprinkled with red crushed pepper.
Keep warm in fondue pot.

title: "lite" strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry jello in water.
Add frozen strawberries and stir until firm. Pour half of mixture into clear container. Chill until firm.
Spread with sour cream.
Pour in rest of jello mixture and chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: shake and bake mixture
directions: Blend together.
Good for chicken, pork chops, etc.

title: pumpkin spice drops
directions: Mix flour, spices and soda.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Stir in brown sugar, molasses and pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Add melted butter.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Cover bowl and chill 4 hours or overnight.
Set oven at 375°.
Use level tablespoon from measuring set to shape cookies.
Put on greased cookie sheet 1-inch apart.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Place potatoes and sea salt in chicken broth and cook under medium heat until tender.
After the potatoes are cooked, hand mash half the amount of potatoes to produce a creamy consistency.
Add the carrots and simmer until tender.
Lightly saute onions with a little unrefined olive oil and dry mustard.
Add the sauteed onions and celery and simmer for another 5 minutes.

title: old smoothies
directions: Combine brown sugar, granulated sugar and milk.
Stirring constantly, cook over medium heat to 228° (soft ball stage). Remove from heat and add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until mixture begins to thicken and turn opaque, about 2 minutes.
Drop quickly in patty shape from tablespoon onto buttered cookie sheet.
Makes about 30.

title: nacho potato slices
directions: Scrub potaotes
and
trim
ends.
Cut the potatoes into 3/8-inch thick slices.
In
an
x 8 x 2-inch microwave safe baking dish
arrange the potato slices, putting smaller slices in the
center.
Sprinkle
with
green onion and green pepper. Cover with vented clear plastic wrap.
Microcook on 100% power (High) 7 to 10 minutes or until tender, giving the dish a half turn once. Drizzle
with
taco
sauce,
barbecue or spaghetti sauce; sprinkle
with
cheese.
Cook,
uncovered,
to
60 seconds more or until cheese is melted.

title: kidney bean dip
directions: Drain kidney beans; rinse.
Mix all ingredients together.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: caldo de queso(mexican cheese-chile soup)
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Saute potato or zucchini and add tomato mixture.
Simmer for about 30 minutes, then add cheeses and cook until melted.
Add water or broth to thin soup if necessary.
Serves 4.

title: cheese stuffed beef rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°, spread 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce in bottom of a 12x8-inch baking dish.
In a large bowl thoroughly combine egg, seasonings, ricotta, parmesan, and 1/2 cup of the mozzarella cheese.
Spoon equal amounts of cheese mixture on 1 end of each beef slice.
Roll up beef slices jelly-roll style and arrange seam-side down in baking dish.
Place zucchini along both sides of dish.
Pour remaining spaghetti sauce over beef rolls and zucchini. Bake covered at 375° for 40 minutes or until heated through.
Top beef rolls with remaining mozzarella cheese.
Bake uncovered 3 minutes or until cheese is golden brown.

title: chilies rellenos squares
directions: Grease an 8-inch square baking dish and sprinkle with the peppers and cheese; pour the beaten eggs over the cheese and peppers.

title: layered peach dessert
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add butter and mix well.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: praline pecan crunch
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Combine cereal and pecans in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Set aside.
Combine syrup, brown sugar and oleo in 2-cup microwavable bowl.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir 1/2 to 1 1/2 minutes more until it's boiling well.

title: banana blueberry bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside. Cream butter and gradually beat in sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour mixture and banana alternately in 3 parts.
Gently stir in blueberries.
Turn into oiled 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Turn out of pan to cool. Makes 1 loaf.

title: coffee orange fudge cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Beat on low until blended.
Beat on medium for 4 minutes.
Stir in chips.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: yellow frosted punch
directions: Add water to orange juice and lemonade as directed on can. Stir in pineapple juice and refrigerate overnight so the juices will blend.
Put juice mixture into a large punch bowl.
Spoon pineapple sherbet over juices.
Pour ginger ale over sherbet. Stir well.
Serves 40 to 48 punch cup servings.

title: pecan chews
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 325° for 45 minutes in greased oblong pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: spinach dip in bread
directions: Mix all well. Place in round pumpernickel bread that has been cut into a well.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Beat with a mixer until well blended on medium speed.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust. Sprinkle with nuts.

title: peppered pecans
directions: Position rack in upper third of oven and preheat to 375°. Brush heavy large baking pan with oil.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Crumble large candy bar; melt in microwave.
Mix in Cool Whip; pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate 6 hours.
Grate small bar to cover pie.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add milk and stir until mixture forms a ball.

Roll out into a lightly floured surface to 1/2 inch thickness; cut out into rectangles 1 inch wide and 3 inches long. Gently place dough rectangles in 1/2 inch of hot oil a few at a time; lightly pressing down with the back of a fork until dough becomes firm.
Turn and cook on the other side until golden in color.
Drain and serve immediately with honey.
Yields about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: almond joy candy
directions: Heat butter and condensed milk until butter is melted.
Add the coconut and sliced almonds; cool completely.
Roll the mixture into balls and freeze.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Combine soups with 2 cups chicken broth.
Combine dressing and margarine.
Layer in dish 1/2 dressing, 1/2 of chicken, 1/2 of broth, other 1/2 of chicken, then broth and top with dressing.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon lush dessert
directions: Mix together butter, flour and nuts.
Press into bottom of a 9 x	13-inch
pan and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: western casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, taco sauce mix (dry), salt and pepper.
Simmer 2 minutes.

title: crunchy baked potatoes
directions: Whip the milk and water until thick and smooth.
Mix in the potatoes, onions, egg, salt and cayenne pepper; beat until light and fluffy.
Place in a 2-quart baking dish (well buttered).
Mix the cornflakes, Parmesan cheese and butter.
Sprinkle over the potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until potatoes are hot through and through.
This recipe can be put in 5 baked potato shells.

title: turkey and rice casserole
directions: Stir soup, milk and sour cream until well blended.
Stir in turkey and rice.
Bake in casserole at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli quiche
directions: Lightly spray a 9-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray. Combine half of chicken and half of broccoli in pie plate.
Puree Ricotta, yogurt, egg, egg white, flour, baking powder, salt, Parmesan and margarine in blender.
Pour over chicken in pie plate. Scatter remaining chicken and broccoli over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until wooden pick tests clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger and add taco seasoning.
Set aside.
In casserole dish, mix sour cream, cream cheese and bean dip.
Spread evenly in dish.
Sprinkle seasoned hamburger meat on top.
Add tomato and onion.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cook at 350° in oven until cheese melts (about 15 minutes).
Serve warm with chips.

title: elaine's peach cake
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
Add next 5 ingredients, mix and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix next 4 ingredients and put on top of first layer.
Beat last 3 ingredients together and pour over the fruit.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Grate sweet potatoes into milk to prevent darkening.
Mix all ingredients and place in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb sauce
directions: Cook on low heat, then cover and simmer for 25 minutes.
Serve over buttered biscuits hot, if you want, or eat plain.

title: hot water corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal and salt thoroughly.
Then add 2 cups boiling water into which 1 tablespoon shortening has been added.
"Scald" is the key word.
The boiling water into the meal is a cooking process which produces a firm mound of dough.
Cool about 20 minutes.
Work into dough 1/2 teaspoon baking powder dissolved in 2 tablespoons cold water.
Pat dough into patties about 3/4-inch thick.
Fry in deep fat until brown.
Serve hot.
This recipe has been in "The Shaw" family for over 75 years.

title: pumpkin raisin bread(makes 3 loaves)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 loaf pans.
Combine oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, softened oleo and sugar and press into bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar with beater.
Fold in whipped cream.
Put on top of graham cracker crust.
Spread cherry pie filling on top.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Use cool broth from chicken.
Make a stiff dough and roll very thin.
Cut and drop into boiling broth.

title: lye soap
directions: Make soap outside using an iron pot or enamel kettle.
Put water in kettle and carefully add the lye.
Avoid breathing the fumes.
Pour grease slowly into the lye water, stirring all the time with a wooden paddle or a wooden spoon.
Stir until the mixture thickens.
Let cool overnight and cut into bars.
Store in a dry place.

title: hardwicke's cheesecake
directions: Cream the cream cheese, eggs (one at a time) and sugar.
Add sour cream and then vanilla.
Mix well. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cocktail meatballs(appetizer)
directions: Thoroughly mix ground beef, onion, garlic, corn flakes and eggs.
Season to taste.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Combine chili sauce, grape jelly and lemon juice in a heavy skillet. Simmer 5 minutes.
Place meatballs in sauce.
Cook slowly for 1 hour.
Cool.
Refrigerate until fat hardens and skim off.
Can be frozen; reheat to serve.

title: chocolate oatmeal candy
directions: In saucepan combine milk, salt, sugar and butter; bring to a boil.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter, vanilla and cocoa; blend well. Spread out on platter to firm up.
Simple enough for kids to make.

title: luscious lemon pie
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cups sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt in double boiler; gradually stir in water.
Cook until thick.
Beat egg yolks; add rind, juice and butter.
Add cooked mixture slowly and return to double boiler.
Cook 5 more minutes.
Cool slightly and pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff; gradually add 6 tablespoons sugar.
Continue to beat until glossy.
Pile on top of cooled filling.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes until lightly brown.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend in blender.
Chill and serve with cut up veggies.

title: country-style smothered chicken
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp. Transfer to paper towels, reserving drippings in pan.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: cherry pie
directions: In a small mixing bowl, mix drained cherries, sugar, tapioca and almond extract. Let this mixture set for 15 minutes or so. Pour this filling into 1 unbaked pie crust; dot with butter. Cover with second pie crust, sealing edges and making a few slits in top for venting. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 375° and bake for 25 minutes longer. You may need to cover edges of crust to prevent overbrowning; use aluminum foil strips.

title: lo-cal cocoa
directions: Combine the dry milk and cocoa.
Store at room temperature. Makes enough for 4 cups of cocoa.
Fill mug with 3/4 cup water. Microwave on High for 1 minute or until hot.
Stir in 1/4 cup cocoa mix and 1/2 to 1 packet of Equal.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and a little bread together.
Mix in sage, celery, onion, oysters, water chestnuts and giblets (add a few giblets, no liquid, and save rest and liquid for use in gravy). Pour chicken broth over and mix.
Pour 1 stick melted margarine over mixture and mix.
Can add more butter if needed (more butter, fluffier and more moist).
Bake at 350° in a large shallow pan until brown on top.
This is Gary's Mom's Thanksgiving dressing!

title: orange french toast
directions: Mix together 1 cup orange juice, eggs, cinnamon and salt.
Dip raisin bread in the mixture and fry in vegetable oil.
Stir together frozen orange juice, margarine and sugar in heavy saucepan over low heat; melt, but do not boil.
Serve hot over French toast, waffles or pancakes.
Makes 2 cups.

title: pie crust (foolproof)
directions: In bowl, mix the flour, Crisco, sugar and salt together.
In separate bowl, beat egg with vinegar and water.
Then mix this into first mixture.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: sauerkraut, potatoes and frankfurters
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients together in a large pot for about 30 minutes.
Add potatoes.
Cook for about 15 minutes.
Add franks and cook another 15 minutes.

title: german pizza
directions: Heat oil or Crisco in frypan; add 1/2 these ingredients: potatoes, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper, 1/2 Spam strips. Repeat process with layers of remaining potatoes, green pepper, onion, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook on medium-low heat 20 minutes.
Add Spam strips, break 3 eggs over top (pierce yolks). Cook covered 10 minutes, then add cheese.
Cook covered for 2 minutes.
Serve in skillet.

title: fried venison
directions: Slice meat thin.
Beat well on both sides.
Marinate with soy sauce for 20 minutes.
Salt, pepper, and garlic salt to taste. Flour well.
Fry in lard or bacon grease until golden brown.

title: apple walnut tea bread *
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices into bowl. Stir in cereal flakes, wheat germ, walnuts and apples.
Combine egg, brown sugar, buttermilk and oil.
Mix into dry ingredients just enough to moisten.
Do not beat.
Turn into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: earthquake cake
directions: You will need a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: ruby's peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Roll mix by hand into small balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet. (I use Pam.)
Mash out into round cookie shape and size with fork. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 31 cookies.
Enjoy.

title: hobo casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, salt and pepper; drain.
Add tomato soup and Veg-All; simmer.
Put in casserole dish; top with canned biscuits.
Put in 250° oven until biscuits are done.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and break into bite size pieces.
Place chicken pieces in greased casserole dish.
Mix soups and sour cream together and pour on top of chicken.
Crush crackers and sprinkle on top of soup mixture.
Drizzle melted margarine on crackers. Sprinkle poppy seed on top and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Bring to boil the sugar, pepper, salt, oil and vinegar.
Mix all vegetables together.
Pour liquid mixture over vegetables. Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: festive onions
directions: Saute onions in butter until transparent.
Put into a baking dish.
Beat eggs until they are light.
Mix in cream and a dash of salt and pepper.
Pour this mixture over onions.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes in a 425° oven.

title: corny potato corned beef
directions: In a large skillet, fry potatoes with salt and pepper until brown. Stir in corn and corned beef until hot.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling water until tender, about 5 minutes; drain.
Combine sour cream and chicken soup; fold in squash and onion.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Put in a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup or more bacon bits and sliced olives. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: fruit party pizza
directions: Roll cookie dough thin.
Put on large cookie sheet and bake. Combine powdered sugar, cream cheese, Cool Whip and mandarin oranges.
Spread on baked cookie dough.
Add 1 layer sliced bananas, can of crushed pineapple, pie filling, chopped pecans and kiwi fruit.
Chill.

title: elderberry wine
directions: Boil sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Pour over elderberries. When lukewarm, add yeast.
Pour into plastic or glass container and let stand 7 days, stirring 3 times a day.

title: judy baker's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat one minute between each egg.
Add flour and milk alternately, beginning and ending with milk.
Add flavoring.
Bake in a well greased (and floured) Bundt pan at 325° for approximately 1 hour.

title: cajon oyster stew
directions: Pour evaporated and whole milk into pan.
Drain fluid from the oysters into the pan.
(Cover and place oysters into refrigerator.)
Simmer for 4 hours, stirring occasionally.
After 2 hours, add butter, hot sauce (to taste), salt and pepper (to taste).
Five minutes before serving, add oysters to milk.
Serve hot.

title: potato salad slaw
directions: Combine potatoes from package with boiling water in saucepan. Cover; simmer for 15 minutes, until tender.
Drain and chill potatoes.
Stir together the Miracle Whip, vinegar and seasoning packet from potatoes.
Combine potatoes, cabbage and celery.
Add Miracle Whip mixture; toss lightly.
Keep cold until serving. Garnish with cherry tomatoes and green pepper.
I add chopped pimento and, if not sweet enough, add sugar to taste.

title: zucchini sticks
directions: Cut zucchini into 1/4 inch to 1/2 inch strips.
Dip into beaten eggs and then into the cornmeal.
Place battered strips into a pot of hot oil.
Cook until brown.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serve with Ranch dressing.

title: fruit dip
directions: Recipe Tripled.
Whip cream cheese, sour cream and almond extract.
Slowly add powdered sugar.
Serve immediately or chill and serve with fresh fruit slices (apples, pears, strawberries, etc.).

title: pecan pie
directions: Chill pie shell.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup, vanilla and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Place a ring of foil around edge of pie to prevent crust from burning.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken in salted water approximately 30 to 40 minutes until cooked through.
After allowing chicken to cool, dice or shred.
On griddle or frying pan, heat oil and fry tortillas until warm and soft (not too much oil or they become greasy).
Don't overcook the tortillas or they will become hard and crispy.

title: calico bean casserole
directions: Cook the bacon; drain and cut into small pieces.
Brown the hamburger; drain the grease off.
Mix the remaining ingredients. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
I bake this in a large roasting pan (large recipe).

title: spiced tea
directions: Bring to a boil and keep in refrigerator.
Warm and serve when needed.

title: quick and easy deer steak
directions: Cut deer steak or tenderloin into 1-inch strips.
Saute in cooking oil or bacon fat until done.
Prepare rice dish (such as Rice-A-Roni or any type prepared rice dish).
Add deer meat strips.
May be served warm or cold.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put into a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until well done.
Let stand a few minutes before cutting.

title: german salted pretzel(salzbrezeln)
directions: Grease a baking sheet; set aside.
In a large bowl, dissolve yeast and sugar in water.
Let stand until foamy, 5 to 10 minutes. Beat in milk, 1 teaspoon salt and oil.
Beat in 2 cups flour. Let stand 10 minutes.
Add enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out dough onto a lightly floured surface.
Clean and grease bowl.
Knead dough 8 to 10 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Place dough in greased bowl, turning to coat all sides. Cover and let rise in a warm place, free from drafts, until doubled in bulk, about 30 minutes.
Punch down dough.
Divide dough in half.
Roll each half into a long roll; cut each into 12 pieces.
Roll each piece into a 14-inch rope.
Twist and loop into pretzel shape.
Cover and let rise 10 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O with cottage cheese.
Add Cool Whip. Drain oranges and cut into small pieces. Add oranges to mixture.
Do not use juice.
Refrigerate.
You can use sugar-free Jell-O, low-fat cottage cheese and lite Cool Whip for a low calorie, low-fat dessert.

title: 1-2-3 fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Mix
sugar,
flour and milk.
Pour into pan with melted butter. Do
not stir.
Spoon fruit over batter.
Do not stir. Bake until golden brown.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook the sugar and milk until it forms soft ball stage.
Take pan off stove and place in sink of cold water. Beat in peanut butter and vanilla until mixture becomes creamy.
Spread into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan. Cut when cool.

title: cuban salad
directions: Crush one clove of garlic and rub in bottom and sides of large salad bowl.
Add next 8 ingredients to the bowl.
Salt and squeeze the juice of one lemon over the mixture.
Toss well.
Top with cottage cheese.
Pepper liberally with cracked pepper. Refrigerate until time to serve.
At serving time, add extra virgin olive oil and red wine vinegar to taste.
Toss well.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
Add	all dry ingredients.
Stir in apples and nuts. Mix well.
Pour
into
a
greased
10 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips over batter and pat down.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: humdinger candy
directions: Cook dates, oleo and sugar 6 to 8 minutes; take off heat.
Add the rest of the ingredients; stir.
Pour on foil and let cool. Roll in balls in confectioners sugar, then serve.

title: groundhog smothered in onions
directions: Cut into chunks about 2 to 3 inches long. Cook in pressure cooker until tender, 10 to 12 minutes.
Fillet by removing the meat from the ribs using a paring knife to push the meat from the bones.
Dredge in seasoned flour to which has been added salt, pepper and a pinch of each of the following herbs:
marjoram, rosemary and savory.
Brown in hot fat.
Serve with turnips, mustard or wild greens, dry beans (navy, pinto or red kidney) and corn bread.

title: potato strudel
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the potatoes with enough cold water to cover them by 2-inches; add the salt and simmer the potatoes for 20 to 25 minutes or until they are just tender. Drain the potatoes and let them cool.
In a heavy skillet, cook the bacon over moderate heat, stirring, until it is crisp; add the onions and marjoram and cook the mixture until the onions are softened.
Remove the skillet from the heat and add the parsley, the chervil, the chives and the habanero chili.
Chop the potatoes coarse and force half of them through the medium disk of a food mill or ricer (or pulse in food processor).
Transfer to large bowl.
Add the remaining chopped potatoes, the bacon mixture and salt and pepper to taste and stir the mixture until it is just combined.

Roll out the dough on a floured surface into a 12 x 17-inch rectangle; brush the dough border with some of the egg yolk and with a short side facing you, spread the potato mixture over the bottom half of the rectangle.

Beginning with the short side, roll the pastry up carefully jelly roll fashion and put it seam side down on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Brush the remaining egg yolk over the top of the rolled strudel and bake in the middle of a preheated 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until it is golden.
Serves 10 as a side dish.

title: cola cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift together flour and sugar; set aside.
Mix margarine, cocoa and cola and heat to boiling point. Pour over sugar and flour.
Add eggs, marshmallows, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix until marshmallows are completely dissolved.
Bake in oblong pan at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Prepare pastry. Mix flour and sugar in a bowl. Stir in cherries, extract and food coloring. Pour into a pastry pie plate. Dot with butter. Cover with the top crust seal and flute the edges. Make several slits in top of cake. Sprinkle with sugar. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes until crust is brown.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Arrange nuts in pie crust.
Beat eggs.
Add and blend with corn syrup, butter and vanilla.
Combine flour and sugar.
Blend with egg mixture.
Pour over nuts in pie crust.
Let stand until nuts rise, so they will get a glaze during baking.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Beat margarine, brown sugar, white sugar and oil until light and fluffy.
Beat in sour milk, vanilla and eggs.
Add dry ingredients, mix until well blended.
Stir in zucchini.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: easy breakfast
directions: Cook potatoes in skins for 15 minutes; drain and cool.
Brown sausage and onion in a skillet; drain off excess fat.
Separate crescent dough into 2 sections of 4 triangles each.
Place in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Press over bottom and up sides just a bit to form a crust; seal holes.
Spoon sausage in.
Shred peeled potatoes.
Add on the sausage.
Top with Cheddar cheese. Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into mix.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° or until set.

title: lemon loaf
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and eggs.
Add milk.
Mix well.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and lemon rind.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover for 10 minutes.
Mix juice of 1 lemon with 1/4 cup white sugar and pour over cake.

title: "puppy chow"
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chips.
Pour over cereal and mix until well coated.
Shake with powdered sugar in large plastic bag.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen berries to jello. When jello is partially set, add nut meats and ice cream; stir in.
Ice cream will not be all melted.
Put in freezer until ready to serve.
Remove 15 minutes before serving.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Combine sugar, molasses and water.
Cook until it forms a soft ball in water, then add vanilla, vinegar and butter.
Cook until it turns brittle in cold water.
Pour syrup over popped corn, tossing kernels apart with a spoon.

title: cheese and vegetable chowder
directions: In a 4-quart Dutch oven combine first 5 ingredients.
Boil; reduce heat and simmer covered for 15 minutes.
Combine the milk and cornstarch; add to soup along with frozen beans.
Simmer, covered, for 10 to 15 minutes more or until beans are tender. Makes 4 to 6 main dish servings.

title: egg omelette
directions: Saute green peppers, onions and jalapeno peppers in skillet sprayed with Pam. Add ham. Pour in stirred eggs, milk and cheese. Cook until done. Salt and pepper to taste. Serve with tomato slices.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crush wafers; set aside.
Mix eggs, sugar and margarine.
Add milk, coconut, pecans and vanilla.
Stir in crushed wafers (will be thick).
Pour into pound cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
May be baked in small loaf pans.

title: orange and onion salad
directions: Place oranges and onion in serving bowl; set aside.
In small jar with tight-fitting lid, shake together all remaining ingredients.
Toss oranges and onion with dressing and serve. Serves 4.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef in oil with onion, garlic and parsley.
Add tomato paste, 2 cups water, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add lasagna to 6 quarts of salted, boiling water, stirring often to prevent sticking together.
Cook for 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake sweet potatoes until tender and peel them.
Mash them, and stir in margarine while they are hot.
After margarine is melted add remaining ingredients, and mix at medium speed until well blended.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Add topping, and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef jerky
directions: Slice roast.
Remove all fat from meat that you can.
Mix all ingredients together; add sliced meat.
Let set together overnight.
Mix well so all meat has some of mixture on it.
Pour off liquid.
Place meat flat on tray of food dehydrator.
Dry at 145° for about 12 hours.
Check to see that jerky is dry before removing.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix oleo, Crisco and sugar until creamed.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon meringue coconut pie
directions: Place all ingredients on top of double boiler and stir constantly over hot water, using low heat, until mixture thickens. Chill 1 hour in refrigerator before pouring filling into pie crust.

title: mushroom meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients in slow cooker. Cover and cook on low 6-8 hours.

title: chickaritos
directions: In bowl, combine chicken, chilies, onions, cheese and seasonings.
Mix well; chill until ready to use.
Remove half of the pastry from refrigerator at a time.
On a lightly floured board, roll to a 9 x 12-inch rectangle.
Cut into 9 small rectangles.
Place about 2 tablespoons of filling across the center of each rectangle. Wet edges of pastry with water and roll pastry around filling.
Crimp edges with fork to seal.
Place seam-side down on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Serve with salsa and guacamole.
Serves 18 appetizers or 6 to 8 main dish servings.

title: aunt estelle's frosted banana bars
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter, eggs, sugar, bananas and vanilla. Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to cream mixture and mix well.
Pour into greased baking pan (15x10x1-inch).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: glazed potato doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool until lukewarm.
Stir in yeast, potatoes and eggs. Gradually add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn onto floured surface; knead until smooth and satiny.
Place in a lightly greased bowl; turn over to grease top.
Cover.
Let rise in a warm place until doubled, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple squares
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well, like pie crust.
Beat the egg yolks in measuring cup; add milk to make 2/3 cup.
Mix into flour mixture, handling gently.
Roll half to fit a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crumble the corn flakes over bottom of crust.

title: barbecued chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients in a measuring cup and pour over chicken wings in a baking dish.
Marinate 24 hours before baking at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: malcalm's duck
directions: Marinate duck 2 hours in mixture of Adolph's meat marinade and white wine.
Shake flour in oven bag.
Place duck in oven bag and cut bag 1/2-inch in 6 places.
Bake duck approximately 30 minutes at 325°.
Serve with sauce made of 1/2 cup currant jelly and 1/2 cup wine.
Heat on stove until almost boiling.

title: mexican cheesecake(can be made day before)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine cheeses.
Beat until fluffy.
Stir in 1 cup sour cream and taco seasoning.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in chiles.
Pour into 9-inch spring-form pan. Bake 35 or 40 minutes or until center is firm.
Remove from oven.
Cool 10 minutes. Spoon remaining 1 cup sour cream over cheesecake.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Cool completely.
Cover and refrigerate several hours. Before serving, remove sides of spring-form pan and top with salsa.
Serve with plain taco chips.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in 3 cups boiling water.
Add cranberries and apples after cooling liquid and pour into 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: cheddar surprise
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain.
Combine all ingredients. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: cherry supreme
directions: Cut butter into flour until crumbly; add nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool crust.
Mix cream cheese and 10x sugar until blended.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour on top of cooled crust.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Can use any type of fruit on top.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix together and pour into prepared pie shell.
Cool.

title: mary's favorite gazpacho
directions: Place 2 c. of the V8 and HALF of all the veggies into blender.
Add vinegar, oil, garlic, pepper sauce and process until smooth.
Pour into large pot and add remaining vegetables and V8. Chill for several hours and serve cold.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Boil water and butter.
Lower heat and add flour to form ball. Cool.
Then add eggs, one at a time.
Beat.
Bake in an 11 x 15-inch greased pan at 400° for 35 minutes.
Check.

title: party mix candy
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Melt white chocolate in microwave for about 2 minutes until completely melted.
(Watch closely and stir often so it doesn't burn.)
Pour over mixture and stir until completely covered.
Spread out on a cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Let cool completely and then break into pieces.

title: shortcake
directions: Turn into 2 (9-inch) pie pans.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: funnel cake
directions: Combine flour, milk, baking soda, salt and egg.
Let batter rest for 10 minutes.
Heat oil until very hot.
Drip the batter through a funnel into the hot fat, forming a kind of spiral design.
Flip over when brown and brown the other side.
Drain on paper towel and sprinkle with the confectioners sugar.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut stew meat into chunks and coat lightly with flour.
Brown in heated oil.
To drippings of oil, add garlic and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add remainder of flour.
Add water, bouillon, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir until slightly thickened. Add meat and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 1/2 hours, until tender, stirring occasionally.

title: my favorite cracker jacks
directions: Cook all ingredients to a soft stage and pour over popcorn and peanuts, stirring good.
Place in preheated oven at 200°, stirring every 15 minutes for 1 hour.
Remove and let cool and store in an airtight container.
Good stuff!

title: blue rhubarb jam
directions: Cook until tender.
Add 1 can blueberry pie filling and bring to a rapid boil.
Add 1 - 6 oz. Or 2 - 3 oz. Packages raspberry jello and stir until dissolved.
Put in blender and blend until smooth.
Ready to seal in jars.

title: mini fruit cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Combine fruit and nuts with 1/4 cup flour; set aside. Cream together butter and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Mix in vanilla. Combine remaining 1 3/4 cups flour, salt and baking soda. Add to creamed mixture alternately with 1/2 cup apple juice. Start and end with flour mixture. Stir in fruit and nuts. Spoon batter into 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans. Bake for 60 to 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. Cool. Makes 2 fruit cakes.

title: strawberry banana punch
directions: Combine strawberries, bananas, orange juice and lemonade concentrates in container of electric blender; blend until smooth. Combine soft-drink mix, pineapple juice, water, and sugar in large mixing bowl or pan, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Add fruit mixture, mixing well.
Freeze (fills three 1/2 gallon orange juice cartons).
To serve, thaw to consistency of a "Slurpy", about 4 hours.
Pour in punch bowl or in pitcher with spout.
Yield:
About 6 quarts (fills a small punch bowl).

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar.
Bring to a boil and add apricot jello.
Refrigerate until partially set.
Mix cream cheese with milk until creamy.
Whip Dream Whip according to directions and fold into cream cheese mixture.
Fold cream cheese into partially set jello mixture.
Pour into jello mold.
This can be made several days in advance.
Keep in a tightly sealed container.

title: meat dressing
directions: Soak bread,
cornbread and crackers in about a quart of water. Stew
the
giblets
and
necks
separately.
When this cools, pick the
meat
from
the
necks
and grind with cooked giblets. Stew
the
hamburger
meat
with
onions,
salt
and pepper.
Mix all
of this into the first mixture.
Add onions, celery, salt, pepper, eggs and all the chicken broth.
Bake in a roast pan which is covered with foil and bake 1/2 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Chop and mash cooked shrimp and mix well with other ingredients.

title: squash pickles
directions: Stir salt into water in a very large bowl or divide into two bowls. Add squash. Weight down with a dinner plate and an unopened can to keep pickles under salt brine. Let stand 3 hours. Drain well.

title: easy cheesy potatoes
directions: Spray vegetable oil on medium glass dish. Layer potatoes, onions and spices in order.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: In the top of a double boiler, over hot but not boiling water, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually add milk and cook for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour a small amount of the hot milk mixture into the egg yolks, return all to double boiler.
Cook for 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from the heat; stir in vanilla.
Cool for about 10 minutes.
Divide mixture in half.
To one portion, stir in peanut butter; mix well.
To the remaining portion, stir in melted chocolate.
Allow mixtures to cool completely.
Fill pie crust with peanut butter mixture, then chocolate mixture.
Chill for 2-3 hours.
Just before serving, top with whipped cream and nuts.
Store leftovers in the refrigerator. Yield:
6-8 servings.

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Cream together peanut butter, cheese and milk.
Add powdered sugar.

title: bagne calde
directions: Cover bottom of pan with oil; heat and add butter.
Add garlic and cook until soft and brown.
Add anchovies; stir 1 minute.
Add cream; heat, do not boil.
Cook vegetables and meat in an electric frypan.
Serve like fondue.
Use bread for plates, then eat when soggy with sauce.

title: southern peanut butter pie
directions: In large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat eggs with corn syrup, sugar, peanut butter and vanilla until smooth, then stir in peanuts.
Pour mixture into chilled pie crust and bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Then bake pie for 30 minutes at 350°, until it is set and top is golden brown.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread into small pieces and put in large square pan. Mix raisins, cinnamon, vanilla and margarine.
Add to bread crumbs.
In separate bowl mix sugar and eggs; mix well.
Heat milk until warm.
Pour over egg mixture and mix.
Pour this over bread in pan.
Let set 5 minutes.
Cover pan with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then remove foil and bake for 30 more minutes.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Heat oil.
Add garlic, ginger and pepper.
Saute until garlic is golden.
Add chicken strips.
Brown about 4 minutes.
Remove meat.
Add vegetables and cook until vegetables are tender as you like.
Return chicken to skillet with vegetables.
Combine soy sauce, sugar and bouillon.
Add to meat and vegetables.
Mix and thicken with cornstarch and water.
Serve over rice.

title: hawaiian punch party punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, combine punch, grapefruit juice and grenadine.
Add strawberries.
Just before serving, add lemon-lime beverage and ice.
Float orange slices on top.
Makes approximately 32 servings (4 ounces each).

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Place cooked, chopped chicken in an 8 x 10-inch shallow baking dish.
Add celery and grated cheese.
Pour undiluted soup over. Sprinkle noodles on and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce and meatballs
directions: *Use less water if can't cook 5 hours.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter or oleo until clear.
Add to vegetables with the olives, pimentos and mushrooms.
Add the mushroom soup mixed with water and pour this over the vegetables and stir.
Heat through, about 25 minutes.
Add the grated cheese and stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: snickerdoodles(cookies)
directions: Mix in given order.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll in 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° until lightly brown, but still soft.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar, water and syrup in a pan.
Bring it to a boil (hard cook 300° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat.
Add baking soda, butter and Spanish peanuts.
Stir.
Pour into well-greased pan and let cool.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter together.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and then combine it with the cream cheese and peanut butter mixture.
Add milk and stir until smooth. Slowly stir in Cool Whip.
Divide mixture between 2 graham cracker crusts.
You can sprinkle chopped peanuts on tops of pies if you so desire.
Freeze pies until shortly before serving time.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from mandarin oranges and pineapple chunks into a large bowl.
To juice, add instant pudding and mix well.
Add the mandarin oranges and pineapple chunks.
Refrigerate.
Shortly before serving, add cut-up fruit of your choice.
Enjoy!

title: jiffie dessert
directions: Stir all together. Cool and serve.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water about 6 minutes.
Drain water off macaroni and place in a lightly greased crock-pot or spray lightly with Pam.
Cut margarine into small pieces and stir into macaroni until melted.
Add remaining ingredients to macaroni in crock-pot, leaving some cheese to sprinkle on top.
Cook on low setting for 2 to 3 hours, or high setting for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Brown onion in shortening. Mix in seasonings. Add chicken and brown 10 minutes.
Add water and cover. Simmer until tender, about 1
hour. Remove chicken and set aside to cool.
Add sour cream to drippings. If more gravy is desired, add light cream.
Remove chicken from bones and add to sour cream mixture. Add dumplings and heat.

title: ma's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground chuck until completely cooked.

Drain fat, leaving only enough to saute chopped onion and crushed garlic. When vegetables are tender, add both cans of crushed tomatoes. Add a splash of red wine, chopped parsley, Parmesan cheese and Vegetable Magic.
Let simmer for several hours and serve over hot spaghetti or linguine.

title: green chili-cheese bake
directions: Butter an 8 x 8-inch pan; drain 1 can of chilies and spread onto bottom of pan.
Next, add grated cheeses.
In separate bowl, mix eggs, milk and chilies; pour over cheese.
Bake for one hour at 350°.
This recipe will serve 5 people.

title: peach pickles(about 3 quarts)
directions: Tie cloves and cinnamon in a spice bag.
Peel peaches.
To prevent darkening, drop peaches into water containing 2 tablespoons each salt and vinegar per gallon.
Mix vinegar, sugar, ginger and water.
Add spice bag and bring to a boil.
Rinse and drain peaches.
Drop into boiling syrup.
Cook about 1 minute (until they are tender and can be pierced with a toothpick).
Remove from heat. Pack into jars, leaving 1/2-inch head space.
Fill jar to within 1/2 inch of top with boiling syrup.
Remove air bubbles.
Adjust lids.
Process 20 minutes in a boiling water bath.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Mix beans and taco mix.
Layer in dish. Mix sour cream and mayonnaise.
Spread over bean dip mixture.
Pour picante sauce over sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped onions, cheese and top with olives.

title: jogging-in-a-jug(health juice)
directions: Yes,
these can be prepared in the microwave oven.
For large quantities
of
these you may prefer to use the conventional kettle
method;
but
for
small quantities of certain fruits, the
microwave oven is a cool, relatively easy method of cooking.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Cook potatoes.
Mash and sweeten to taste.
Roll into a ball with a marshmallow in each one, then roll in coconut.
Put in baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for about 25 minutes.
Very good!

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain the green beans.
In casserole dish, blend soup, milk, soy sauce and a dash of pepper.
Stir in beans and 1/2 can of onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Stir and top with remaining onions.
Bake for 5 minutes more.
Do not cover.

title: yummy pork ribs
directions: Place ribs in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar over ribs.
Slice onions and place on top.
Squeeze mustard over top. Dump jar of salsa over.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Seal pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes (or until the meat falls off the bones).
Serves 2 to 6 depending on how well you like them.
Serve with lots of napkins.

title: peanut butter delights
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk, salt and vanilla flavoring. Bring to a boil. Add stick of butter. Cook for about 5 minutes. Take off heat. Add peanut butter. Mix well. Add oatmeal. Dip on wax paper.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid according to directions.
Mix can of Awake according to directions.
Add to Kool-Aid.
Add crushed pineapple, Hawaiian Punch, orange drink, pineapple juice, sliced strawberries, sliced bananas and ginger ale.
Chill Kool-Aid, Awake, Hawaiian Punch, orange drink, pineapple juice, crushed pineapple and strawberries.
Mix all together.
Before you serve, slice bananas into punch to float on top.
Add ginger ale and serve.

title: oatmeal (boiled) cookies
directions: Soften oleo.
Mix cocoa with sugar.
Then add milk and butter in saucepan.
Bring to boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add oatmeal, peanut butter, vanilla and nuts.
Beat well.
Work fast.
Spoon out onto waxed paper.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Add milk.
Put on stove top and heat to lukewarm.
Beat egg yolks and add to mixture; stir.
Cook on stove top.
Stir until thick.
Pour thick sauce over wafers and sliced bananas.

title: spinach and ham roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, mix soup, sour cream and mustard.
In medium bowl, combine 1/2 cup soup mixture, rice, spinach, cheese, eggs, onion and flour.
Mix well.
Place about 2 heaping tablespoons of the spinach mixture on each ham slice. Roll up and place close together, seam side down in an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Spoon remaining soup mixture over ham rolls.
Top with crumbs and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes or until hot.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel, core and slice apples thinly.
Sprinkle sugar, flour and spices on apples, mix well.
Fill crust with mixture, add butter. Add top crust, brush with milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Rotate, then bake 20 to 25 minutes (or more).

title: rave review rolls!
directions: Mix all the ingredients well.
Pour into miniature muffin tins (well greased) and bake at 400° until brown.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Heat milk.
Mix sugar, flour and salt together and gradually stir into milk.
Mix small amount with beaten egg yolks and stir into hot mixture.
Cook over medium heat in heavy pan until thickened.
Stir in gelatin.
Mix well and let cool, then add Milnot and vanilla (14 cups liquid fills 1 gallon freezer).
Freeze in hand-turned or electric ice cream freezer.

title: sunshine pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain well.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice. Mix together pasta, pineapple juice and remaining ingredients, except pineapple chunks and broccoli.
Arrange pineapple and broccoli around pasta.
Cover and chill.

title: three bean enchiladas
directions: Stack tortillas and wrap tightly in foil.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until warm.

title: sausage and peppers italiano
directions: In covered skillet, over medium heat, cook sausage in
2 tablespoons water 5 minutes.
Uncover and cook until sausage is browned. Add green peppers, onion and garlic to sausage in skillet.
Cook until peppers are tender-crisp, stirring frequently. Spoon off fat. Stir in soup, 1 cup water and vinegar. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: betty's broccoli(quick and easy)
directions: Mix broccoli, raisins, bacon and chopped onions. Blend mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar. Mix well with the broccoli mixture.

title: quick homemade chili
directions: Heat oil in large skillet; add ground beef.
Stir until meat loses its color.
Pour off excess fat.
Add beans with their liquid, onions and green pepper.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt and chili powder.
Simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally until chili is desired thickness.

title: rum cake(mike's favorite cake)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add wet ingredients. Beat with electric mixer until blended.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Sprinkle pan with chopped nuts.
Pour batter over nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Cool.
Icepick top of cake and pour glaze over cake.

title: wine cookies
directions: Cream the butter; add sugar.
Add egg yolks and beat 2 1/2 minutes.
Add wine and beat again.
Add flour and mix well.
Form cookies into balls.
Make well in center and fill with jelly. Bake at 350° until slightly brown.

title: savory glazed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Arrange chicken, skin side up, in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with onion and oil.
Roast 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt the cream drops in microwave for about 1 minute.
Take out and mix in the peanut butter.
Mix quickly and pour into a greased 10-inch pan or Pyrex dish.
Let cool, then cut into squares.
Ready to eat.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil until they become light brown.
Add crushed tomatoes and tomato paste.
Mix together and add small amount of water to thin.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Add cooked Italian sausage.
Serve over any type of pasta.
Enjoy! Chow!

title: calvin's mango sauce(for coconut shrimp)
directions: Mix all together and bring to bubbling. Cover loosely.
Simmer on low for 1/2 hour.
Add what you need.

title: parmesan steak fries
directions: Pare potatoes and cut into slices (should look like big French fries).
Combine flour, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper in medium-size bowl.
Moisten potato slices with water; coat potatoes in flour mixture.
Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Place potatoes in a single layer in pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, turning once during baking.
When brown, remove from oven.

title: kelli's mock oyster dip
directions: Cook broccoli in water (overdone).
Saute onion in butter. Add cream of mushroom soup, mushrooms and juice.
Break up garlic cheese and add to mixture.
Add hot sauce and broccoli.
Mix well. Keep warm in chafing dish.
Eat with dipper chips or snack crackers.

title: special k bars
directions: Melt together in double boiler, chocolate chips and peanut butter chips.
In another large pan, bring to a boil, 1 cup of white sugar and 1 cup of light Karo syrup.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 1/2 cups of peanut butter.
Mix well and pour in 6 cups of Special K. Press into 10 x 15-inch buttered pan and spread chocolate mixture on top.
Chill until one hour before serving; cut into bars.
Makes 7 dozen 2 x 1-inch bars.

title: batter for fish
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Mix other ingredients well and fold in egg white.
Dry fish.
Dip in batter and deep-fry 4 to 6 minutes.
Drain.
Will coat 2 pounds fish.

title: grandmommy's indian curry
directions: In a large pan, cover chicken with water and cook until chicken is tender.
While chicken is cooking, dice bell pepper and onions.
You can use a food processor if you wish.
Roll out meatballs about the size of walnuts.
Remove chicken from broth and let cool to debone.
Save broth; add bell peppers, onions, meatballs and seasonings to broth.
Simmer, debone chicken and add to broth.
Peel eggs; add to chicken broth.
This dish is best if you cook for about an hour; add eggs about 15 or 20 minutes before removing from heat.
Serve over rice.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage and chop bell pepper, onion and ripe tomato. Mix together in large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt, sugar and black pepper.
