Mix and refrigerate for one hour.
Heat oil in large heavy skillet.
Add vegetables and hot water.
Stir well.
Cover and cook for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown the hamburger; keep the drippings.
In a large kettle, add the hamburger mixture and all of the other ingredients. Simmer for at least 1/2 hour and serve.

title: caramel pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: In a large pan or heavy skillet, put 2 cups of sugar on low heat.
Stir often while sugar is melting into a liquid.
Remove from heat as soon as the sugar is all liquid.
Immediately pour liquid in a small stream into milk, stirring constantly until all liquid sugar is dissolved.
Milk will be a light caramel color now.

title: corn and olives
directions: Fry bacon, remove from grease.
Saute onion and add drained corn and olives.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Saute meat in skillet. Add taco seasoning mix, tomato sauce and water. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, simmer uncovered for 15 minutes. Add tortilla chips; mix, being careful not to break the chips. Pour into a 2-inch deep X 8-inch round or square baking dish. Bake in 400 degree oven 10 to 15 minutes. Top with cheese.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender.
Add soup and mix until heated thoroughly.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir until cheese melts.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: white bean soup
directions: Wash beans in lots of cold water.
Remove beans that float to top.
Cover beans with more water and let soak for several hours, usually overnight.
Add salt pork or ham bone and bring beans to a boil.
Cut heat down and let beans simmer slowly until tender, about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: mexican-style pot roast
directions: Trim excess fat from roast.
In Dutch oven, brown meat on both sides in hot oil.
Combine undrained tomatoes, chopped green chilies, 1/4 cup water, dry taco seasoning mix, beef bouillon granules and sugar.
Pour over meat.
Cover and simmer for 2 to 3 hours until meat is
tender.

title: perfect peanut brittle
directions: Mix all ingredients in a heavy kettle and boil until slightly brown.
Remove from fire, add the soda.
Stir well.
Pour on lightly greased cookie sheet and spread thin.
When cool, break into pieces.
Store in plastic or metal containers.

title: monkey bread
directions: Thaw frozen bread dough, then cut into pieces and form into balls about the size of walnuts.
Melt butter. Add enough brown sugar to make paste.
In bottom of Bundt pan, place chopped nuts and brown sugar to taste.
Roll dough balls in brown sugar paste, then place balls in pan, sprinkling with cinnamon and brown sugar. Let bread rise 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Remove bread from pan immediately after baking or bread will stick to pan.

title: saucy apple swirl cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Blend cake mix, applesauce and eggs (can use 3 egg substitutes).
Pour 1/2 batter into pan.
Sprinkle sugar mixture.
Cover with remaining batter.
Bake at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes.
Check with toothpick.
Cool upright for 25 minutes. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine meat, eggs and bread.
Form into small meat balls. Place in oblong pan.
Mix together soups and water.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake one hour at 350°.
Then bake 1 hour at 250°.
Tastes like country fried steak and gravy.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Make
a dark brown roux of flour and bacon grease in a heavy large pot.
Add onion, green onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic.
Saute until soft.
Add tomato paste and mix well.
Add all other ingredients except last three.
Simmer slowly for one hour, stirring occasionally.
Add shrimp and cook until done, 5 to 15 minutes.
This should set a while and is actually better the next day, reheated but not boiled.
Add parsley before serving. Serve over rice.
Serves 10.

title: easy homemade deer sausage
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape into 2 log rolls and wrap in foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Unwrap and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and cool.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate.
Makes delicious party snacks served on Club crackers.

title: steak marinade
directions: Brush over meat.
Wrap meat with plastic wrap and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in loaf pan 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry topping for angel cake
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water. Stir in 4 tablespoons sugar. Cool until almost jelled. Fold in strawberries and whipping cream, whipped. Beat on low speed.
Slice cake twice lengthwise and put mixture on top and sides.
Refrigerate.

title: cupcakes
directions: Take bread and put in a pan.
Make shapes with them.
Put them in the oven.
Cook 10 minutes.
Take out of oven and eat them.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cukes and slice.
Next, slice the onion into 1/8 or 1/4-inch slices.
Add salt and ice to the cukes and onion.
Let it stand 3 hours.
Mix sugar, spices and vinegar; heat to boiling. Drain cukes and onion.
Add to vinegar and heat 5 minutes.
Pack in pint jars and seal.

title: italian pasta and spinach casserole
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Meanwhile, in a bowl, stir together all remaining ingredients except spaghetti sauce; stir in spaghetti.
Place pasta mixture in 13 x 9-inch baking dish; pour spaghetti sauce over entire surface. Cover with plastic wrap; microwave on High until heated through (9 to 11 minutes).
Or if you want to fix in a conventional oven, do not cover with plastic wrap and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dino's cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spray a cast-iron skillet with Pam cooking spray. Pour into prepared pan and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: powdered sugar cookies
directions: Mix well.
Chill dough.
Roll in small balls and flatten with a glass that's been greased and dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops.
Brown pork chops in small amount of oil on both sides.
Place in covered baking dish.
Pile cooked rice on pork chops.
Drain oil from skillet.
Put soup and water in skillet and simmer about 5 minutes.
Pour over pork chops. Bake for about 30 minutes in regular oven at 400° or microwave on High.

title: fish with cajun sauce
directions: Wash and dry fish fillet.
Dredge with lemon juice, salt and pepper on both sides.
In a frying pan heat oil.
Quick fry fish, high heat, 2 minutes each side.
Remove and set aside.
Add butter and saute tomatoes for 1 minute.
Add onions.
Saute for 1 minute. Add broth.
Stir in sugar.
Simmer (optional:
add jalapeno peppers).
Add fish.
Cook for 15 minutes or until fish flakes off easily.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: hershey's cocoa frosting
directions: Melt cocoa and butter.
Add to sifted sugar.
Then add water. Beat well (large mixer works best).
Add vanilla and salt.
Work quickly to frost cake.
If it gets too thick, add small spoonfuls of water gradually.
Frosts a large cake.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender, drain.
Slice onions and pepper very thin.
Bring oil, vinegar, dill seed, pepper and sugar to a boil, pour over the vegetables.
Let stand overnight.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 can of onions.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at
Top with remaining onions and bake for 5 more minutes.

title: cheesesteak pockets
directions: In a skillet, brown and cook beef or chicken sandwich steaks. Add vegetable oil, onions, mushrooms and salt and pepper to taste. Mix well.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat pita bread on a baking sheet for 5 to 7 minutes.
Then for each pocket, spoon cheese in first, then meat mixture, then more cheese.
Repeat until cheese is on top.
Place back in oven for 5 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Drain eggplant and cook.
Don't overcook.
Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Saute onions, celery and green pepper in butter about 10 minutes.
Mix bread mixture, onion, celery-pepper mixture and cooked eggplant together.
Add eggs, pimento and all seasonings. Mix well.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° until golden brown. Remove from oven and sprinkle cheese over top and return to oven and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: applesauce bars
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add egg and beat, then add applesauce and beat.
Add all dry ingredients and nut meats. Spread into a 10 x 14-inch shallow pan, greased and floured.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch quiche dish or pie plate. Cook and stir beef with onion over medium heat until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread into dish; sprinkle with chilies.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth, 15 seconds, in blender or high for 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into dish.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: american heart association seasoning
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
A great substitute for salt.

title: quick frosting
directions: Mix milk and sugar in 2-quart saucepan.
Add vanilla.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat and put directly into freezer (for 5 minutes).
Mix oleo and shortening to cream in large stand mixer bowl.
Must beat for usually 15 minutes at least.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring cornstarch, strawberry Jell-O, sugar and water to a boil and let cool.
Cook pie shell; place fresh, clean berries into pie shell.
Then pour in filling.
Cool in refrigerator.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: white chocolate popcorn
directions: Pour chocolate over popped corn and peanuts.
Mix until well coated.
Cool and break up.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken in serving pieces.
Salt chicken lightly.
Spread rice over bottom of greased pan.
Dilute mushroom soup with water. Add onion soup and mix well.
Put chicken over rice.
Then pour soup mixture over chicken and rice.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Reduce heat to 300°.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mary jo's pie crust
directions: Mix flour, Crisco, sugar and salt with fork.
In small bowl, beat water, vinegar and egg.
Add to first mixture; blend with a fork until dry ingredients are moistened.
Mold into ball with your hands and chill for 15 minutes or longer.
Roll into crust.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix with beater the cream cheese, Parmesan and mayonnaise until smooth.
Drain artichoke hearts and dice.
Fold into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Add and blend well mayonnaise, cold water and vanilla. Add to the above mixture and blend well flour, sugar, baking soda, cocoa and salt. Bake in lightly greased and floured 9 x 9 cake pan at 375° for approximately 30 minutes (use toothpick to test for doneness).

title: easy chicken delight
directions: Place chicken on a bed of sauce; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Add the rest of sauce on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered with foil, in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook the pasta according to directions.
Take chicken out and place the Mozzarella and Provolone cheese on chicken.
Re-cover and cook for 10 minutes, until cheese is melted.
Place on pasta with sauce over top.

title: chip dip
directions: In a bowl, mix cream cheese, garlic salt and milk. Finely chop onion, scraping onion juice into bowl as well. Add chopped onion to cream cheese mixture. Mix well.

title: german slaw
directions: Mix cider vinegar, vegetable oil, salt, celery seed and mustard.
Heat to boil.
Put chopped cabbage, chopped bell peppers and sliced onion in bowl.
Pour sugar over vegetables.
Pour hot mixture over all.

title: blueberry angel dessert
directions: In mixing bowl, combine cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip and cake cubes.
Spread evenly in ungreased pan.
Top with pie filling.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: creamed soups
directions: Cook vegetables and bouillon cube in water until tender.
Melt butter and gradually add flour.
Stir in milk to make a thin white sauce.
Pour white sauce into cooking vegetables.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add cheese.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes, being careful not to scorch milk.
Serve and enjoy.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Crumble biscuits fine.
Pour hot water over them to make soft. Add 1/2 cup sugar over this.
Sprinkle the nutmeg or any flavoring over mixture.
Beat eggs, milk and 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat well.
Pour over biscuit mixture.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
May be served hot or chilled.
If hot, bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serve with crackers or toast points. Time:
Approximately 15 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat 1/2 cup oil and 1 cup sugar together.
Add 2 beaten eggs and 3 bananas mashed to a pulp.
Beat well.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to first mixture with milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Bake in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, lined with wax paper on the bottom.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: riley's chicken parmesan
directions: Pound chicken breasts flat or roll flat by putting in a plastic bag and using rolling pin.
Beat egg.
Dip chicken in egg to coat (Riley loves this part).
Dip egged chicken in bread crumbs to coat.
Dip crumbed chicken in cheese; press cheese into chicken.
Fry in olive oil about 3 to 5 minutes per side or less (hot pan).

title: cheesecake dip
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add sour cream, milk and extract; mix until smooth.
Transfer to serving bowl.
Place strawberries and crumbs in separate serving bowls. Dip strawberries into cheesecake mix, then into crumbs.
Yield 1 cup cheesecake mix.

title: percolator punch
directions: Combine first 3 juices in percolator.
Place sugar and spices in percolator basket.
Perk full cycle.
Serve hot.
Makes 16 (1/2 cup) servings.
Good on cold winter day!

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown the onions and meat in butter.
Add mushrooms, salt, Worcestershire sauce, bouillon and flour.
Blend well.
Bring to a gentle boil for 5 minutes.
Pour into buttered casserole dish. Combine milk and biscuit mix.
Spoon over meat mixture.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes, uncovered.
Spread sour cream on top. Sprinkle with grated cheese and return to oven for 5 minutes. Serves 6.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet and add onion to saute.
Add milk, soup, broccoli and cheese.
Mix well and simmer gently.
Add rice to skillet mixture.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Bake until bubbly on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: banana split brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare brownie mix according to package.
Pour brownie mix on 14-inch circle.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Cool to room temperature.
Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Spread over brownie crust.
Top with fruit and nuts.
Melt chocolate and butter together, stirring until smooth.
Drizzle over pizza.
Cut and serve.

title: italian barbecue sauce
directions: Place garlic, parsley and basil to large bowl.	Add tomato sauce (uncooked).
Add water and olive oil.
Mix together and let stand in refrigerator for one hour.

title: white gingerbread
directions: Sift flour.
Combine with sugar and shortening.
Mix until crumbly; reserve 1/2 cup.
To remaining flour mixture, add spices, baking powder, soda, egg and buttermilk.
Blend.
Pour into a greased pan.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: granny's coconut cake
directions: Blend shortening and butter, gradually add sugar until fluffy. Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat well after each one.

title: banana coffee cake muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 2 1/2-inch muffin pans.
Stir together in a small bowl the flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Reserve.

title: okra patties
directions: Combine cut okra, onion, salt, pepper, water and egg. Mix well. Combine flour, baking powder, meal and garlic powder. Add to okra mixture. Stir well. Make into patties, then fry in 1/2-inch hot oil over medium heat until brown on both sides. Drain on paper towels.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: In a bowl, beat egg.
Add sugar and melted shortening. Add dry ingredients and liquid. Add raisins or nuts, if desired.
Place in muffin tins and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening and add eggs; beat by hand. Sift flour and cocoa together and add to the first mixture.
Beat well and add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into oblong pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes.
When done, spread marshmallows evenly over cake.
Put into oven until slightly melted.
When cake is cool, add icing.

title: sugar-free pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine water and fructose and simmer over low heat 5 minutes, then cool. Mix dry pudding into fructose mixture. Add skim milk and eggs; blend well. Pour into pie shell and sprinkle pecans and Grape-Nuts on top. Bake for 30 minutes, until top is firm. Cook 3 hours before slicing. Serves 8.

title: holiday prime beef tzimmes
directions: Brown meat in oil on all sides.
Sprinkle seasoning over meat; add prunes, tomato sauce, raisins and boiling water.
Slowly simmer, covered, 1 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables and cook until almost done.
Add honey and lemon juice; mix and simmer a few minutes until blended.
Serves 6.

title: tropical sea jello
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water, then add pineapple juice.
Let slightly gel for 2 to 3 hours.
With wire whisk, add sour cream and mix thoroughly.
Stir in with a spoon the remaining ingredients.
Place in an 8 x 8-inch pan and refrigerate overnight for best results.
Cut into squares.
Serves 6.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in a large pot and bring to a boil. Turn down and let simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Put in hot quart jars and seal.

title: catalina stir-fry
directions: Cook rice as directed and drain.
Set aside.
Stir-fry shrimp, red pepper, and snow peas in oil for 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 1 minute.
Stir in rice.

title: 7 happiness beef and rice casserole
directions: Place ground chuck in a large bowl.
Add everything, except the cheese.
Mix well.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Reduce heat and bake at 275° to 300° for 1 hour longer.

title: lemon nut bread(quick bread)
directions: Cream butter and sugar in mixing bowl.
Blend in eggs one at a time and lemon rind.
Stir in sifted ingredients alternately with liquids.
Spoon batter in lightly greased loaf pan.
Be sure batter is in all corners of pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan.
Cool.

title: pecan pie(makes three pies)
directions: Cream oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Add other ingredients (except pie shells).
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 310° about 1 hour or until set solid.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Place in casserole dish.
Heat soup, liquid from beans and cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Sprinkle drained mushrooms and bacon bits over beans. Cover with cheese sauce. Cook in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Crush onion rings and put on top. Heat in oven for 5 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim fat from meat; cut meat in strips.
Heat oil in skillet; add meat and cook until brown.
Stir in water, onions, garlic salt and ginger.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat, cover and simmer 12 to 15 minutes.
Add green pepper strips during last 5 minutes of simmering.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix the cracker crumbs and butter for crust.
Mix powdered sugar, eggs and butter on high speed until fluffy.
Spread on crust.
Split bananas lengthwise and put on top, then crushed, drained pineapple.
Put Cool Whip or Dream Whip on top, then cherries and nuts.
Set in refrigerator.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and then add next four ingredients.
Stir in margarine and pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: gumdrop candy (thutlee)
directions: Place gelatin and sugar in a saucepan.
Stir in water and salt.
Heat over low heat and stir until dissolved.
Simmer for 20 minutes, remove from heat and add orange juice.
Chill, stirring occasionally until thickened.

title: flancati(a fried dough pastry)
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add sour cream, wine, sugar and salt.
Mix until well combined.
Add flour, reserving about 1/2 cup.
Mix with wooden spoon until dough develops.
Add more flour as needed. Dough should be soft.
Transfer to a lightly floured surface and knead well.
Cut dough into 2 or 3 sections and work each section into a ball.
Place on floured surface and cover with a bowl.
Let rest 1 hour.
Roll each ball on a floured board or pastry cloth until very thin.
Cut rolled out dough into 3-inch squares or any size or shape desired.
Each rolled section should yield 25 to 30 flancati.
Make 1 or 2 slits in each square.
Invert corner and pull through slits.
Fryer should be set at 340° and filled to a 1-inch depth.
Fry in heated grease until just faint tinge of brown appears.
Turn and fry on other side.
Remove from fat and drain on rack or paper toweling.
Dust with powdered sugar while hot. Flancati will hold well in airtight container.
They also can be frozen.

title: mustard chicken
directions: Coat chicken breasts with Dijonnaise, then with bread crumbs. Coat a pan with cooking spray and bake chicken at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in 1/8-inch diagonal slivers.
Place oil, salt and pepper; add slivers of steak and brown.
Then add onion, garlic, green peppers, celery and bouillon.
Cover skillet with tight fitting lid.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce; add to mixture and cook until juice thickens. Serve with hot cooked rice.

title: sweet and sour zucchini salad
directions: Pour tarragon vinegar over soup mix and set aside.
Combine sugar, salt, pepper, oil, cider vinegar, green pepper, celery and carrots.
Add soup mixture and stir well.
Add the zucchini; stir again.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: watermelon punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour half of mixture into punch bowl.
Use remaining half of mixture to replace used punch.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine
ingredients; stir until mixed well.
Turn into casserole
dish.
Bake at 350° until mixture is set and top is golden brown.

title: bacon wrapped bread sticks
directions: Take a plate and pour grated cheese on plate.
Take a bread stick and wrap in slice of bacon.
Roll the bacon wrapped bread stick in the cheese, then place in oven at 350° and cook until bacon is cooked.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 6 tablespoons juice.
Mix sugar, flour, pineapple juice and melted butter.
Pour over pineapple chunks and toss with grated cheese.
Top with cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: white chocolate strawberry pie
directions: Combine pineapple, yogurt, pudding mix and toasted coconut. Mix well. Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon into crust.
If desired, top with additional Cool Whip and sprinkle with toasted coconut. Refrigerate.

title: tuna ball
directions: Soften cheese.
Blend in mayonnaise and tuna; mix well.
Add other ingredients, except nuts; beat until fluffy.
Chill thoroughly.
Form into ball and roll in pecans.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain both cans of asparagus and spread in a casserole dish. Layer cheese soup and the mushroom soup.
Layer croutons on top and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheese is melted and browned.

title: italian style pork chops
directions: Trim fat from chops.
Put a little oil in a heavy pan; heat over medium heat.
Brown chops; remove from pan.
Pour off fat. Add a little oil to pan over low heat.
Saute onions, pepper and garlic until wilted.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Put chops back in.
Cook over low heat until tender.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: pasta salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Season shrimp with soy sauce, wine and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in
nonstick pan or wok; scramble eggs.
Break egg into small pieces and set aside.
Add 1 tablespoon oil in pan, stir-fry shrimp and spring onion in hot oil for two minutes.
Then add ham/pork, green peas, mushrooms, onion, celery, sesame oil and pepper.
Continue to cook over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes, then set aside.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch, stir in water gradually.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil one minute.
Slowly stir at least half of the hot mixture into the beaten egg yolks.
Return mixture to saucepan. Boil together one minute longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, continue stirring until smooth.
Add butter, lemon juice and rind.
Pour into baked crust.
Cover with meringue.
Bake until a delicate brown.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook onions in grease until brown.
Add potatoes, carrots, sauce, seasonings and juice.
Boil.
Add clams, half and half, chives and butter.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Fry bacon crisp.
Add, crumpled, into soup.
(Save some to garnish as served.)
Add cornstarch to thicken as desired.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Garnish with chives and bacon.
Freezes for 1 to 2 months.

title: peach heaven
directions: Pour boiling water over peaches and peel immediately.
Slice into a large Pyrex dish, filling only half way.
Whip the cream until thick and blend in vanilla.
Cover peaches with
the whipped cream.
Place dish in the freezer for 2 hours.
Just before serving, remove from the freezer; spread brown sugar over the top and broil on the highest oven rack until cream begins to come through the brown sugar layer.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: california mold
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first five ingredients. Break up dry Top Ramen noodles (do not cook).
Toss.

title: german pizza
directions: Melt butter in 10-inch skillet.
Add hash browns, onions, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Stir to combine; cover and cook over low heat about 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Pour 4 slightly beaten eggs evenly over the potatoes.
Arrange, spoke fashion, luncheon meat cut in 3/4 x 3 1/2-inch sticks over the top.
Cover and cook until eggs are set.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup shredded cheese.
Cover until cheese melts.
Cut into wedges. Serves 5 or 6.

title: french coconut pies
directions: Mix in the order given.
Pour gently into 12 miniature (Bama Brand) unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in a saucepan; cook to soft ball stage.
Add dates and nuts.
Continue cooking until dates are dissolved or until small amount forms a small, firm ball in cold water.
Pour out on a damp cloth and shape into a 2-inch roll. Chill in refrigerator until firm and slice
in 1/2-inch slices.

title: fish creole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse fillets and pat dry.
Arrange in shallow baking dish.
Melt margarine in a medium saucepan.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Carefully pour tomato mixture over fish.
Bake 35 minutes or until fish flakes easily.

title: steaks of perfection
directions: In black iron skillet, melt butter.
Lay steak in skillet, season and top with onions and peppers.
Cook to desired taste on low to medium fire.

title: easy baked stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large baking dish with cover.
Bake at 350°
for 4 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: glorified lemonade
directions: Boil sugar and water 10 minutes.
Cool.
Add juice of lemons and limes and the orange or lemon beverage or ginger ale.
Serves 6.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add meat and cook over medium heat until browned.
Add onions.
Cook 5 minutes or until soft.
Mix in tomatoes, mushrooms, ketchup, paprika, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer about 45 minutes.
Blend flour and water; mix into meat. Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Cook noodles.
Drain and serve with goulash.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice.
Stir in other ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: tortillas
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Place 3 tablespoons batter on hot ungreased griddle. Spread in a thin circle (375°).
Turn onto other side and lightly golden.

title: chicken-dressing casserole
directions: Combine stone-ground cornmeal, baking soda and baking powder in a medium mixing bowl; make a well in the center of mixture. Combine buttermilk and 1/4 cup egg substitute; add buttermilk mixture to dry ingredients, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into an 8-inch cast-iron skillet coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes until golden. Remove cornbread from skillet and cool slightly on a wire rack. Crumble cooled cornbread into a large mixing bowl.
Add chicken and remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon mixture into a 2-quart baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, brown sugar and margarine until crumbly. Stir in oats. Reserving 1 1/2 cups oat mixture, press remainder into a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan. Bake 10 minutes.

title: bread pudding with currants and maple syrup
directions: Mix and bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Pour maple syrup over.

title: no peek casserole
directions: Combine ingredients well in a 2-quart casserole; cover.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Don't peek until it's done.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Serves 6.

title: cheese pudding
directions: Layer all ingredients and bake at 375 degrees until brown.

title: eggplant with tomatoes
directions: In a large skillet or Dutch oven, fry the bacon until crisp and transfer to a small platter.
Add the onion and garlic to the fat in the pan and saute for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, pressing them down into the skillet with a spoon, so they they will yield a little juice.
Add the green pepper, celery, parsley, basil, eggplant, salt and pepper.
Cover tightly and cook until the eggplant is tender and most of the moisture has converted into sauce, about 25 minutes.
Crumble bacon over the top and serve hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Dice onion and place in pot with sausage. Brown onions on low flame. Pour in tomatoes and simmer on low flame. Stir frequently. Cook to desired thickness. (Add water if sauce is too thick.) Serve over pasta. Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken cheddar rice bake
directions: Melt margarine. Blend in flour and chicken broth. Stir in milk. Continue to stir until thickened. Remove from heat.
Add chicken and mushrooms. Arrange the cooked rice in a baking casserole. Spoon the chicken mixture over the top. Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked gouda en croute
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Remove wax casing from cheese. Separate crescent rolls into 2 rectangles.
Place rectangles together to form a square.
Seal perforations.
Spoon preserves over center of dough.
Place cheese in center of dough.
Bring corners together over cheese.
Pinch edges to seal.

title: presbyterian chicken
directions: Boil chicken; remove bone if any.
Cut in bite size pieces. Place in bottom of 8 x 8 dish.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Make stuffing according to box directions; put on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bran cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat egg in mixing bowl; add buttermilk and oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in muffin pan or cornstick pan sprayed with Pam for 20 minutes.
Yields 12.

title: coconut cake
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake cake mix as directed.
When cooked, leave in pan.
Mix pudding and milk; set aside.
Combine softened cream cheese and Cool Whip, then add pudding mix.
Frost cake in pan with above mixture.
Top with crushed pineapple, then sprinkle on coconut.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Mix margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, sour cream and zucchini.
Mix.
Put in 8 x 11-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done in center.
Frost with Zucchini Cake Frosting.

title: bacon crackers
directions: Break
crackers
into
separate
crackers.
Hold over a bowl and
sprinkle each section with cheese.
Put half a strip of
thin bacon
lengthwise
along the wafer, tucking the ends under well. Place on rack of large broiler pan near center of oven.
Bake
at 200° to 225° for 2 hours (maybe longer depending on
oven).
Bacon gets
very
crisp and crackers dry out. They are
very
tasty. Do
not
rush
these!
Can be prepared ahead and you can serve warm or cold.

title: oatmeal lace cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Stir in both sugars, then remove from heat.
Stir in oats and flour.
Stir in beaten egg and vanilla.
Refrigerate 10 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Line 2 cookie sheets with foil.
Lightly grease foil.
Drop by scant tablespoons onto 1 sheet, 7 to 8, leaving room to spread. Fill second sheet while first one bakes.
Bake 7 minutes.
Watch closely, cookies should be deep golden brown around edges.
Remove from oven.
Slide foil onto wire rack or counter.
Cool cookie sheet completely before adding next batch.
Cool cookies completely.
Carefully peel them off the foil.
Do not stack. Grease and reuse foil.
Store cooled cookies with wax paper between layers and in tightly covered container.
Yields approximately 52 cookies, 83 calories and 4 g fat.
Do not use margarine, quick cooking oats or dark brown sugar.
Bake on a clear, crisp, sunny morning.

title: spring flower cake
directions: Toss coconut with food coloring until evenly tinted. Set aside.

title: crab dip
directions: Drain crabmeat and mix with cream cheese.
Chill and cover top with cocktail sauce when ready to serve (in place of crab meat, cooked, chopped shrimp may also be used).

title: chewy pecan pie bars
directions: Pour melted butter into 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan and set aside. Combine brown sugar, flour, eggs, vanilla, salt and baking soda. Mix well. Stir in pecans. Spread over the butter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Remove from oven and immediately dust with confectioners sugar. Cool before cutting. Makes 2 dozen.

title: pineapple cream salad
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar, vinegar and salt.
Cook in double boiler, stirring until thickened.
Whip cream.
Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand at least 6 hours.
Serve on lettuce with Ritz crackers.

title: bread or rolls
directions: Mix together and let rise until double in bulk.
I make yeast in warm water first while shortening is melting to see if yeast rises.
Also I add a bit of sugar to yeast to speed up process. Be sure dough is not too warm when you add the yeast.
You can use this dough for coffee cake, rolls, tea rings, etc.

title: mama's pineapple puffs
directions: Mix egg and 1 cup sugar.
Add vanilla, flour and water. Drain and save juice of pineapple.
Squeeze pineapple to get all the juice out.
Add 1 cup sugar to pineapple juice.
Let it come to a boil.
Sit aside.
Take 1 lb. can Crisco and melt it in the frying pan.
Whenever hot drop by spoonfulls the batter into the hot Crisco.
Turn to brown on each side.
Pour juice mixture on both sides of puffs.

title: roquefort puffs
directions: In mixer beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add Roquefort and chives; blend well.
Add 2 tablespoons beaten eggs.
Mix well and chill until firm.
Toast bread rounds on one side; spoon mounds of cheese mixture on center of toasted side.
Place low under broiler until lightly browned.

title: butterscotch pudding
directions: Mix together the sugar, milk and cornstarch. Cook until thick, then add butter and vanilla.

title: oatmeal spice cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, butter, flour, eggs, spice and vanilla and beat.
Stir in oats, nuts and raisins.
Drop heaping tablespoons of dough on ungreased sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes (until bottoms and edges are brown).
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: reese's peanut butter balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix until well blended (except almond bark).
Chill for several hours.
Melt almond bark in microwave.
Roll the chilled peanut butter mixture into balls and dip in the chocolate until well coated.
Let excess chocolate drip off and drop onto waxed paper.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook beef; drain.
Combine taco seasoning with both cans of soup and add to beef.
Cook until all ingredients are combined. Place chips in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour soup mixture on chips and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: supreme turkey divan
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium saucepan, whisk together salad dressing and flour over low heat until smooth.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly over medium heat until thickened. Add Cheddar cheese; stir until melted.
Layer broccoli and rice in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with half of sauce.
Sprinkle with half of Parmesan cheese.
Top with turkey, remaining sauce and remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until sauce is bubbly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Prep time:
15 minutes. Cooking time:
30 minutes.
Contains about 440 calories per serving.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Combine all ingredients except certo in a large pot and bring to a boil; boil for twenty minutes.
Bring to a rolling boil and add certo, continue boiling for an additional five minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and mix with onion, carrot and 1/2 of herb stuffing mix.
Add soup to this and pour in casserole dish. Spread sour cream over top of mixture.
Mix stick of melted margarine with other 1/2 of herb stuffing and spread on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar until well blended.
Add oil.
Sift dry ingredients.
Alternate strawberries and dry ingredients.
Beat on low speed.
Add nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Makes 2 loaves.

title: easy apple coffee cake
directions: Combine egg, sugar and oil.
Add flour and cinnamon mixture. Add remaining ingredients and pour into greased and floured 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with mix of cinnamon and sugar if desired.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well and pour into freezer.
Fill to line with milk (about 1 gallon). Freeze.

title: ground nut stew(west african dish)
directions: About 2 hours before serving, in covered medium saucepan over low heat, cook meat, 1 1/2 cups water, salt and pepper for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Meanwhile, chop onions and tomatoes very fine.
In large skillet over medium-high heat in hot oil, cook onion-tomato mixture for 5 minutes.
Add meat mixture and peanuts. Cook about 20 minutes or until sauce cooks down slightly.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican stew
directions: Cook onion with meat until onion is tender and meat is brown. Drain.
Add all ingredients.
Cook until warm.

title: summertime squash pickles
directions: Stir salt into water in a very large bowl.
Add squash.
Weigh down with a dinner plate.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.

title: squash apple bake
directions: Cube squash and put in casserole.
Arrange apples on squash. Mix all the other ingredients and pour over the apples.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Put powdered sugar in glass dish. Make well in center. Put peanut butter in center; pour milk around peanut butter. Put pats of butter in corners. DO NOT STIR! Put in microwave for 4 1/2 minutes. Remove. Add vanilla. Then stir. Refrigerate until firm, about 2 hours.

title: hidden valley ranch seasoning
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients thoroughly.
Spread pretzels on cookie sheet and add dressing.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese ring
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except strawberry preserves, in a bowl.
Mix well and chill.
Form chilled mixture into a ring and re-chill.
Fill center of ring with strawberry preserves.
Serve with crackers; garnish with parsley.

title: cucumber sour cream salad
directions: Peel and thinly slice cucumbers.
Toss with salt.
Mix remaining ingredients and toss with cucumbers.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute
onion and celery in 2 tablespoons butter; spread 1/2 herb
dressing
mix
in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Heat 1/2 cup butter in 1 cup water and pour over mixture.
Mix chicken, sauteed onions
and
celery,
mayonnaise,
salt
and pepper. Spread over crumb mixture in baking dish.
Blend eggs and milk and
pour over mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: homemade chili burgers
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion.
Drain.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Cook in oil the onion, pepper and celery until golden.
Add meat and stir to break up as it cooks.
Drain.
Add tomatoes, macaroni, water, salt and pepper.
Stir.
Cook covered 15 to 20 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and place in casserole.
Mix crushed crackers and margarine and put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Lightly mix ingredients together.
Form medium size cakes. Coat crab cakes with cracker crumbs.
Fry in oil until golden brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: burger patties
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Form into patties and brown in oil.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Stir in seasonings and tomato sauce. Simmer slowly for 20 minutes.
Prepare 1/2 package of noodles according to directions.
Drain.
Arrange one layer of lasagna noodles in parallel strips in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with 1/3 meat mixture and 1/3 cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: peanutty crunch pie
directions: Mix together peanut butter and corn syrup, then add cereal. Mix until coated.
Butter pie pan before adding mixture, then add ice cream.

title: jelly cheese puffed pastry
directions: Fill 4-quart saucepot with oil on a medium flame.
Separate and flatten out biscuits (in order to enlarge).
Place a drop of cream cheese and/or jelly on the dough; fold over and pinch dough to seal edges.
Place in oil and fry, turning frequently to brown lightly.
Place on paper towel to drain oil off.
Top with powdered sugar.
Enjoy.
If you're on a diet serve them and run!

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; mix all ingredients except margarine and saltines.
Pour into 1, 2 or 3 casserole dishes.
Top with buttered saltine cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight; bake in moderate oven at 370° for 45 minutes.
This can be frozen without the topping.
Thaw in refrigerator; add topping just before baking.

title: homemade pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl; let stand 5 minutes. Add sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt and flour; stir until smooth. Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead until smooth. Cut dough into 18 pieces; roll each piece on a lightly floured surface into a 9-inch rope. Shape each rope as desired; place on greased baking sheet. Brush pretzels with egg; sprinkle with salt. Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cold red beet soup(saltibarsciac)
directions: Bring red beets to a boil in water, adding vinegar to the water.
In the water, also add the allspice, caraway seed, dill seed, scallions and dill.
While the red beets are boiling, peel and dice the (Kirby) cucumbers.
Put them in the sour cream and mix.
Let stand while you peel the red beets that are cooked.
Also dice them or slice them if you desire.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
After the red beets and broth are cool, add the sour cream and cucumber mix.

title: zucchini crabcakes(poor man's crabcakes)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into cakes or crab balls.
Fry and serve hot.

title: caramel pear pudding cake
directions: In a large bowl, stir flour, granulated sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and cloves.
Add milk; beat until smooth.
Stir in pears and pecans.
Turn into an ungreased 2-quart casserole.
In a separate bowl, combine brown sugar, butter and boiling water; pour evenly over batter.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: old fashioned peach cobbler
directions: Let 2 cups of sliced peaches stand in 1/2 cup sugar for 20 minutes.
Add a dash of cinnamon.
Melt 1 stick butter in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk with butter in baking dish.
Stir in peaches and sugar with other ingredients in baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Place half of this mixture in 8 x 8-inch greased baking dish.
Cover with cranberry sauce.
Spread half of oatmeal mixture over sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix, 1 egg and 1/3 cup oil until crumbly. Reserve 1 cup.
Press mixture in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: orange glaze
directions: Mix sugar and undiluted orange concentrate together.
Great for ice cream and cookies.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare pastry.
In large bowl, combine brown sugar, flour, corn syrup, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in margarine and pecans.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until center of pie is puffed and golden brown.
Cool.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: individual hamburger dinners
directions: Place hamburger patty on tinfoil (1 patty per 1 piece of foil). Top with carrots, onions, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Wrap foil around patty and vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Place on a foil-lined cookie sheet to catch extra drippings.)

title: pickled carrots
directions: Drain carrots reserving 1 cup liquid.
Combine carrots, reserved liquid, vinegar and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cool and refrigerate in covered bowl.
Drain before serving.

title: cinnamon marshmallow crispies
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Add marshmallows, stirring until completely melted.
Remove from heat; add Rice Krispies.
Mix completely.
Spread into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press down firmly with buttered spatula.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon/sugar mixture.

title: frozen bananas(microwave)
directions: Peel bananas and cut them in half crosswise.
Insert a popsicle stick into each half.
Melt morsels in a saucepan over low heat or microwave in glass dish or measuring cup.
Heat on High power for 1 minute.
Morsels will keep their shape until stirred. Add milk to the chocolate and stir until smooth.
Dip each banana in melted chocolate and roll it in pecans.
Place on a plate covered with wax paper or plastic.
Freeze for about 3 hours. Serves 4.

title: leslie's chocolate chip pie
directions: Cover pie crust with chocolate chips.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over the chips.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.
When the top turns gold, it is ready.
If it gets brown, it will be hard.

title: sausage ball appetizers
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Roll into balls, size of walnuts.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until brown.
Makes 4 dozen.
